The index begins with a broad universe of eligible emerging market companies, removes SOEs, and weights the remaining securities by modified float-adjusted market capitalization, subject to country and sector adjustments. This index is rebalanced annually. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund's total assets are invested in components of this index or investments with substantially similar economic characteristics. The fund is non-diversified.

name: First Trust S-Network Global E-Commerce ETF
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets in the common stocks and depository receipts that comprise the index. The index seeks to provide exposure to companies with securities listed on recognized global securities exchanges that are engaged in the global e-commerce industry. It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: ISHP invests in the largest stocks, by market capitalization, of the global e-commerce industry. The index includes companies primarily engaged in the following business segments: (1) content navigation, (2) online retail, (3) online marketplace, and (4) e-commerce infrastructure. Content navigation companies derive their revenues from advertisers paying to use the search results, social media feeds, email systems, banner ads, etc. to efficiently target their ads. The index ranks the companies in each segment by market-cap. Then, the top 15 companies from each of the four business segments are selected and equally weighted. The Index is rebalanced and reconstituted quarterly. Prior to Jan. 26, 2022, the fund name was First Trust Nasdaq Retail ETF (Ticker: FTXD). It followed the Nasdaq US Smart Retail Index, which selected US securities by liquidity and weighted them using multiple factors.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield (before the fund’s fees and expenses) of an equity index called the S-Network Global E-Commerce Index. The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets in the securities that comprise the index. The index seeks to provide exposure to companies with securities listed on major global recognized exchanges that are engaged in the global e-commerce industry. It is non-diversified.
merged_description: The fund seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield of an equity index focused on the global e-commerce industry. It aims to invest at least 90% of its net assets in the common stocks and depository receipts that comprise this index. The index provides exposure to companies engaged in global e-commerce by focusing on the largest stocks by market capitalization within four specific business segments: content navigation, online retail, online marketplace, and e-commerce infrastructure. The index selects the top 15 companies from each segment and weights them equally. The index is rebalanced and reconstituted quarterly, and the fund is non-diversified.

name: WisdomTree Emerging Markets ESG Fund
description_original: The fund is actively managed using a model-based approach. It seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing primarily in equity securities of issuers in emerging markets that exhibit certain characteristics that the fund's investment adviser believes to be indicative of positive future returns as well as incorporating favorable environmental, social, and governance ("ESG") characteristics based on a model developed by the adviser. The adviser employs a quantitative model to identify which securities the fund might purchase and sell and opportune times for purchases and sales. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
RESE is actively managed to invest in emerging market equities selected for various factors and ESG characteristics.

The fund is closing. The last day of trading on an exchange is January 26, 2024. RESE uses active management with a multi-factor approach to create its portfolio of emerging market stocks. The fund uses both fundamental and technical factors, such as value, quality, momentum and correlation. RESE also utilizes an ESG screen based on a composite sustainability score that is calculated by an independent third party ESG research. Holdings are weighted on a modified market-cap basis, giving heavier weight to constituents with higher market-cap and positive sustainability scores. Note: Prior to March 16, 2020, the fund traded as DVEM, held dividend-paying stocks and tracked the WisdomTree Emerging Markets Dividend Index.
merged_description: This actively managed strategy invests primarily in emerging market equities, using a quantitative, model-based approach. It selects stocks based on a multi-factor strategy targeting characteristics for positive future returns, including factors such as value, quality, momentum, and correlation. The strategy also integrates favorable environmental, social, and governance (ESG) characteristics, with holdings weighted on a modified market-cap basis that favors both higher market capitalization and positive sustainability scores. The fund is non-diversified. Note: The fund is closing, with its last day of trading on January 26, 2024.

name: KraneShares MSCI One Belt One Road Index ETF
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in instruments in its underlying index or in instruments that have economic characteristics similar to those in the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to measure the equity market performance of listed companies with high revenue exposure to the Chinese government's "One Belt, One Road" initiative, as determined by the provider of the underlying index.
description_eftcom:
OBOR tracks a market-cap-selected, tier-weighted index of companies likely to benefit from China's One Belt, One Road initiative.

OBOR targets companies likely to benefit from China`s One Belt, One Road initiative, which is a framework adopted by the Chinese government to emphasize cooperation and connection between China and other Eurasian countries. More specifically, the fund`s underlying index targets companies that stand to profit from China`s infrastructure spending. The portfolio allocates 45% of its weight to Chinese companies and 55% to non-Chinese companies. Within each category, individual constituents are market-cap weighted, with individual countries (other than China) capped at 10%.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the price and yield performance of the MSCI Global China Infrastructure Exposure Index. The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in instruments in its underlying index or in instruments that have economic characteristics similar to those in the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to measure the equity market performance of listed companies with high revenue exposure to the Chinese government's "One Belt, One Road" initiative, as determined by the provider of the underlying index.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to provide exposure to listed companies globally with significant revenue exposure to China's "One Belt, One Road" initiative, a framework emphasizing infrastructure development and cooperation across Eurasia. The fund aims to track the performance of an underlying index designed to measure the equity performance of companies poised to benefit from associated infrastructure spending. It invests at least 80% of its net assets in instruments that comprise this index or have similar economic characteristics. The index allocates its weight across a portfolio of approximately 45% Chinese and 55% non-Chinese companies, selected and weighted by market capitalization within tiers, with individual non-China countries capped at 10%.

name: Themes Cybersecurity ETF
description_original: The index is designed to provide exposure to companies that have business operations in the cybersecurity industry. The fund will invest, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in securities that comprise the index and in American Depositary Receipts (“ADRs”) and Global Depositary Receipts (“GDRs”) based on the securities in the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
SPAM seeks to track a concentrated index of stocks from developed markets that derive their revenues from digital security software. Stocks are weighted based on market capitalization.

SPAM is passively managed, providing targeted exposure to the largest companies, by market capitalization, in digital security software. In order to be considered for inclusion, a company must generate at least 50% of its revenue from the industry, define by RIBCS. All eligible securities are ranked and weighted by their market capitalization, selecting the top 35 names for inclusion in the index. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced on a quarterly bases in February, May, August, and November. Additionally, the fund may lend securities representing up to one-third of its total assets.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the performance, before fees and expenses, of Solactive Cyber Security Index. The index is designed to provide exposure to companies that have business operations in the cybersecurity industry. The fund will invest, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in securities that comprise the index and in American Depositary Receipts (“ADRs”) and Global Depositary Receipts (“GDRs”) based on the securities in the index. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This passively managed fund seeks to track a concentrated index focused on developed market companies operating in the digital security software and broader cybersecurity industry. To be included, companies typically derive a significant portion of their revenue from the sector, with the index comprising the top 35 names based on market capitalization and weighted accordingly. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in securities comprising the index, including American and Global Depositary Receipts, and is classified as non-diversified. The underlying index is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly in February, May, August, and November. Additionally, the fund has the ability to lend securities.

name: First Trust Expanded Technology ETF
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in the common stocks of companies identified by it’s investment advisor as either information technology companies or consumer discretionary and communication services companies whose operations are principally derived from and/or dependent upon technology (such companies are collectively referred to herein as “Expanded Technology Companies”). The fund’s investments will be concentrated (i.e., invest more than 25% of fund assets) in the industries or group of industries comprising the information technology sector. It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
XPND actively invests in US stocks whose businesses are derived from or dependent on technology.

XPND aims to provide an expanded tech exposure in the US large-cap segment. Aside from holding conventional technology stocks, the fund may also include tech-dependent companies that are classified as communication services or consumer discretionary (particularly internet & direct marketing retail) under GICS. XPND holds approximately 50 companies that are selected using a quantitative model, which considers factors such as return on equity, momentum and free cash flow growth. The resulting portfolio is generally market-cap-weighted with weights typically ranging from 0.25% to 4.50%. Since XPND is actively managed, the fund adviser has the discretion to adjust portfolio weights and exclude certain securities. The portfolio is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to provide long-term capital appreciation. The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in the common stocks of companies identified by it’s investment advisor as either information technology companies or financial companies and communication services companies whose operations are principally derived from and/or dependent upon technology ( “Expanded Technology Companies” ). The fund’s investments will be concentrated (i.e., invest more than 25% of fund assets) in the industries or group of industries comprising the information technology sector. It is non-diversified.
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks long-term capital appreciation by investing in US large-cap companies with businesses derived from or dependent on technology. It aims to provide expanded exposure beyond traditional information technology firms by including tech-reliant companies in sectors like communication services and consumer discretionary. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in common stocks of these companies, typically holding around 50 securities selected using a quantitative model considering factors such as return on equity, momentum, and free cash flow growth. The portfolio is generally market-cap-weighted, with adviser discretion over individual security weights and exclusions, and undergoes quarterly rebalancing and reconstitution. Classified as non-diversified, the fund maintains a concentration of over 25% in the information technology sector.

name: AAM S&P 500 High Dividend Value ETF
description_original: The index is a rules-based, equal-weighted index that is designed to provide exposure to the constituents of the S&P 500® Index that exhibit both high dividend yield and sustainable dividend distribution characteristics, while maintaining diversified sector exposure. At least 80% of the fund’s net assets, plus borrowings for investment purposes, will be invested in equity securities that (i) are included in the S&P 500 Index and (ii) have had a positive indicated annual dividend yield within the past year.
description_eftcom: SPDV follows an index of US companies that screens for fundamental factors. Index construction begins by selecting companies from the S&P500 index with high, positive dividend and free-cash-flow yields. Outliers are removed from the selection pool. Using a statistical normalization model, each security is scored based on its dividend and free-cash-flow yields. The top five constituents are selected from each sector and weighted equally. Diversifying the portfolio across economic sectors in this manner should help avoid value traps, though it also means that SPDV will underweight the largest sectors while overweighting the smallest. The index is reconstituted semi-annually.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the S&P 500 Dividend and Free Cash Flow Yield Index. The index is a rules-based, equal-weighted index that is designed to provide exposure to the constituents of the S&P 500® Index that exhibit both high dividend yield and sustainable dividend distribution characteristics, while maintaining diversified sector exposure. At least 80% of the fund’s net assets, plus borrowings for investment purposes, will be invested in equity securities that (i) are included in the S&P 500 Index and (ii) have had a positive indicated annual dividend yield within the past year.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to track a rules-based, equal-weighted index designed to provide exposure to S&P 500 companies exhibiting high dividend yield and sustainable dividend distribution characteristics. The index screens S&P 500 constituents for high, positive dividend and free-cash-flow yields using a statistical scoring model after removing outliers. It then selects the top five constituents from each sector, which are equally weighted. This sector-diversified approach aims to avoid value traps, although it typically leads to underweighting larger sectors and overweighting smaller ones compared to the broader S&P 500. The index undergoes semi-annual reconstitution. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in S&P 500 equity securities that have had a positive indicated annual dividend yield within the past year.

name: WisdomTree Battery Value Chain and Innovation Fund
description_original: The adviser employs a “passive management” investment approach designed to track the performance of the index. The index is designed to provide exposure to equity securities of exchange-listed companies globally, which are primarily involved in the investment themes of Battery and Energy Storage Solutions (“BESS”) and Innovation. The fund will concentrate its investments to approximately the same extent as the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: WBAT is passively managed to provide exposure to the global battery & energy storage solutions value chain. The index divides the value chain into four segments: (i) raw materials, (ii) manufacturing, (iii) enablers or building block components, and (iv) emerging technologies. The selection universe also includes companies which introduce or service innovative technologies. Eligible companies must derive at least 50% revenue from any of the value chain segments or from innovation. To select securities, the index ranks companies based on an intensity rating that indicates a companys involvement in the battery & energy storage solutions value chain, and a composite risk score which combines quality and momentum factors. The four value chain segments are initially weighted equally in the portfolio. Securities within each segment are then weighted according to an adjusted intensity rating, subject to a 3.5% single issuer cap. The index reconstitutes and rebalances semi-annually.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the WisdomTree Battery Value Chain and Innovation Index (“Index”). The adviser employs a “passive management” investment approach designed to track the performance of the index. The index is designed to provide exposure to equity securities of exchange-listed companies globally, which are primarily involved in the investment themes of Battery and Energy Storage Solutions (“BESS”) and Innovation. The fund will concentrate its investments to approximately the same extent as the index. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This passively managed fund seeks to track the price and yield performance of an index focused on global equity securities involved in the Battery and Energy Storage Solutions (BESS) value chain and Innovation. The index provides exposure to companies across four segments of the battery value chain—raw materials, manufacturing, enablers/components, and emerging technologies—as well as those introducing or servicing innovative technologies, selecting companies that derive at least 50% of their revenue from these areas. Securities are chosen based on an intensity rating reflecting involvement in the value chain and a composite risk score, with segments initially equally weighted and securities weighted by adjusted intensity, subject to a 3.5% single issuer cap; the index rebalances semi-annually. Reflecting the index's structure, the fund maintains a concentrated, non-diversified portfolio.

name: Vanguard High Dividend Yield Index Fund
description_original: The manager employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the index, which consists of common stocks of companies that pay dividends that generally are higher than average. The adviser attempts to replicate the target index by investing all, or substantially all, of the fund's assets in the stocks that make up the index, holding each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index.
description_eftcom:
VYM tracks the FTSE High Dividend Yield Index. The index selects high-dividend-paying US companies, excluding REITS, and weights them by market cap.

VYM offers a diversified, conservative approach to high dividend yield in a low-cost wrapper. The fund`s broad basket stems partly from its comparatively lax dividend screens: Firms are ranked by forecast dividends over the next 12 months, those in the top half are selected. Stocks that make the cut are weighted by market cap rather than dividends, an approach also used by our benchmark. As a result, the broad portfolio aligns well with our benchmark by firm size, yield, and sector exposure. REITs are out of bounds too, in keeping with the conservative approach. The fund is a possible choice for those looking for broad dividend focus.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the performance of the FTSE High Dividend Yield Index that measures the investment return of common stocks of companies that are characterized by high dividend yield. The manager employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the index, which consists of common stocks of companies that pay dividends that generally are higher than average. The adviser attempts to replicate the target index by investing all, or substantially all, of the fund's assets in the stocks that make up the index, holding each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index.
merged_description: This ETF employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the FTSE High Dividend Yield Index. It seeks to replicate the index by investing substantially all of its assets in the common stocks that make up the index, holding each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting. The index focuses on high-dividend-paying US companies, characterized by yields typically higher than average, and excludes REITs. Companies are selected based on forecast dividends, with those in the top half included and weighted by market capitalization, aligning its broad, diversified portfolio closely with its benchmark across size, yield, and sector exposure. This offers a conservative, low-cost option for investors seeking broad exposure to high dividend yield stocks.

name: Vanguard Industrials Index Fund Admiral Shares
description_original: The fund employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the MSCI US Investable Market Index (IMI)/Industrials 25/50, an index made up of stocks of large, mid-size, and small U.S. companies within the industrials sector, as classified under the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS). The Advisor attempts to replicate the target index by seeking to invest all, or substantially all, of its assets in the stocks that make up the index, in order to hold each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the performance of the MSCI US Investable Market Index (IMI)/Industrials 25/50. The fund employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the index, an index made up of stocks of large, mid-size, and small U.S. companies within the industrials sector, as classified under the GICS. The Advisor attempts to replicate the target index by seeking to invest all, or substantially all, of its assets in the stocks that make up the index, in order to hold each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index.
merged_description: This fund employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the MSCI US Investable Market Index (IMI)/Industrials 25/50. It seeks to invest substantially all of its assets in the stocks of this index, which is composed of large, mid-size, and small U.S. companies within the industrials sector as classified by the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS). The fund aims to hold these stocks in approximately the same proportion as their weighting in the index and is considered non-diversified.

name: iShares Global Comm Services ETF
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The index is designed to measure the performance of global equities in the communication services sector. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
IXP tracks a market-cap-weighted index of global communication services companies, drawn from 1,200 global stocks selected by S&P.

IXP delivers a market-cap weighted portfolio of global communication services stocks as defined by S&P. The well-established fund changed indexes on June 24, 2019 to a capped version which at quarterly rebalance limits single positions at 22.5% and caps aggregate positions over 4.5% at 45% total. Such index variants are not unusual and still allow for plenty of single-name impact. Moreover, stock selection resulting from the underlying industry classification system (GICS ) is likely a larger driver of returns. (Major changes in GICS communication sector occurred in Fall 2018.) The index pulls from a universe of 1,200 global stocks selected by S&P.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the S&P Global 1200 Communication Services 4.5/22.5/45 Capped IndexTM. The fund invests at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The index is designed to measure the performance of global equities in the communication services sector. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This fund aims to track an index that measures the performance of global equities within the communication services sector. It primarily invests at least 80% of its assets in securities of its underlying index or investments with substantially identical economic characteristics. The index is selected by S&P from a universe of 1,200 global stocks and is generally market-cap-weighted, but utilizes a specific capping methodology introduced in June 2019. This cap limits individual security weights to 22.5% and caps the aggregate weight of securities exceeding 4.5% at 45% during quarterly rebalances. Focused on this sector, the fund is classified as non-diversified, with stock selection notably influenced by the underlying industry classification system.

name: First Trust Indxx Innovative Transaction & Process ETF
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in common stocks and depositary receipts that comprise the index. The index is designed to track the performance of companies that are either actively using, investing in, developing, or have products that are poised to benefit from blockchain technology and/or the potential for increased efficiency that it provides to various business processes.
description_eftcom:
LEGR tracks an index of global equities selected based on their exposure to the development or usage of blockchain technology.

LEGR offers global exposure to firms with varying degrees of investment in blockchain technology. Various types of public information are used in this assessment including annual reports, press releases, industry reports, and news outlets. Based upon this research, firms are separated into three tiers of blockchain investment: Active Enablers, which are firms developing blockchain technology, products, or services, either for internal use or for sale, Active Users, firms using blockchain technology, generally supported by an Active Enabler, and Active Explorers, which are firms that have announced their intention to incorporate blockchain into their business, but without at least one active use case or test case. Active Enablers and Active Users are selected for inclusion in LEGR. Holdings are equally divided between Active Enablers and Active Users. Component securities within each grouping are equally weighted. The Index is rebalanced and reconstituted semi-annually.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield (before the fund's fees and expenses) of an index called the Indxx Blockchain Index (the "index"). The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in common stocks and depositary receipts that comprise the index. The index is designed to track the performance of companies that are either actively using, investing in, developing, or have products that are poised to benefit from blockchain technology and/or the potential for increased efficiency that it provides to various business processes.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to track the performance of an index composed of global companies involved in the development, usage, or investment in blockchain technology. The fund typically invests at least 90% of its assets in the stocks and depositary receipts of these index constituents. Companies are selected based on their active involvement in the blockchain ecosystem, identified through public information, and categorized into tiers like Active Enablers (developing the technology) and Active Users (using the technology). The portfolio includes companies from these categories, providing global exposure, and is constructed by equally weighting holdings within each category, with the overall portfolio equally divided between Enablers and Users. The index is rebalanced and reconstituted semi-annually.

name: Direxion Daily FTSE China Bull 3X Shares
description_original: The fund, under normal circumstances, invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowing for investment purposes) in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, exchange-traded funds ("ETFs") that track the index, securities of the index and other financial instruments that provide daily leveraged exposure to the index or to ETFs that track the index. The index consists of the 50 largest and most liquid public Chinese companies currently trading on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
YINN provides daily 3x leveraged exposure to a market-cap-weighted index of the 50 largest Chinese stocks traded in Hong Kong.

YINN is an aggressive daily bet on Chinese large-cap equities, delivering 3x leveraged exposure to about 50 large and liquid names traded in Hong Kong. The fund's underlying equity exposure doesn't aim for comprehensive all China exposure since it excludes A-shares traded on the mainland and names listed solely in the US. Given the underlying index, big sector bets can be expected. The fund rebalances its leveraged exposure daily, so over the long haul, compounding effects can lead to profound differences in expected returns relative to the index. Thus, it is not a buy-and-hold investment and should not be expected to provide index leverage returns greater than a one-day period. The index is rebalanced quarterly.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks daily investment results, before fees and expenses, of 300% of the daily performance of the FTSE China 50 Index. The fund, under normal circumstances, invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowing for investment purposes) in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and exchange-traded funds ("ETFs") that track the index, that, in combination, provide 3X daily leveraged exposure to the index, consistent with the fund's investment objective. The index consists of the 50 largest and most liquid public Chinese companies currently trading on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This fund seeks daily investment results that are 300% of the daily performance of an index composed of the 50 largest and most liquid public Chinese companies trading on the Hong Kong Stock Exchange. To achieve this 3x daily leveraged exposure, under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in financial instruments such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and ETFs that track the index. Focusing specifically on HKEX-listed names while excluding A-shares or US listings, this non-diversified fund represents an aggressive daily bet on Chinese large-cap equities and may involve significant sector concentration. Crucially, the fund rebalances its leveraged exposure daily, meaning it is designed for short-term use and should not be expected to provide returns simply equal to three times the index performance over periods longer than a single day due to the effects of compounding; it is therefore not suitable as a long-term buy-and-hold investment.

name: VictoryShares THB Mid Cap ESG ETF
description_original: The adviser pursues the fund’s investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its assets in equity securities of mid-cap companies. The adviser considers “mid-cap companies” to be companies with market capitalizations that, at the time of initial purchase, are within the capitalization range of companies comprising the Russell Mid Cap Index. Generally, the adviser expects the fund will hold approximately 30 securities. The equity securities in which the fund invests are primarily common stocks. In addition, the fund may invest in foreign securities, including ADRs and GDRs.
description_eftcom:
MDCP is an actively managed ETF that provides exposure to high-quality mid-cap US stocks with positive ESG ratings.

The security is being delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is April 23, 2025. MDCP actively invests in mid-cap stocks using a bottom-up, fundamental research investment process. The portfolio comprises about 30 stocks believed to offer the highest adjusted return, which is calculated by applying a proprietary quality assessment and risk measures to each securitys pre-adjusted expected return. The quality assessment identifies high-quality companies based on their management, financial strength, industry position, and ESG rating. The ESG rating is derived using a proprietary methodology from an internal financial materiality map that considers how material various ESG factors are to a companys specific industry. The fund focuses on common stocks and expects to invest only 10% or less in foreign securities, ADRs, and GDRs. On February 1, 2024, the fund dropped ESG from its name. This change did not affect the funds investment strategy.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks capital appreciation. The adviser pursues the fund’s investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its assets in equity securities of mid-cap companies. The adviser considers “mid-cap companies” to be companies with market capitalizations that, at the time of initial purchase, are within the capitalization range of companies comprising the Russell Mid Cap Index. Generally, the adviser expects the fund will hold approximately 30 securities. The equity securities in which the fund invests are primarily common stocks. In addition, the fund may invest in foreign securities, including ADRs and GDRs.
merged_description: This actively managed ETF seeks capital appreciation by investing primarily in equity securities of mid-cap companies, defined as those within the market capitalization range of the Russell Mid Cap Index at the time of purchase. Utilizing a bottom-up, fundamental research process, the fund aims to build a concentrated portfolio of around 30 stocks. Selection targets companies believed to offer high adjusted returns based on a proprietary quality assessment that considers management, financial strength, industry position, and ESG factors. While primarily holding common stocks, the fund limits foreign exposure, including ADRs and GDRs, to 10% or less. Please note that this fund is scheduled for delisting, with its last day of trading being April 23, 2025.

name: iShares Core Dividend Growth ETF
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The underlying index is a subset of the Morningstar® US Market IndexSM, which is a diversified broad market index that represents approximately 97% of the market capitalization of publicly-traded U.S. stocks.
description_eftcom:
DGRO tracks an index of US stocks that are selected by dividends, dividend growth and payout ratio, then weighted by dividend dollars.

DGRO offers a straightforward execution of a dividend growth strategy. The fund aims to find stocks that pay steadily increasing dividends by requiring a 5-year track record of increasing dividends while ensuring that the firms pay out no more than 75% of earnings. Both factors in tandem aim for sustainable growth. While mild sector bets abound, overall the fund looks pretty marketlike. The US total market space is an active battleground for a crowded space, and DGRO is placed competitively within the segment.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the Morningstar® U.S. Dividend Growth IndexSM. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The underlying index is a subset of the Morningstar® U.S. Market IndexSM, which is a broad market index that represents approximately 97% of the market capitalization of publicly-traded U.S. stocks.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to track the investment results of the Morningstar U.S. Dividend Growth Index, generally investing at least 80% of its assets in the index's component securities. The underlying index is a subset of the diversified Morningstar U.S. Market Index, which represents approximately 97% of the market capitalization of publicly-traded U.S. stocks. The index focuses on selecting U.S. stocks based on their dividend payments and growth, specifically requiring a minimum five-year track record of increasing dividends and a payout ratio below 75% to target sustainable dividend growth. Stocks meeting these criteria are weighted by dividend dollars, providing investors with a straightforward approach to accessing companies with a history of growing dividends while maintaining a market-like overall profile.

name: Pacer Military Times Best Employers ETF
description_original: The investment seeks to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the Military Times Best for VetsSM Index (the "index"). Normally at least 80% of the fund's total assets (exclusive of collateral held from securities lending) will be invested in the component securities of the index in the same approximate weight as such component securities. The index is generally composed of the U.S.-listed stocks of companies that have been included in the Best for Vets List for the last three consecutive years, have a minimum market capitalization of $200 million, and meet the index's liquidity threshold. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This investment product aims to track the performance of an index focused on U.S.-listed companies recognized for their support of veterans. It primarily holds stocks of companies that have consistently appeared on a relevant "Best for Vets" list for the past three years, meet specific minimum market capitalization requirements (at least $200 million), and satisfy liquidity criteria. The product typically invests at least 80% of its assets in the securities comprising this index, in similar proportions. It is classified as non-diversified.

name: iShares Exponential Technologies ETF
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is a subset of the Morningstar Global Markets Index (the “Parent index”).
description_eftcom:
XT tracks an equal-weighted index that provides exposure to firms from developed and emerging markets, which create or use exponential technologies as defined by Morningstar.

XT invests in firms involved with production and use of groundbreaking technologies or exponential technologies. Morningstar determines the related-themes and may revise it annually, the following themes are: big data and analytics, nanotechnology, medicine, networks, energy and environmental systems, robotics, 3-D printing, bioinformatics and financial services. Eligible stocks must be in the Morningstar Global Equity Index family. The selection and weighting of companies is done with a somewhat-opaque method, using fundamental research to score companies along a three-point scale based on exponential technology involvement while applying liquidity screens. It then ranks the remaining stocks by exposure to the exponential technology themes with bias to small caps, up to five stocks within each theme are considered until the final constituents reach 200. The Underlying Index is equal weighted and is reconstituted and rebalanced annually.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the Morningstar® Exponential Technologies IndexSM composed of stocks of developed and emerging market companies that create or use exponential technologies. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is a subset of the Morningstar Global Markets Index (the “Parent index”).
merged_description: This ETF seeks to provide exposure to companies involved with exponential technologies by tracking a related Morningstar index. Investing globally in developed and emerging markets, it targets firms that create or utilize groundbreaking technologies across defined themes like big data, robotics, and bio/nanotechnology. The index is equal-weighted and drawn from a broader Morningstar global index family. The fund generally invests at least 80% of its assets in index components or instruments with substantially identical economic characteristics. The underlying index employs a selection methodology that scores companies, applies liquidity screens, and includes a bias towards small-cap companies among its approximately 200 constituents, which are annually rebalanced and reconstituted.

name: Nuveen Sustainable Core ETF
description_original: The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund (“ETF”) that seeks to pursue its investment objective by investing, under normal market conditions, at least 80% of the sum of its net assets and the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes in equity securities of sustainable companies.
description_eftcom: NSCR utilizes an ESG factor model to evaluate companies based on their adherence to specific ESG themes. The fund targets large-cap US companies ranking in the top 50% of this model, emphasizing themes such as energy transition and innovation, inclusive growth, and strong governance. The selection process integrates quantitative models, fundamental research, and discretionary judgment exercised by the sub-adviser. While the fund seeks to capitalize on attractive investment opportunities within its universe, it acknowledges the qualitative and subjective nature of sustainable investing. Therefore, there is no guarantee that every investment will perfectly align with designated themes or maintain its ranking within the ESG factor model over time. Sustainable company determination utilizes proprietary models, fundamental research, and third-party data. The sub-adviser has the discretion to revise or modify themes based on market conditions, relevance, and other factors.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks favorable long-term total return. The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund (“ETF”) that seeks to pursue its investment objective by investing, under normal market conditions, at least 80% of the sum of its net assets and the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes in equity securities of sustainable companies.
merged_description: This actively managed exchange-traded fund seeks favorable long-term total return by investing primarily in equity securities of sustainable large-cap U.S. companies. Under normal conditions, it allocates at least 80% of its assets to this objective. The strategy identifies sustainable companies using proprietary models, fundamental research, and third-party data, specifically targeting large-cap U.S. firms based on an ESG factor model. This model evaluates companies on adherence to themes like energy transition & innovation, inclusive growth, and strong governance, aiming for those ranking in the top 50%. The investment selection process blends quantitative analysis, fundamental research, and discretionary judgment. While aiming to capitalize on attractive opportunities within this universe, the fund acknowledges the inherent subjectivity of sustainable investing, meaning investments may not always perfectly align with designated themes or maintain their ESG ranking. The sub-adviser retains discretion to modify themes based on market conditions.

name: Nuveen Winslow Large-Cap Growth ESG ETF
description_original: The fund is actively managed and seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing primarily in exchange-traded equity securities of large-cap U.S. companies that exhibit ESG characteristics. It, under normal market conditions, invests at least 80% of the sum of its net assets in exchange-traded equity securities of companies with large capitalizations at the time of purchase. The fund may invest up to 20% of its net assets in non-U.S. equity securities listed on a foreign exchange that trade on such exchange contemporaneously with the shares of the fund. It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
NWLG is an actively managed, non-transparent fund with exposure to US large-cap stocks screened for both growth and positive ESG characteristics. The fund utilizes the Natixis/NYSE non-transparent model.

NWLG primarily invests in large-cap US companies exhibiting positive environmental, social and governance (ESG) factors that are relevant to their long-term financial performance. The fund specifically screens the Russell 1000 Index for both quantitative (focuses on companies potential for above-average future earnings growth) and qualitative (consists of various ESG factors, as determined by independent ESG research providers) measures through a fundamental, bottom-up approach. An exclusionary screen is also applied to remove companies engaged in the manufacturing and production of: nuclear weapons, civilian firearms, tobacco and thermal coal. The fund is actively managed and may have a non-US exposure of up to 20%. Unlike traditional ETFs, NWLGs non-transparent structure does not disclose its actual holdings daily and instead publishes a proxy portfolio on its website. Actual holdings will be disclosed on a monthly basis with a 30-day lag.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to provide long-term capital appreciation. The fund is actively managed and seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing primarily in exchange-traded equity securities of large-cap U.S. companies that exhibit ESG characteristics. It, under normal market conditions, invests at least 80% of the sum of its net assets in exchange-traded equity securities of companies with large capitalizations at the time of purchase. The fund may invest up to 20% of its net assets in non-U.S. equity securities listed on a foreign exchange that trade on such exchange contemporaneously with the shares of the fund. It is non-diversified.
merged_description: This actively managed fund primarily seeks long-term capital appreciation by investing in large-cap U.S. companies screened for both growth potential and positive environmental, social, and governance (ESG) characteristics. Employing a fundamental, bottom-up approach, the fund utilizes quantitative and qualitative screening, including exclusionary filters for specific industries like nuclear weapons, civilian firearms, tobacco, and thermal coal. It typically invests at least 80% of its assets in U.S. large-caps but may hold up to 20% in non-U.S. equities. The fund is non-diversified and operates with a non-transparent structure, providing a proxy portfolio daily with actual holdings disclosed monthly on a 30-day lag.

name: Viridi Bitcoin Miners ETF
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets, plus borrowings for investment purposes, in securities of companies that are Bitcoin Miners. It may invest in U.S. equity securities and non-U.S. equity securities in developed markets, including via depositary receipts. The fund may invest in common stock of newly listed IPOs, IPO stocks derived from Special Purpose Acquisitions Corporations (“SPACs”), and securities that result from reverse mergers. It is non-diversified.
merged_description: This ETF is designed to provide focused investment exposure to companies primarily involved in Bitcoin mining. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets, plus any borrowings for investment purposes, in securities of these companies. The fund may invest in equity securities, including depositary receipts, of such companies located in the U.S. and developed non-U.S. markets. Additionally, it has the flexibility to invest in newly listed IPOs, including those derived from SPACs, and securities resulting from reverse mergers. This fund is classified as non-diversified.

name: VictoryShares Dividend Accelerator ETF
description_original: The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing, under normal market conditions, at least 80% of its assets in securities included in the Nasdaq Victory Dividend Accelerator Index (the "index"). The index utilizes a rules-based approach designed to identify dividend paying stocks with a higher likelihood of future dividend growth.
description_eftcom:
VSDA tracks an index of dividend-paying US large- and mid-cap stocks with a high likelihood of future dividend growth.

VSDA selects US large- and mid-cap companies that have grown their dividend successfully over the past five or more years. The fund selects 75 stocks ranked by a predictive model as most likely to continue to increase dividends year-over-year. The model incorporates 15 fundamental and technical metrics, including valuation, profitability, leverage, and stability factors. Holdings are weighted by a combination of yield and income stability. The Index is reconstituted annually and rebalanced quarterly.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that track the performance of the Nasdaq Victory Dividend Accelerator Index before fees and expenses. The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing, under normal market conditions, at least 80% of its assets in securities included in the Nasdaq Victory Dividend Accelerator Index (the "index"). The index utilizes a rules-based approach designed to identify dividend paying stocks with a higher likelihood of future dividend growth.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to track a rules-based index designed to identify dividend-paying US large- and mid-cap stocks with a high likelihood of future dividend growth. The index selects approximately 75 companies that have successfully grown their dividend for five or more years, using a predictive model incorporating 15 fundamental and technical metrics like valuation, profitability, leverage, and stability factors. Holdings are weighted by a combination of yield and income stability. The fund normally invests at least 80% of its assets in securities included in this index, which is reconstituted annually and rebalanced quarterly.

name: Fidelity Metaverse ETF
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the index and in depositary receipts representing securities included in the index. The index is designed to reflect the performance of a global universe of companies that develop, manufacture, distribute, or sell products or services related to establishing and enabling the Metaverse. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
FMET tracks a market cap-weighted index of equities that provides global exposure to the future state of the internet: the metaverse.

FMET holds stocks and depositary receipts of globally listed companies that develop, manufacture, distribute, or sell products related to the metaverse. Eligible companies must derive at least 50% of their revenue from (i) computing hardware, (ii) digital infrastructure, (iii) design & engineering software, (iv) gaming technology & software, (v) web development & content services, and (vi) smart phone & wearable technology. The index uses quality screens based on trailing or next 12-month revenues, operating cash flow, sales growth, and analyst coverage to filter out companies that pose significant risks. Then securities are ranked for thematic relevance, which is a composite of total significant revenue, percent of significant revenue, and a natural language processing (NLP) score. Approximately 50 stocks are selected and the portfolio is weighted according to market capitalization, subject to liquidity constraints and a 4.5% single weight capping. The index is rebalanced quarterly.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to provide investment returns that correspond, before fees and expenses, generally to the performance of the Fidelity Metaverse IndexSM. The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the index and in depositary receipts representing securities included in the index. The index is designed to reflect the performance of a global universe of companies that develop, manufacture, distribute, or sell products or services related to establishing and enabling the Metaverse. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This fund tracks a market cap-weighted index designed to capture the performance of global companies related to establishing and enabling the metaverse. It normally invests at least 80% of its assets in global stocks and depositary receipts included in this index. The index targets companies that derive at least 50% of revenue from categories such as computing hardware, digital infrastructure, gaming, and smart wearables. Companies are selected using quality screens and thematic relevance scores based on revenue analysis and NLP. Approximately 50 stocks are included and weighted by market capitalization, with a 4.5% single security cap. The fund is non-diversified and the index is rebalanced quarterly.

name: BlackRock ETF Trust
description_original: Under normal market conditions, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in equity securities issued by U.S. and non-U.S. technology companies in all market capitalization ranges, selected for their rapid and sustainable growth potential from the development, advancement and use of technology. The fund is non-diversified.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to provide long-term capital appreciation. Under normal market conditions, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in equity securities issued by U.S. and non‑U.S. technology companies in all market capitalization ranges, selected for their rapid and sustainable growth potential from the development, advancement and use of technology. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This fund seeks long-term capital appreciation by investing at least 80% of its assets in equity securities of U.S. and non-U.S. technology companies across all market capitalization ranges. These companies are selected for their potential for rapid and sustainable growth derived from their involvement in the development, advancement, and use of technology. The fund is non-diversified.

name: iShares Emerging Markets Infrastructure ETF
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents, as well as in securities not included in the index. It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
EMIF tracks a market-cap-weighted index of infrastructure companies operating in emerging markets.

EMIF provides concentrated exposure to 30 of the largest emerging market infrastructure firms. For EMIF, the infrastructure industry only spans three sectors: energy, transportation and utilities. Notably, the fund completely excludes telecom firms. EMIFs cherry-picked sector exposure and its small, 30-holding portfolio give the fund a narrower geographic scope. The funds index sets target weights for the three clusters20% for energy, 40% for transportation and 40% for utilitiesand then applies market-cap-weighting to each cluster. The index is rebalanced semi-annually.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the S&P Emerging Markets Infrastructure IndexTM, which is designed to track the performance of 30 of the largest publicly listed companies in the infrastructure industry in emerging markets. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. It is non-diversified.
merged_description: This ETF is designed to track the performance of an index focused on the emerging markets infrastructure sector. It targets the 30 largest publicly listed companies in this industry, concentrating solely on the Energy, Transportation, and Utilities sectors while deliberately excluding telecom firms. Holdings are weighted by market capitalization within specific sector clusters, and the underlying index is rebalanced semi-annually. The fund typically invests at least 80% of its assets in securities of its underlying index or those with substantially identical economic characteristics, with up to 20% allocated to other investments such as futures or cash. Reflecting its focused approach, the fund is considered non-diversified.

name: Invesco S&P SmallCap Industrials ETF
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the index. Strictly in accordance with its guidelines and mandated procedures, S&P Dow Jones Indices, LLC compiles, maintains and calculates the index, which is designed to measure the performance of securities of small-capitalization U.S. companies in the industrials sector, as defined by the Global Industry Classification Standard.
description_eftcom:
PSCI tracks a cap-weighted index of industrial stocks selected from the S&P SmallCap 600.

PSCI delivers traditional cap-weighted exposure to US industrial companies but just the small-caps. The industrials sector as classified by GICS are firms engaged in providing industrial products and services, including engineering, heavy machinery, construction, electrical equipment, aerospace and defense and general manufacturing. The Index is a capped version of S&P SmallCap 600. It limits single positions at 22.5% and caps aggregate positions over 4.5% at 45% total. The Index is rebalanced and reconstituted quarterly.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the S&P SmallCap 600® Capped Industrials Index. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the index. Strictly in accordance with its guidelines and mandated procedures, S&P Dow Jones Indices, LLC compiles, maintains and calculates the index, which is designed to measure the performance of securities of small-capitalization U.S. companies in the industrials sector, as defined by the Global Industry Classification Standard.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to provide focused exposure to small-capitalization companies within the U.S. industrials sector, as defined by the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS). It aims to track the performance of an index derived from the S&P SmallCap 600 universe. The index employs a modified capitalization-weighting methodology, which includes specific caps on individual security positions (limiting them to 22.5%) and aggregate positions over 4.5% (limited to 45%). The fund generally invests at least 90% of its total assets in the securities comprising this index.

name: Inspire Corporate Bond Impact ESG ETF
description_original: The fund generally invests at least 80% of its total assets in the component securities of the index. The index provider selects domestic corporate bonds issued by companies that have market capitalizations of $5 billion or more, have credit ratings of BBB- or higher from Standard and Poor’s or Baa3 or higher from Moody’s and which have an Inspire Impact Score® of zero or higher.
description_eftcom:
IBD tracks an equally weighted index of bonds issued by S&P 500-component companies that meet biblically responsible investing standards according to the Issuer.

IBD utilizes a principles-based bond strategy that aligns with evangelical Christian values defined by the issuer. Starting from a broad universe of USD-denominated, investment-grade corporate bonds issued by S&P 500 companies, the fund screens out firms with any participation in activities inconsistent with biblical values as defined by the index sponsor. The fund applies a proprietary model to score companies based on primary business activities, products and services, philanthropy, legal activities, policies, and practices. The fund holds 250 bonds from the 200 highest-scoring issuers, weighted equally across four maturity tranches of 0-3, 3-5, 5-7,and 7-10 years. The portfolio will have an average maturityof approximately5 years. IBD is a potential fit for investors who share the faith-based principles defined by the issuer. Between March 30 and August 19, 2022, the fund's name included a reference to 'ESG'. There was no change in the strategy.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to replicate investment results that generally correspond to the performance of the Inspire Corporate Bond Impact Equal Weight Index. The fund generally invests at least 80% of its total assets in the component securities of the index. The index Provider selects domestic corporate bonds issued by companies that are considered large capitalization companies, are rated investment grade quality from a bond ratings agency widely recognized in the financial services industry and which have an Inspire Impact Score of zero or higher.
merged_description: The fund seeks to replicate the performance of an equally weighted index focusing on domestic, USD-denominated, investment-grade corporate bonds. It targets large-cap companies, including S&P 500 components, meeting specific market capitalization and credit rating criteria (BBB-/Baa3 or higher). A key differentiator is its screening process, which aligns with faith-based or biblically responsible principles; it uses a proprietary model and an 'Inspire Impact Score' to identify issuers with a score of zero or higher and exclude those with activities inconsistent with defined values. Generally investing at least 80% of its assets in index components, the fund holds approximately 250 bonds from the 200 highest-scoring issuers, equally weighted across four maturity tranches (0-3, 3-5, 5-7, and 7-10 years) for an average portfolio maturity of about 5 years, making it a potential fit for investors prioritizing these values.

name: Direxion Daily Cnsmr Discret Bull 3XShrs
description_original: The fund, under normal circumstances, invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowing for investment purposes) in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, and securities of the index, ETFs that track the index and other financial instruments that provide daily leveraged exposure to the index or ETFs that track the index. The index is provided by S&P Dow Jones Indices (the "index provider") and includes domestic companies from the consumer discretionary sector. It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: WANT is a daily 3x leveraged bet on the S&P Consumer Discretionary Select Industry Index. WANT does this through a portfolio of swaps contracts that gets rebalanced at the end of each trading day. Because of this rebalancing, the funds return for periods longer than a day becomes path dependent, and is likely to be different from three times the return of the index for the same period. This makes WANT suitable primarily for short-term traders. The expense ratio has minimal impact on the cost of holding these funds for a short period of time, and would matter little to someone who is speculating on the short-term movements of consumer discretionary companies. Trading costs as reflected in spreads, and potential premium/discounts are the predominant consideration here.3
description_moringstar: The investment seeks daily investment results, before fees and expenses, of 300% of the daily performance of the Consumer Discretionary Select Sector Index. The fund, under normal circumstances, invests at least 80% of its net assets in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and ETFs that track the index, that, in combination, provide 3X daily leveraged exposure to the index, consistent with the fund's investment objective. The index is provided by S&P Dow Jones Indices (the "index provider") and includes domestic companies from the consumer discretionary sector. It is non-diversified.
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund seeks daily investment results corresponding to 300% (3X) the daily performance of an index tracking U.S. domestic companies from the consumer discretionary sector, provided by S&P Dow Jones Indices. Under normal circumstances, it invests at least 80% of its net assets in financial instruments, including swap agreements, securities of the index, and index-tracking ETFs, designed to provide this 3X daily leveraged exposure. The use of instruments like swaps requires daily rebalancing. Due to this daily compounding of returns, performance over periods longer than a single trading day can deviate significantly from three times the index's return for that same period, making the fund particularly suitable for short-term trading strategies. The fund is non-diversified.

name: MicroSectors FANG+ Index 3X Leveraged ETN
description_original: The notes are intended to be daily trading tools for sophisticated investors to manage daily trading risks as part of an overall diversified portfolio. The index is an equal-dollar weighted index designed to represent a segment of the technology and consumer discretionary sectors consisting of highly-traded growth stocks of technology and tech-enabled companies.
description_eftcom: FNGU offers 3x leveraged exposure to an index of FANG companies (Facebook, Apple, Amazon, Netflix, and Google [Alphabet Inc.]) and other companies that exhibit similar characteristics. Presumably, the index will always include these five companies, an index committee is responsible for selecting the additional names. Eligible stocks must be listed on a US exchange (although ADRs are acceptable), classified in either the technology or consumer discretionary sectors, and exhibit similar traits to other technology and internet companies. At least ten stocks must be included in the index, the number it held when the note launched so investors can expect a high level of concentration. All holdings are equally weighted. As a geared product, FNGU is designed as a short-term trading tool and not a long-term investment vehicle. Long-term returns could materially differ from those of the underlying index due to daily compounding.
merged_description: This ETF provides 3x leveraged exposure to an equally-weighted index focused on prominent technology and consumer discretionary companies. The index primarily targets major internet and technology firms, including key "FANG" stocks, along with others exhibiting similar growth characteristics within these sectors. Containing at least ten constituents, the index is highly concentrated. Designed specifically as a daily trading tool for sophisticated investors managing short-term risk, this leveraged product is not suitable for long-term investment due to the potential for significant differences in long-term returns compared to the underlying index resulting from daily compounding.

name: Simplify Volt TSLA Revolution ETF
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in Tesla-related instruments. The manager defines Tesla-related instruments as Tesla common stock, Tesla linked ETFs, Tesla linked swap contracts, and Tesla call options. The fund includes any leveraging effect of ETFs, swaps, and call options for the purposes of the 80% test. It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
TESL aims to provide capital appreciation by investing in shares of Tesla and related instruments. The fund uses a momentum-based proprietary daily algorithm to adjust the degree of its exposure to the underlying stock. It also utilizes a supplemental options strategy.

TESL seeks to provide exposure to the price returns of Tesla, Inc. (ticker: TSLA). The actively managed fund primarily invests in TSLA common stock and utilizes related instruments, such as TSLA-linked ETFs, swap contracts, and call options, to adjust total strategic exposure. The sub-adviser utilizes a proprietary strategy that adjusts the fund's exposure to the underlying stock based on momentum indicators, adopting an aggressive (150%), bullish (110%), or neutral (80%) posture. The fund aims to take advantage of the underlying stock's price volatility by periodically entering into leveraged positions. Additionally, the fund may invest up to 20% of its assets in a supplemental options strategy, where the fund buys exchange-traded and over-the-counter put and call options on TSLA to hedge against significant short-term price drops or capture significant price rises. Prior to November 1, 2024, the fund was named Simplify Volt RoboCar Disruption and Tech ETF. Before January 2, 2025, the fund traded under the ticker VCAR.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to provide capital appreciation. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in Tesla-related instruments. The manager defines Tesla-related instruments as Tesla common stock, Tesla linked ETFs, Tesla linked swap contracts, and Tesla call options. The fund includes any leveraging effect of ETFs, swaps, and call options for the purposes of the 80% test. It is non-diversified.
merged_description: This actively managed ETF seeks capital appreciation primarily by investing in Tesla common stock and related instruments, including linked ETFs, swap contracts, and call options, maintaining at least 80% exposure under normal circumstances. It employs a proprietary momentum-based strategy to adjust its exposure to the underlying stock, aiming to leverage positions based on market signals, potentially reaching up to 150%. The fund also utilizes a supplemental options strategy with puts and calls to manage risk and capture price movements. As a non-diversified fund, it offers concentrated exposure to its core holding and related strategies.

name: Global X Internet of Things ETF
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to provide exposure to exchange-listed companies in developed markets that facilitate the Internet of Things industry, including companies involved in wearable technology, home automation, connected automotive technology, sensors, networking infrastructure/software, smart metering and energy control devices. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
SNSR tracks a market-cap-weighted index composed of developed market companies that facilitate the Internet of Things industry.

SNSR provides exposure to developed markets companies involved in the Internet of Things (IoT) industry, which is the development of everyday objects having network connectivity, allowing them to send and receive data. Included in this industry are companies that provide wearable technology, home automation, connected automotive technology, sensors, networking infrastructure/software, smart metering, and energy control devices. These pure-play companies are weighted by market cap, with a maximum of 6% and a minimum of .3% for any given holding. In addition, companies that are identified as critical to the IoT ecosystem and have a business unit focused on IoT products and services may also be included if there are less than 100 pure-play companies. The index undergoes annual reconstitution and rebalance.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the Indxx Global Internet of Things Thematic Index. The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to provide exposure to exchange-listed companies in developed markets that facilitate the Internet of Things industry, including companies involved in wearable technology, home automation, connected automotive technology, sensors, networking infrastructure/software, smart metering and energy control devices. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to provide investment results that generally correspond to the performance of a market-cap-weighted index focused on developed market companies facilitating the Internet of Things (IoT) industry. Investing at least 80% of its assets in the securities of the underlying index, the fund offers exposure to firms involved in areas such as wearable technology, home automation, connected automotive technology, sensors, networking infrastructure/software, smart metering, and energy control devices. The underlying index primarily targets pure-play companies but may include others with significant IoT business units under certain conditions, applying market-cap weighting with constraints and undergoing annual reconstitution. The fund is non-diversified.

name: BondBloxx B Rated USD High Yield Corporate Bond ETF
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes) in high-yield, below-investment grade bonds denominated in U.S. dollars of corporate issuers, either directly or indirectly (e.g., through derivatives). It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
XB tracks a market value-weighted index that specifically invests in USD-denominated corporate bonds with a credit rating of B (or its equivalent), based on an average of three main credit rating providers.

XB is part of an ETF suite that targets specific niches of the high-yield corporate bond market. This fund invests in USD-denominated corporate bonds that are rated B1 through B3, based on an average of Moodys, S&P, and Fitch. Eligible debt securities must be issued by companies having risk exposures as FX-G10 member countries, with at least $250 million outstanding face value. Bonds should have a maturity of at least 18 months at the time of issuance and at least one year remaining to maturity. Holdings are weighted according to market value, with each issuer capped at 2%. The fund has no limit to the number of issuers to be selected. If fewer than 50 qualify for inclusion, holdings will be weighted equally. The fund may invest up to 20% of its net assets in derivatives such as swaps, options, and futures contracts. Note: Although cash flows from bond payments are retained until each monthly rebalancing, it does not earn any reinvestment income while being held in the index.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the ICE BofA Single-B US Cash Pay High Yield Constrained Index composed of B (or its equivalent) fixed rate U.S. dollar-denominated, high yield corporate bonds. The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes) in high-yield, below-investment grade bonds denominated in U.S. dollars of corporate issuers, either directly or indirectly (e.g., through derivatives). It is non-diversified.
merged_description: This fund seeks to track the performance of an index focused on a specific, niche segment of the U.S. dollar-denominated corporate high-yield bond market. It primarily targets fixed-rate corporate bonds rated B or equivalent, based on average ratings from major credit providers, specifically within the B1 through B3 range. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in these below-investment grade bonds, either directly or indirectly, utilizing tools such as derivatives, and is classified as non-diversified. Eligible bonds must meet specific criteria, including requirements regarding issuer risk exposure to G10 countries, a minimum outstanding face value of $250 million, and at least one year remaining to maturity. Holdings in the index it tracks are weighted by market value, subject to a 2% cap per issuer, with an equal weighting applied if fewer than 50 bonds qualify. Cash flows from bond payments are held until monthly rebalancing and do not earn reinvestment income during this period.

name: Vanguard Industrials Index Fund
description_original: The fund employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the MSCI US Investable Market Index (IMI)/Industrials 25/50, an index made up of stocks of large, mid-size, and small U.S. companies within the industrials sector, as classified under the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS). The Advisor attempts to replicate the target index by seeking to invest all, or substantially all, of its assets in the stocks that make up the index, in order to hold each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: The fund provides broad, pure-play exposure to industrials companies with an all-cap exposure that reach all the way down to micro-caps. The portfolio is highly representative of its sector. The underlying index uses the GICS classification to include companies that manufacture and distribute capital goods and companies that offer construction and engineering services. Certain investment limits are applied for RICs to help ensure diversification.
