Holdings, which are market-cap-weighted, have no more than 25% of the value to a single issuer and the sum of the weights of all issuers with more than 5% cannot exceed 50% of total assets. The index is rebalanced quarterly.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the performance of the MSCI US Investable Market Index (IMI)/Industrials 25/50. The fund employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the index, an index made up of stocks of large, mid-size, and small U.S. companies within the industrials sector, as classified under the GICS. The Advisor attempts to replicate the target index by seeking to invest all, or substantially all, of its assets in the stocks that make up the index, in order to hold each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index.
merged_description: This fund employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the MSCI US Investable Market Index (IMI)/Industrials 25/50. The index provides broad, pure-play exposure to the U.S. industrials sector, encompassing large, mid-size, small, and micro-cap companies as classified under the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS), including those involved in manufacturing capital goods or offering construction and engineering services. The fund aims to replicate the target index by investing substantially all of its assets in the index constituents in approximately the same proportion as their market-cap weighting. This weighting is subject to diversification limits where no single issuer exceeds 25% and the sum of issuers over 5% does not exceed 50% of total assets. The index is rebalanced quarterly.

name: iShares International Developed Property ETF
description_original: The fund generally invests at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents, as well as in securities not included in the index, but which BFA believes will help the fund track the index.
description_eftcom:
WPS tracks a market-cap-weighted index of companies that own or develop real estate throughout the developed world, excluding the United States.

The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is August 12, 2024.WPS is iShares' 'other' ex-US real estate fund. The fund tracks an S&P index of developed ex-US real estate, using a very simple methodology to construct its portfolio: selecting and weighting publicly-traded companies based on market-cap. It may invest in large-, mid and small-capitalization companies. It isn't constructed significantly differently than IFGL, its sister fund, but if the details of the index appeal specifically to your investment thesis, WPS is a viable option. Rebalancing occurs annually.
merged_description: This ETF tracks a market-cap-weighted index focused on publicly-traded companies that own or develop real estate in the developed world, specifically excluding the United States. The fund typically invests at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of this index and may include large, mid, and small-capitalization companies. However, this security has been delisted, with its last day of trading on an exchange being August 12, 2024.

name: Morgan Creek - Exos SPAC Originated ETF
description_original: The fund is an actively-managed ETF that seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing primarily in U.S.-listed special purpose acquisition companies ("SPACs") and in companies that have merged with or been acquired by a SPAC. A SPAC is a "blank check" company with no commercial operations that is designed to raise capital via an initial public offering ("IPO") for the purpose of engaging in a merger, acquisition, reorganization, or similar business combination (a "Combination") with one or more operating companies. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This actively-managed ETF is primarily focused on investing in U.S.-listed Special Purpose Acquisition Companies (SPACs) and the companies that have completed a business combination, such as a merger or acquisition, with a SPAC. It targets SPACs, defined as "blank check" entities raising capital via IPOs to combine with operating businesses, thereby seeking opportunities related to this market process. The fund is classified as non-diversified.

name: ProShares Ultra Technology
description_original: The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should produce daily returns consistent with the fund's investment objective. The index is designed to measure the stock performance of U.S. companies in the technology industry. Component companies include, among others, those involved in computers and office equipment, software, communications technology, semiconductors, diversified technology services and Internet services. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
ROM provides 2x leveraged exposure to a market-cap-weighted index that measures the performance of large US technology companies.

ROM provides 2x levered exposure to the S&P Technology Select Sector Index, with daily leverage resets. Like all levered funds, it tends to underperform in volatile markets if held for longer than its reset period, and is more suitable for short-term trading positions. The underlying index is market-cap weighted and typically includes companies engaged in IT services, software, communications equipment, technology, hardware, storage & peripherals, electronic equipment, instruments, & components, and semiconductors & semiconductor equipment. The fund reflects the concentrated nature of a space dominated by the tech industry leaders selected and weighted by market cap. Prior to March 20, 2023, the fund provided exposure to the Dow Jones U.S. Technology Index.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks daily investment results that correspond to two times (2x) the daily performance of the S&P Technology Select Sector Index. The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should produce daily returns consistent with the Daily Target. The index is designed to measure the performance of information technology companies included in the S&P 500 Index. Under normal circumstances, the fund will obtain leveraged exposure to at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This ETF seeks daily investment results corresponding to two times (2x) the daily performance of the S&P Technology Select Sector Index, which measures the performance of information technology companies included in the S&P 500 Index. It provides 2x leveraged exposure with daily resets, achieved by investing in financial instruments designed to produce daily returns consistent with this target. Due to the effects of daily leverage resets, the fund is generally more suitable for short-term trading positions and may underperform over longer holding periods, particularly in volatile markets. The underlying index is market-cap weighted and focuses on US technology companies across sub-sectors such as software, hardware, semiconductors, communications technology, and IT services. The fund is non-diversified.

name: SPDR MSCI ACWI Climate Paris Aligned ETF
description_original: The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index. The index is designed to exceed the minimum standards for a “Paris-Aligned Benchmark” under the EU BMR. A Paris-Aligned Benchmark is designed to align with a principal objective of the Paris Agreement to limit the increase in the global average temperature to well below 2 degrees Celsius above pre-industrial levels.
description_eftcom:
NZAC tracks a tier-weighted index of large- and mid-cap global stocks selected and weighted based on ESG criteria that are compatible with the Paris Climate Agreement and carbon reduction goals.

NZAC takes a climate approach to investing in the global large- and mid-cap space. The index initially screens out stocks from the MSCI ACWI Index, that are involved in controversial weapons, tobacco, thermal coal mining, oil and gas, and power generation, as well as severe ESG controversies and environmental issues. The portfolio selection and weighting utilize an optimization process that minimizes exposure to physical and transition risks of climate change while providing exposure to sustainable opportunities. Optimization constraints include greenhouse gas intensity reduction, low carbon transition score, climate value-at-risk, green revenue, and fossil fuels-based revenue. The index also uses an optimizer to maintain the sector weighting in the parent index. The fund uses a sampling strategy to track its index, which is rebalanced semi-annually. Before April 22, 2022, NZAC traded as SPDR MSCI ACWI Low Carbon Target ETF (LOWC) and tracked the MSCI ACWI Low Carbon Target Index.
merged_description: This ETF provides exposure to a global portfolio of large- and mid-cap stocks chosen and weighted based on environmental, social, and governance (ESG) criteria with a specific focus on climate change and carbon reduction goals. Designed to align with the Paris Climate Agreement objective to limit global temperature increases, the underlying index initially screens out companies involved in controversial weapons, tobacco, thermal coal, oil and gas, and power generation, alongside those with severe ESG or environmental controversies. Utilizing an optimization process, the portfolio minimizes exposure to climate-related risks while seeking sustainable opportunities based on metrics such as greenhouse gas intensity, low carbon transition scores, and green revenue, all while aiming to maintain sector weights comparable to a broad global equity index. The fund invests at least 80% of its assets in the securities of this index, which is structured to exceed the minimum standards for a "Paris-Aligned Benchmark" under the EU BMR.

name: Pacer PE/VC ETF
description_original: A strategy driven exchange traded fund that aims to deliver a return similar to Private Equity (PE) and Venture Capital (VC) investments through publicly traded securities.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the FTSE PE/VC Index. The index is a rules-based index that aims to provide exposure to a portfolio that mimics the returns of a theoretical investment in a diversified pool of private equity and venture capital-backed companies. Under normal circumstances, the fund will seek to invest at least 80% of the fund’s total assets in a combination of publicly traded equities, ETFs and futures contracts that provide exposure to the private equity and venture capital markets. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This strategy-driven exchange-traded fund aims to provide exposure to and mimic the returns of private equity and venture capital investments. It seeks to achieve this by primarily investing in publicly traded securities, including equities, ETFs, and futures contracts that offer exposure to these markets, normally allocating at least 80% of its total assets this way. The fund seeks to track the total return performance of a specific rules-based index designed to represent a theoretical investment in a diversified portfolio of private equity and venture capital-backed companies. The fund is non-diversified.

name: IQ Candriam ESG International Equity ETF
description_original: The Advisor employs a "passive management"?-?or indexing?-?investment approach designed to track the performance of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to deliver exposure to equity securities of companies meeting environmental, social and corporate governance (ESG) criteria developed by Candriam and weighted using a market-capitalization weighting methodology.
description_eftcom:
IQSI tracks a proprietary index of developed-market stocks selected by ESG criteria and weighted by market-cap.

IQSI is an index-tracking fund designed to deliver exposure to international developed companies meeting environmental, social, and corporate governance criteria developed by IndexIQ and Candriam. To form the initial index universe, the fund combines sector-specific analysis and ranking of issuer-specific factors, like corporate governance and labor practices, along with a macro analysis of the issuers exposure to global sustainability trends, including health and wellness. Companies in the top 70% within each sector are selected. Companies are further screened based on any continued and significant non-compliance to Candriams ESG criteria to exclude from the final index. The index is market-cap weighted with 10% cap placed on each security. IQSI is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly. Prior to Aug. 28, 2024, the fund name was branded under IndexIQ.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks investment results that track (before fees and expenses) the price and yield performance of its underlying index, the NYLI Candriam International Equity Index. The Advisor employs a "passive management" - or indexing - investment approach designed to track the performance of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to deliver exposure to equity securities of companies meeting environmental, social and corporate governance (ESG) criteria developed by Candriam and weighted using a market-capitalization weighting methodology.
merged_description: This ETF employs a passive, index-tracking investment approach designed to provide exposure to developed-market equity securities selected based on environmental, social, and corporate governance (ESG) criteria. The rigorous ESG methodology, developed with input from Candriam and others, involves detailed sector and issuer analysis, evaluating factors like governance, labor practices, and sustainability trends. Companies are generally chosen from top performers within their sector and excluded for significant non-compliance. Constituents are weighted by market capitalization, subject to a 10% cap per security, and the index is typically rebalanced quarterly.

name: Fidelity Dividend ETF for Rising Rates
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the underlying index and in depository receipts representing securities included in the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to reflect the performance of stocks of large and mid-capitalization dividend-paying companies that are expected to continue to pay and grow their dividends and have a positive correlation of returns to increasing 10-year U.S. Treasury yields.
description_eftcom:
FDRR tracks an index of large- and mid-cap companies in developed nations that exhibit strong dividend characteristics and have a positive correlation to increasing 10-year US Treasury yields.

FDRR invests in US and developed international equities that exhibit strong dividend characteristics and a positive correlation to increasing 10-year US Treasury yields. The selection universe begins with 1,000 of the largest US stocks and the largest 1,000 developed-market international stocks by market capitalization. These stocks are scored and selected according to their dividend yield, dividend payout ratio, dividend growth, and their correlation to increasing 10-year US Treasury yields. Each sector maintains its weight relative to the broader equity market, and each stock within each sector receives a modified market capitalization weight plus an equal overweight adjustment within each sector. This avoids concentration to the large-cap constituents. FDRR invests mostly in US stocks, with a 10% maximum on international stocks, as well as a 35% cap on any individual sector. The index is rebalanced annually.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to provide investment returns that correspond, before fees and expenses, generally to the performance of the Fidelity Dividend Index for Rising Rates℠. The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in securities included in the underlying index and in depository receipts representing securities included in the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to reflect the performance of stocks of large and mid-capitalization dividend-paying companies that are expected to continue to pay and grow their dividends and have a positive correlation of returns to increasing 10-year U.S. Treasury yields.
merged_description: This fund seeks to mirror the performance of an index focused on large and mid-capitalization companies in developed nations. It targets those exhibiting strong dividend characteristics—like yield, payout, and growth—that also show a positive correlation to increasing 10-year U.S. Treasury yields. The selection process involves scoring stocks from a broad universe of large US and developed international equities. Portfolio construction emphasizes maintaining sector weights relative to the broader market while employing a weighting scheme within sectors to avoid concentration, primarily focusing on US stocks with limited international exposure (maximum 10%) and a cap on individual sectors (maximum 35%). The fund normally invests at least 80% of its assets in the securities of this underlying index, which is rebalanced annually.

name: iShares Inflation Hedged U.S. Aggregate Bond ETF
description_original: The underlying index is designed to minimize the inflation risk of a portfolio composed of U.S. dollar-denominated, investment-grade bonds. The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in component securities and instruments in the fund’s underlying index. It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
AGIH tracks an index that holds the iShares Core US Aggregate Bond ETF (AGG), which targets USD-denominated, investment-grade bonds, while mitigating inflation risk through swaps.

AGIH follows an index that combines a long position in iShares Core US Aggregate Bond ETF (AGG) with an overlay of inflation swaps. The fund includes a fixed number of AGGs shares and a series of up to 10 inflation swap contracts with different maturities, intended to hedge the portfolios inflation risk at key points on the yield curve. By entering these swaps, the fund agrees to give up a portion of the fixed payments it receives from AGGs bond portfolio in exchange for floating payments tied to the inflation rate. Since inflation is already priced into the market for bonds, the fund effectively hedges inflation expectations rather than the inflation rate itself. Thus, even if inflation rises, AGIH will underperform AGG if the rise is less than expected, and will outperform (before costs) when inflation exceeds expectations. Swaps are rebalanced daily and restructured monthly. Due to the potential use of futures and options, the fund is registered as a commodity pool.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the BlackRock Inflation Hedged U.S. Aggregate Bond Index designed to minimize the inflation risk of a portfolio composed of U.S. dollar-denominated, investment-grade bonds. The underlying index is designed to minimize the inflation risk of a portfolio composed of U.S. dollar-denominated, investment-grade bonds. The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in component securities and instruments in the fund’s underlying index. It is non-diversified.
merged_description: This ETF is based on a portfolio of U.S. dollar-denominated, investment-grade bonds and is specifically designed to mitigate their inflation risk. It seeks to track an index reflecting this strategy, which is primarily achieved through an overlay of inflation swaps. These swaps aim to hedge inflation expectations by exchanging fixed payments from the bond holdings for payments tied to inflation, meaning the fund's performance relative to a standard bond fund is influenced by whether actual inflation exceeds or falls short of expectations. Under normal circumstances, it invests at least 80% of its assets in accordance with its index. The fund is non-diversified and, utilizing derivatives like swaps, is registered as a commodity pool.

name: RiverNorth Enhanced Pre-Merger SPAC ETF
description_original: Under normal market conditions, the fund seeks to invest primarily in units made up of common stock, warrants and rights of U.S.-listed special purpose acquisition companies (“SPACs”). In seeking to achieve the fund’s investment objective, the sub-adviser will monitor the fund’s portfolio and adjust positions based on changes in expectations of the investments or the availability of better alternatives. At least 80% of the fund’s net assets, plus borrowings for investment purposes, will be invested in Pre-Merger SPACs. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: SPCZ actively invests in equities and warrants of US-listed pre-combination SPACs, which are those seeking or have not yet completed a combination with a target. The fund advisers combine quantitative and qualitative analysis, with fundamental and technical analysis to assess the relative risk/reward potential of its investment universe, and to select those SPACs with the greatest potential returns. Sponsors of these SPACs are also closely evaluated based on the teams strategy, experience, deal flow, and demonstrated track record in building enterprise value. History of a company's growing operating business is also considered. Moreover, the advisers will evaluate a SPACs market value relative to the value of the funds share of the SPAC to realize additional value. In managing the fund, the sub-adviser monitors the portfolio and adjusts positions based on expected returns or availability of better alternatives.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to preserve capital and provide incremental total return. Under normal market conditions, the fund seeks to invest primarily in units made up of common stock, warrants and rights of U.S.-listed special purpose acquisition companies (“SPACs”). In seeking to achieve the fund’s investment objective, the sub-adviser will monitor the fund’s portfolio and adjust positions based on changes in expectations of the investments or the availability of better alternatives. At least 80% of the fund’s net assets, plus borrowings for investment purposes, will be invested in Pre-Merger SPACs. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks to preserve capital and provide incremental total return by investing primarily in U.S.-listed Pre-Merger special purpose acquisition companies (SPACs). It focuses on their units, common stock, warrants, and rights, with at least 80% of its net assets concentrated in these Pre-Merger SPACs. The fund utilizes a blend of quantitative, qualitative, fundamental, and technical analysis to evaluate risk/reward and select potential investments, carefully assessing sponsors based on experience, strategy, and track record, and considering market value relative to the value of the underlying SPAC. The portfolio is continuously monitored, and positions are adjusted based on evolving expectations or alternative opportunities. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Valkyrie Balance Sheet Opportunities ETF
description_original: The fund is an actively-managed exchange-traded fund (“ETF”) that will invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in the securities of U.S. operating companies that have innovative balance sheets, which the fund’s adviser, Valkyrie Funds LLC (“Valkyrie” or the “Adviser”), consider to be operating companies that directly or indirectly invest in, transact in, or otherwise have exposure to bitcoin (such as bitcoin custodians, exchanges or traders). It is non-diversified.
merged_description: This actively-managed exchange-traded fund seeks to invest primarily in U.S. operating companies that have direct or indirect exposure to bitcoin, reflecting what is considered an "innovative balance sheet" strategy. These companies may engage in bitcoin investment, transactions, or provide related services such as custody or exchange operations. The fund commits at least 80% of its net assets, plus borrowings for investment, to these securities and operates on a non-diversified basis.

name: Cambria Global Tail Risk ETF
description_original: Under normal market conditions, the fund’s bond portfolio invests at least 40% of its total assets in investment grade, intermediate U.S. treasuries and TIPS and at least 40% of its total assets in ex-U.S. sovereign bonds, including investment grade and non-investment grade bonds issued by developed and emerging market governments with short and intermediate durations. The investment adviser intends to spend approximately one percent of the fund’s total assets per month to purchase put options.
description_eftcom:
FAIL aims to provide a defensive approach to global ex-US equities by actively managing put options with similar exposure and managing the collateral of the fund consisting mostly of cash and government bonds.

The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is January 8, 2025. FAIL is a global version of ETF: TAIL from the same issuer. The fund holds a portfolio of primarily cash and government bonds from both developed and emerging markets, but the primary strategy of the fund involves investing one percent of its holdings every month in at-the-money or out-of-the-money put options on stock indices or US-listed ETFs in the global ex-US space. The main purpose behind holding these options is hedging a portfolio against significant negative movement in the value of global ex-US equities, commonly referred to as global tail risk. Cambria intends to target options that are 0 to 30% out of the money. FAIL is an actively-managed fund that seeks to provide income and capital appreciation. Prior to March 15, 2021, FAIL was a fixed-income ETF under ticker: SOVB and traded as Cambria Sovereign Bond ETF.
merged_description: This actively managed fund provides a defensive approach to global ex-US equities by hedging against significant negative movement, commonly referred to as global tail risk. It achieves this by managing a portfolio consisting primarily of fixed-income assets and strategically purchasing put options. The fixed-income portion invests at least 40% of total assets in investment grade, intermediate U.S. treasuries and TIPS, and at least 40% in ex-U.S. sovereign bonds from developed and emerging markets across investment grade and non-investment grade ratings, with short and intermediate durations. Approximately one percent of the fund’s total assets is intended to be spent per month on purchasing at-the-money or out-of-the-money (targeting 0-30% OTM) put options on global ex-US stock indices or US-listed ETFs, specifically designed to protect against downside movements. The fund seeks to provide income and capital appreciation.

name: Vanguard Energy Index Fund Admiral Shares
description_original: The fund employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the MSCI US Investable Market Index (IMI)/Energy 25/50, an index made up of stocks of large, mid-size, and small U.S. companies within the energy sector, as classified under the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS). The Advisor attempts to replicate the target index by seeking to invest all, or substantially all, of its assets in the stocks that make up the index, in order to hold each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the performance of the MSCI US Investable Market Index (IMI)/Energy 25/50. The fund employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the index, an index made up of stocks of large, mid-size, and small U.S. companies within the energy sector, as classified under the GICS. The Advisor attempts to replicate the target index by seeking to invest all, or substantially all, of its assets in the stocks that make up the index, in order to hold each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: Employing an indexing investment approach, this fund is designed to track the performance of the MSCI US Investable Market Index (IMI)/Energy 25/50. This index represents large, mid-size, and small U.S. companies within the energy sector, as classified by the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS). To achieve its goal, the fund attempts to replicate the index by investing substantially all its assets in the index's constituent stocks in similar proportions to their weighting. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Invesco International Dividend Achievers ETF
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of Global Depositary Receipts (“GDRs”) that are listed on the London Stock Exchange (“LSE”) or the London International Exchange, and American Depositary Receipts (“ADRs”) and non-U.S. common or ordinary stocks, limited partnership interests and shares of limited liability companies that are listed on the NYSE.
description_eftcom:
PID tracks a dividend-yield-weighted index of foreign securities with high dividend growth.

PID offers exposure to equities with growing dividends that are determined as Dividend Achievers. In addition to its requirement for five years of dividend growth, the fund gets its exposure to non-US international firms that trade in the United States and the London Stock Exchange, which includes ADRs, GDRs and common stocks. The index is rebalanced quarterly starting every February based on the trailing 12-month dividend yield of each security as compared to the dividend yield of all its components.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the NASDAQ International Dividend AchieversTM Index. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of Global Depositary Receipts (“GDRs”) that are listed on the London Stock Exchange (“LSE”) or the London International Exchange, American Depositary Receipts (“ADRs”), non-U.S. common or ordinary stocks, limited partnership interests and shares of limited liability companies that are listed on the NYSE.
merged_description: This ETF aims to track an index composed of international companies known for their consistent history of growing dividends, often requiring a minimum of five years of increases. It seeks to invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities of this underlying index, which is weighted based on dividend yield and rebalanced quarterly according to trailing yields. The portfolio primarily consists of non-U.S. firms trading on major exchanges like the NYSE and the London Stock Exchange, holding a variety of security types including American and Global Depositary Receipts, common stocks, limited partnership interests, and shares of limited liability companies.

name: AdvisorShares Pure US Cannabis ETF
description_original: The fund is an actively managed ETF that seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in securities of companies that derive at least 50% of their net revenue from the marijuana and hemp business in the United States and in derivatives that have economic characteristics similar to such securities. It will concentrate at least 25% of its investments in the pharmaceuticals, biotechnology & life sciences industry group within the health care sector. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: MSOS is the first US-listed actively managed ETF to provide exposure solely to American cannabis and hemp companies, including multi-state operators (MSOs). This is the second fund from AdvisorShares dedicated to the cannabis investment strategy. MSOS seeks long-term capital appreciation by investing entirely in legal, domestic cannabis equity securities. Stocks may be of mid- and small-cap companies. In addition, the fund will use total return swap contracts to create such exposure. The fund advisor uses a variety of tools and ratings sources to select securities. Companies must be registered with the DEA specifically for the purpose of handling marijuana for lawful research and development of cannabis or cannabinoid-related products. Stocks selected may focus on areas such as REITs, health care, cannabidiol (CBD), pharmaceutical and hydroponics. In addition to investment risks, investors need to be aware of the ongoing regulatory risks.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks long-term capital appreciation. The fund is an actively managed ETF that seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in securities of companies that derive at least 50% of their net revenue from the marijuana and hemp business in the United States and in derivatives that have economic characteristics similar to such securities. It will concentrate at least 25% of its investments in the pharmaceuticals, biotechnology & life sciences industry group within the health care sector. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: Seeking long-term capital appreciation, this actively managed ETF provides focused exposure exclusively to U.S. cannabis and hemp companies. It aims to invest at least 80% of its net assets (including borrowings) in securities and derivatives, such as total return swaps, of companies deriving at least 50% of their net revenue from the U.S. marijuana and hemp business. The fund concentrates significantly, with at least 25% of investments directed towards the pharmaceuticals, biotechnology, and life sciences group within the healthcare sector. It targets legal, domestic companies, potentially requiring DEA registration for lawful research and development, and may include exposures to multi-state operators (MSOs), mid/small-caps, and related areas like REITs, CBD, and hydroponics. This is a non-diversified fund, and investors should consider the inherent investment and regulatory risks of this sector.

name: iShares North American Tech-Multimedia Networking ETF
description_original: The fund generally invests at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of U.S.-traded stocks of communication equipment companies in the U.S. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: IDGT tracks an index of US-listed stocks associated with the infrastructure for the storage, processing, transmission, and/or access of digital data and services. The fund employs a tiered approach for both selection and weighting, targeting 50 stocks across 17 sub-industries based on FactSets RBICS classification. The first tier is divided between Tier 1a (Telecommunication Towers) and Tier 1b (Data Centers) categories. Tier 2 belongs to communications equipment, communications semiconductors, and data storage equipment categories. The fund first selects Tier 1 companies. If less than 50, the fund selects the largest Tier 2 stocks by market-cap. The fund sets strict group and stock targets, subject to single-security capping. The fund is reviewed annually and weighted quarterly. Prior to Dec. 18, 2023, the fund traded under the name iShares North American Tech-Multimedia Networking ETF with the ticker IGN that tracked the S&P North American Technology Multimedia Networking Index.
merged_description: This fund provides exposure to US-listed companies focused on the infrastructure for the storage, processing, transmission, and access of digital data and services. It seeks to track an index that selects approximately 50 stocks across around 17 relevant sub-industries using a tiered methodology. The selection prioritizes companies operating telecommunication towers and data centers, supplementing with those in communications equipment, semiconductors, and data storage to reach the target count. The fund typically invests at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index or investments with similar economic characteristics, adheres to specific group and single-stock capping rules, and is weighted quarterly. It is classified as non-diversified.

name: BNY Mellon Women's Opportunities ETF
description_original: BNY Mellon ETF Trust - BNY Mellon Women's Opportunities ETF is an exchange traded fund launched and managed by BNY Mellon ETF Investment Adviser, LLC. The fund is co-managed by Newton Investment Management North America, LLC and Newton Investment Management Ltd. It invests in public equity markets of the United States. The fund invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in value stocks of companies across diversified market capitalization. It invests in stocks of companies that are deemed socially conscious in their business dealings. It employs fundamental and quantitative analysis to create its portfolio. The fund employs internal research to create its portfolio. BNY Mellon ETF Trust - BNY Mellon Women's Opportunities ETF is domiciled in the United States.
description_eftcom:
BKWO is an actively managed portfolio of US companies that are believed to be financially attractive and promote gender equitable opportunities. The fund invests in companies of any market capitalization and any industry.

BKWO primarily invests in US companies that promote opportunities for women. These include companies incorporating gender equitable practices in the workplace or providing products and services that enable women to meet their work or personal life responsibilities and needs. Such companies include those relating to household, dependent and elder care, and gender-specific healthcare. Companies are scored based on organizational structure, commitment to gender equality, and benefit programs. The top 50% scoring companies within their peer groups are included in the eligible universe. Companies with at least one woman on the board and providing women-related products or services are also eligible for inclusion. BKWO screens the eligible companies to select those with the most favorable combination of revenue, profit, free cash flow growth, and valuation. The fund adviser intends to contribute at least 10% of its management fees to charitable or non-profit womens organizations.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks long-term capital growth. To pursue its goal, the fund normally invests principally in equity securities of U.S. companies that, in the view of the fund's sub-adviser, demonstrate attractive financial attributes and promote "Women's Opportunities." "Women's Opportunities" is defined as opportunities that enhance the professional development and advancement of women and/or the ability of women to meet their work or other personal life responsibilities and needs, such as those relating to household responsibilities, dependent/elder care responsibilities, and gender-specific healthcare. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This actively managed ETF seeks long-term capital growth by investing in US equity securities. It focuses on companies that demonstrate both attractive financial characteristics and a commitment to promoting women's opportunities. This commitment can manifest through gender equitable workplace practices or by providing products and services that help women meet their personal and professional needs, including those related to household, caregiving, and healthcare responsibilities. The fund invests across companies of any market capitalization and diverse sectors, utilizing fundamental and quantitative analysis for selection. While investing across varied sectors, the portfolio is classified as non-diversified. A portion of the management fees received by the fund's adviser is intended to be donated to women's charitable organizations.

name: iShares Climate Conscious & Transition MSCI USA ETF
description_original: iShares Trust - iShares Climate Conscious & Transition MSCI USA ETF is an exchange traded fund launched by BlackRock, Inc. It is managed by BlackRock Fund Advisors. The fund invests in public equity markets of the United States. It invests in stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in growth and value stocks of companies across diversified market capitalization. The fund invests in stocks of companies that are deemed socially conscious in their business dealings and directly promote environmental responsibility. It seeks to track the performance of the MSCI USA Extended Climate Action Index, by using representative sampling technique. It does not invest in stocks of companies operating across tobacco, controversial or nuclear weapons, thermal coal mining or sales or oil sands extraction sectors. iShares Trust - iShares Climate Conscious & Transition MSCI USA ETF is domiciled in the United States.
description_eftcom: USCL targets US companies that are better positioned relative to their sector peers in terms of low carbon transition. Starting with the MSCI USA Index (parent index), the fund applies various exclusionary screens removing firms involved in controversial business activities, very severe ESG controversies, high emissions intensity, and are in the worst quartile of their respective GICS sector. The initial GHG Intensity Score assigned to each remaining security can improve depending on the firms emissions reduction target, credible track record, climate risk management, or green revenue. Lastly, based on the best GHG Intensity Score and highest market capitalization, stocks are selected until around 50% of the securities from each GICS sector in the parent index is reached. Portfolio weights are renormalized to 100%, subject to constraints. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced semi-annually.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the MSCI USA Extended Climate Action Index composed of U.S. large- and mid-capitalization companies based on their positioning, relative to their sector peers, with respect to the transition to a low-carbon economy, as determined by the index provider, based primarily on current emissions intensity, emissions reduction targets, green business revenue, and/or climate risk management. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This exchange-traded fund seeks to track a specific MSCI index focused on U.S. large and mid-capitalization companies based on their positioning relative to sector peers regarding the transition to a low-carbon economy. The index methodology evaluates companies primarily based on factors like current emissions intensity, emissions reduction targets, green business revenue, and climate risk management. It excludes companies involved in controversial activities, severe ESG controversies, high emissions, thermal coal, oil sands, or those performing in the worst quartile within their sector. The fund aims to invest at least 90% of its assets in the index components or use representative sampling, constructing a portfolio that selects leading companies within each sector of a broader U.S. market index. The portfolio is rebalanced semi-annually and is considered non-diversified.

name: Fairlead Tactical Sector Fund
description_original: The fund is a diversified actively-managed ETF that under normal circumstances will invest more than 80% of the fund’s net assets in passive domestic equity sector ETFs and ETFs investing respectively in gold and U.S. Treasuries. The fund’s principal investment strategy will employ a systematic approach to technical analysis focused on the identification of important trends. The fund’s investable universe will consist of the sectors of the S&P 500®, as defined by the State Street series of SPDR® ETFs.
description_eftcom:
TACK relies on a proprietary, technical model to actively manage a US large-cap sector rotation strategy. During periods deemed risk-off, the fund toggles the exposure to short- or long-term US Treasurys or gold. The objective is to outperform the S&P 500.

TACK is a fund-of-funds whose strategy starts with top-down market analysis and combines trend-following, price momentum, and sector relative strength. The funds investable universe consists of 14 State Street SPDR ETFs: the 11 Select Sector SPDRs, the SPDR Gold Trust, and SPDR short- and SPDR long-term US Treasury ETFs. Relying on the expertise of a technical analyst, the selection process follows a rules-based filtering system that considers market trends and overbought/oversold indicators. ETFs that pass the technical filter, receive a momentum score and a ranking is calculated. During periods of risk-on, the portfolio will hold between 5-8 of the highest-ranked ETFs on an equal-weighted basis. During periods of risk-off, the portfolio may hold up to 75% of its exposure in short- or long-term US Treasury ETFs or gold. The portfolio is rebalanced monthly. Due to the tactical nature of the strategy, the fund is anticipated to have a very high turnover.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks capital appreciation with limited drawdowns. The fund is a diversified actively-managed ETF that under normal circumstances will invest more than 80% of the fund’s net assets in passive domestic equity sector ETFs and ETFs investing respectively in gold and U.S. Treasuries. The fund’s principal investment strategy will employ a systematic approach to technical analysis focused on the identification of important trends. The fund’s investable universe will consist of the sectors of the S&P 500®, as defined by the State Street series of SPDR® ETFs.
merged_description: This is a diversified, actively-managed fund-of-funds that employs a systematic technical analysis approach for a US large-cap sector rotation strategy. Under normal circumstances, it invests over 80% of its assets in a universe of passive ETFs covering S&P 500 equity sectors, gold, and US Treasuries (both short- and long-term). The strategy utilizes a proprietary model combining trend-following, momentum, and relative strength to identify important trends and rank opportunities. During periods deemed "risk-on", the portfolio typically holds a select number of the highest-ranked equity sector ETFs; however, during "risk-off" periods, the fund can significantly shift its exposure, allocating up to 75% of assets to US Treasury and gold ETFs to limit drawdowns. Seeking capital appreciation and aiming to outperform the S&P 500, the portfolio is rebalanced monthly and is expected to have high turnover due to its tactical nature.

name: iShares Europe Developed Real Estate ETF
description_original: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the FTSE EPRA/NAREIT Developed Europe Index composed of real estate equities in developed European markets. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of companies engaged in the ownership and development of developed European real estate markets as defined by FTSE EPRA/NAREIT. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This ETF provides targeted exposure to the developed European real estate sector by seeking to track the performance of an index composed of companies involved in the ownership and development of real estate in that region. It generally invests at least 90% of its assets in securities representing this index. The fund is structured as non-diversified.

name: Amplify CrowdBureau(R) Online Lending & Digital Banking ETF
description_original: The investment seeks investment results that generally correspond (before fees and expenses) to the price and yield of the CrowdBureauÂ® P2P Online Lending and Digital Banking Index. The fund will normally invest at least 80% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the securities that comprise the index. The index is a rules-based stock index owned, developed and maintained by CrowdBureau Corporation (âCrowdBureauâ or the âindex providerâ) designed to provide exposure to U.S.-listed equity securities of companies included within the peer-to-peer securities based crowdfunding and digital lending ecosystem. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This investment product seeks to track the performance of an index designed to capture exposure to U.S.-listed companies within the peer-to-peer securities based crowdfunding and digital lending ecosystem. It invests at least 80% of its assets in the equity securities comprising this rules-based index. Classified as non-diversified, the fund offers targeted exposure to companies within this specific financial technology sector.

name: AGFiQ U.S. Market Neutral Anti-Beta Fund
description_original: The fund will invest primarily in long positions in low beta U.S. equities and short positions in high beta U.S. equities on a dollar neutral basis, within sectors. It will construct a dollar neutral portfolio of long and short positions of U.S. equities by investing primarily in the constituent securities of the Dow Jones U.S. Thematic Market Neutral Low Beta Index in approximately the same weight as they appear in the index. The universe for the index is comprised of the top 1,000 eligible securities by market capitalization, including REITs.
description_eftcom:
BTAL is an actively managed fund that takes long positions in low beta US stocks, offset by short positions in high beta US stocks.

BTAL actively manages its portfolio of stocks through a market neutral strategy. The fund targets the top 1,000 by market-cap, including REITs, in the Dow Jones U.S. Index. The fund`s market neutral approach aims to offset nominal long and short positions. BTAL ranks stocks in each sector by beta, and individual stocks get equal weight within their sectors. Overall, long low beta and short high beta might be expected to negatively correlate to equities despite the equal dollar offsetting exposure. While BTAL uses swaps at times, it typically takes direct short positions in stocks rather than relying solely on derivatives for short exposure. Therefore, the fund reports short interest costs in its expense ratio, something that purely swaps-based long-short funds don`t have to do, although short interest expense hits the bottom line in either case. Prior to Feb. 14, 2022, the fund tracked the Dow Jones U.S. Thematic Market Neutral Low Beta Index following the same strategies.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to provide a consistent negative beta exposure to the U.S. equity market. The fund will invest primarily in long positions in low beta U.S. equities and short positions in high beta U.S. equities on a dollar neutral basis, within sectors. It will construct a dollar neutral portfolio of long and short positions of U.S. equities by investing primarily in the constituent securities of the Dow Jones U.S. Thematic Market Neutral Low Beta Index in approximately the same weight as they appear in the index. The universe for the index is comprised of the top 1,000 eligible securities by market capitalization, including REITs.
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks to provide consistent negative beta exposure to the U.S. equity market by taking long positions in low beta U.S. equities and short positions in high beta U.S. equities. It implements this strategy on a dollar neutral basis within sectors, drawing from an investment universe comprised of the top 1,000 U.S. stocks by market capitalization, including REITs. The fund typically utilizes direct short positions rather than solely swaps, which may result in reported short interest costs.

name: iShares Cybersecurity and Tech ETF
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. The index is composed of developed and emerging market companies that are involved in cyber security and technology, including cyber security hardware, software, products, and services. It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
IHAK tracks a market cap-selected and -weighted index of large- and mid-cap companies involved in cyber hardware and software.

IHAK measures the performance of equity securities issued by companies involved in cybersecurity and technology, including: cybersecurity hardware, software, products, and services. Revenues are a key factor in determining a companys inclusion in this portfolio those that derive 50% or more of their revenue from such industry make the cut. Some included businesses are customer premises network security equipment producers, enterprise network security software providers, and aerospace and defense IT service manufactures. IHAK covers both developed and emerging markets, and includes all market caps. Moreover, its index is reconstituted annually, rebalanced semi-annually and weighted by market-cap (with individual constituents capped at 4% of the index weight).
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the NYSE® FactSet® Global Cyber Security IndexTM. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. The index is composed of developed and emerging market companies that are involved in cyber security and technology, including cyber security hardware, software, products, and services. It is non-diversified.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to track an index focused on companies involved in global cybersecurity. The index is composed of developed and emerging market companies across various market capitalizations that derive 50% or more of their revenue from cybersecurity and related technology, including hardware, software, products, and services. The fund generally invests at least 80% of its assets in the index's component securities or investments with substantially identical economic characteristics, allowing up to 20% in certain derivatives and cash. The index is market-cap weighted, with individual constituents capped at 4%, and is rebalanced semi-annually and reconstituted annually. It is classified as non-diversified.

name: Invesco Dow Jones Industrial Average Dividend ETF
description_original: The fund will generally invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to provide exposure to dividend-paying equity securities of companies included in the Dow Jones Industrial Average™, which is a price-weighted index of 30 U.S. companies that meet certain size, listing and liquidity requirements. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
DJD follows an index comprising dividend-paying securities of the companies listed on the Dow Jones Industrial Average, weighted by yield.

DJD is a blue-chip, high dividend yield play based on the one of the oldest US indexes the Dow. It tracks an index, which selects securities that have paid consistent dividends over the past four quarters from the Dow Jones Industrial Average. DJDs difference from the Dow: Companies are weighted according to their dividend yield rather than price-weighted. This produces higher portfolio yield and reshuffles the Dows significant sector biases. Overall, DJD provides a concentrated, yield-oriented sampling of some well-known names. The Fund and the Index are rebalanced semi-annually.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the Dow Jones Industrial Average Yield Weighted (the "underlying index"). The fund will generally invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to track the dividend-paying equity securities of companies included in the Dow Jones Industrial Average™, which is a price-weighted index of 30 U.S. companies that meet certain size, listing and liquidity requirements. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to track an index composed of dividend-paying equity securities selected from the 30 companies included in the Dow Jones Industrial Average. While the standard DJIA is price-weighted, this underlying index weights its constituents based on their dividend yield. This yield-weighting approach aims to produce a higher portfolio yield and can result in different sector exposures compared to the price-weighted index. The fund generally invests at least 90% of its total assets in these index securities, providing a concentrated, yield-oriented exposure to well-known, blue-chip U.S. companies. As a result, the fund is considered non-diversified. The index and fund are rebalanced semi-annually.

name: WisdomTree International AI Enhanced Value Fund
description_original: The fund is actively managed and seeks to invest primarily in equity securities selected from a universe of developed market equities, excluding the United States and Canada, that exhibit value characteristics based on the selection results of a proprietary, quantitative artificial intelligence (“AI”) model developed by Sub-Adviser. The equity securities selected by the AI model typically have a lower price-to-book ratio, a lower price-to-earnings ratio, and greater free cash flow. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: AIVI invests in value stocks from developed markets, excluding the US and Canada. The fund employs a proprietary, quantitative AI model that analyzes various inputs, including company fundamentals and market sentiment, to select 60-190 stocks that exhibit value characteristics. The AI model weights stocks based on their overall model scores, capped at 6% per individual security. The sub-adviser generally buys and sells stocks monthly based on the AI models updated recommendations. As an actively managed fund, the portfolio managers can analyze market and financial data to make buy, sell, and hold decisions at their discretion. Prior to Jan. 18, 2022, the fund was called WisdomTree International Dividend ex-Financials Fund, which traded under the ticker DOO, and tracked the WisdomTree International Dividend ex-Financials Index.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks income and capital appreciation. The fund is actively managed and seeks to invest primarily in equity securities selected from a universe of developed market equities, excluding the United States and Canada, that exhibit value characteristics based on the selection results of a proprietary, quantitative artificial intelligence (“AI”) model developed by Sub-Adviser. The equity securities selected by the AI model typically have a lower price-to-book ratio, a lower price-to-earnings ratio, and greater free cash flow. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: Seeking income and capital appreciation, this actively managed fund invests primarily in value equity securities from developed markets, excluding the United States and Canada. Stock selection is driven by a proprietary, quantitative artificial intelligence (AI) model which analyzes company fundamentals and market sentiment. The AI model identifies equities exhibiting value characteristics, typically focusing on those with lower price-to-book, lower price-to-earnings ratios, and greater free cash flow. It selects 60-190 stocks and weights them based on AI scores, capping individual securities at 6%. The portfolio is generally adjusted monthly based on the AI's updated recommendations. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Simplify Tara India Opportunities ETF
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its assets in securities of Indian issuers. The manager define Indian issuers as entities: (i) organized in India; (ii) having a class of securities whose principal securities market is in India; (iii) deriving more than 50% of total revenues or earnings from goods produced, sales made, or services provided in India; or (iv) maintaining more than 50% of its employees, assets, investments, operations, or other business activity in India.
description_eftcom: IOPP invests in equity securities of Indian issuers positioned to benefit from its key themes relating to the countrys growing middle class, sectors with increasing economic participation, and the governments focus on defense, green energy, and exports. The fund invests in Indian companies perceived as high quality with potential for long-term growth and capital appreciation. The actively managed fund invests in companies with no restriction to market capitalization. The portfolio managers use a bottom-up selection process that identifies stocks through company-specific research and analysis. The process starts with 800-1,000 stocks that are screened using multiple factors, such as an evaluation of a companys competitive position, management, growth potential, and track record. Companies are further narrowed down using KPIs, model building, and valuations. To maintain the portfolio and ensure diversification, securities are monitored by tracking news and analyzing quarterly results.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to achieve long-term capital appreciation. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its assets in securities of Indian issuers. The manager define Indian issuers as entities: (i) organized in India; (ii) having a class of securities whose principal securities market is in India; (iii) deriving more than 50% of total revenues or earnings from goods produced, sales made, or services provided in India; or (iv) maintaining more than 50% of its employees, assets, investments, operations, or other business activity in India.
merged_description: This actively managed fund aims for long-term capital appreciation by investing primarily in securities of Indian issuers, defined broadly as entities organized in, principally listed in, or deriving significant revenue, assets, or business activity from India. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its assets are allocated to these securities. The fund seeks high-quality companies positioned to benefit from key themes in India, including the growth of the middle class, increasing economic participation across sectors, and governmental focus areas like defense, green energy, and exports. Utilizing a bottom-up selection process, managers conduct extensive company-specific research to identify firms with long-term growth potential, screening candidates based on competitive position, management quality, growth prospects, and track record, before refining selections through quantitative analysis and valuations, without restriction on market capitalization.

name: Global X Cybersecurity ETF
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index and in American Depositary Receipts ("ADRs") and Global Depositary Receipts ("GDRs") based on the securities in the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to provide exposure to exchange-listed companies that are positioned to benefit from increased adoption of cybersecurity technology. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
BUG tracks a modified market-cap-weighted global index of companies selected on the basis of revenue related to cybersecurity activities.

BUG provides exposure to companies involved in the development and management of security protocols preventing intrusion and attacks to systems, networks, applications, computers, and mobile devices. Eligible securities are those in emerging and developed countries and are selected based on revenue which must be at least 50% generated from cybersecurity activities. The fund also invests in ADRs and GDRs based on such securities. The index weights its constituents by market-cap but each are subject to caps, thereby limiting concentration on large-cap companies and increasing exposure to other companies. The top 40 cybersecurity companies will form the final index. The index is reconstituted and re-weighted semi-annually.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the Indxx Cybersecurity Index. The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index and in American Depositary Receipts ("ADRs") and Global Depositary Receipts ("GDRs") based on the securities in the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to provide exposure to exchange-listed companies that are positioned to benefit from increased adoption of cybersecurity technology. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This fund provides exposure to companies positioned to benefit from the increased adoption of cybersecurity technology. It tracks a global index focusing on exchange-listed companies in developed and emerging markets that derive at least 50% of their revenue from cybersecurity activities, such as developing and managing security protocols for various systems and devices. The underlying index employs a modified market-cap-weighting methodology with constituent caps to limit concentration, selecting the top 40 eligible companies. The index is reconstituted and re-weighted semi-annually. The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of this underlying index and in related American and Global Depositary Receipts. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Invesco Nasdaq Biotechnology ETF
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the index. Strictly in accordance with its guidelines and mandated procedures, Nasdaq compiles the underlying index, which is a modified market capitalization weighted index that is designed to measure the performance of securities listed on the Nasdaq Stock Market that are classified as either biotechnology or pharmaceutical companies. The index may include securities of large-, mid- and small-capitalization companies. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
IBBQ tracks a modified market-cap-weighted index of US biotechnology and pharmaceutical companies listed on the NASDAQ.

IBBQ provides exposure to US biotech and pharma companies that are exclusively listed on the NASDAQ Stock Market. The index includes companies classified under the biotechnology or pharmaceuticals sub sector of the Industry Classification Benchmark. Companies from any capitalization may be included, but since weighting is based on market cap, it produces a basket that heavily favors large-caps and concentrates exposure in the top names. Individual holdings are subject to capping requirements, 8% on the five largest constituents and 4% for the remaining. IBBQ may miss opportunities in companies traded on the NYSE, which several of the other similar funds are eligible to hold. The index is rebalanced quarterly and reconstituted annually in December.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the Nasdaq Biotechnology Index ®. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the index. Strictly in accordance with its guidelines and mandated procedures, Nasdaq compiles the underlying index, which is a modified market capitalization weighted index that is designed to measure the performance of securities listed on the Nasdaq Stock Market that are classified as either biotechnology or pharmaceutical companies. The index may include securities of large-, mid- and small-capitalization companies. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This fund seeks to track the performance of a modified market-capitalization weighted index comprising US biotechnology and pharmaceutical companies listed exclusively on the Nasdaq Stock Market. While the index includes companies of all market capitalizations (large, mid, and small), its weighting methodology, which includes capping individual holdings (8% for the top five, 4% for others), tends to concentrate exposure in larger-cap names and the leading constituents. The fund generally invests at least 90% of its assets in the securities of this index. It is classified as non-diversified and its focus solely on Nasdaq-listed securities means it will not hold biotech or pharma companies traded on other exchanges like the NYSE. The underlying index is rebalanced quarterly and reconstituted annually.

name: Roundhill BIG Bank ETF
description_original: The fund is an actively managed exchange-traded fund (“ETF”) that pursues its investment objective by seeking investment exposure to the largest companies (“Underlying Issuers”) in the Banks Industry and/or Capital Markets Industry (“Bank and Capital Markets Industries”), each an industry defined by an independent industry classification scheme. The fund generally will offer exposure to between five and ten underlying issuers primarily through the use of swap agreements and/or forward contracts. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
BIGB is actively managed to provide highly concentrated exposure to the largest and most liquid US-listed banks and Capital Markets Issuers. The fund primarily uses swaps and forwards to provide exposure.

The fund is closing. The last day of trading on an exchange is December 12, 2023. BIGB launched quickly at a time when smaller banks happened to be under pressure. The funds strategy aims to select 6-10 large, liquid, financial service firms that may benefit from such distress or considered to be globally systemically important banks. On an annual basis the issuer reviews the universe of stocks in the banking and capital markets industries to select the largest institutions based on market cap and trading volume. The stocks selected for the fund are equally weighted and rebalanced quarterly. From time to time the fund may investing up to 100% of the holdings in US Treasury securities, money market funds, or other short-term instruments. The funds manager has full discretion in managing the portfolio. The fund is a non-diversified investment company and will hold concentrated exposure. The funds holdings may include common stocks and ADRs, but expected to gain its exposure through the use of swaps and forward contracts.
merged_description: This is an actively managed ETF providing highly concentrated, non-diversified exposure to 6-10 of the largest and most liquid US-listed financial service firms in the Banks and Capital Markets industries. The strategy aims to select institutions based on criteria including market capitalization, trading volume, and potential status as globally systemically important banks or beneficiaries of distress. Exposure is primarily achieved through the use of swap agreements and forward contracts, with selected firms typically equally weighted and the portfolio rebalanced quarterly. While holdings may temporarily include short-term instruments, the core exposure is gained via derivatives. Importantly, the fund is closing, with its last day of trading scheduled for December 12, 2023.

name: Direxion Moonshot Innovators ETF
description_original: The fund, under normal circumstances, invests at least 80% of its net assets in the securities that comprise the index or investments with economic characteristics similar to the securities included in the index. The index measures the performance of the securities of 50 U.S. companies that pursue innovative technologies that have the potential to disrupt existing technologies and/or industries (i.e., moonshot innovators). The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
MOON tracks a tier-weighted index that selects US-listed companies seeking innovative technologies.

The security was delisted.The last day of trading on an exchange is July 19, 2024. MOON targets US companies that pursue innovative and disruptive technologies, or moonshot innovators. The selection universe is drawn from companies in the S&P Kensho New Economy indices or from the Wireless Telecommunication or Internet industries. To construct the portfolio, the index picks the top 50 companies with the highest early-stage composite innovation scores. This score is based on a natural language processing (NLP) algorithm used for keyword searches relating to the theme and on the companies research and development expense ratio to revenue. While MOON may include stocks of all capitalizations in its portfolio, the fund aims to focus on mid- and small-cap stocks and exclude mega-cap stocks. Furthermore, the index applies modified equal-weightingstocks are first equal-weighted, and then adjusted to meet liquidity, industry group, and diversification constraints. The index is rebalanced quarterly and reconstituted semi-annually.
merged_description: This fund, which was delisted with its last trading day on July 19, 2024, tracked an index of 50 U.S. companies identified as "moonshot innovators" pursuing innovative and disruptive technologies. The index selected US-listed firms from specific industries and S&P Kensho indices using early-stage innovation scores based on natural language processing and R&D data. While capable of holding any market capitalization, it aimed for mid- and small-cap stocks, excluding mega-caps, and employed a modified equal-weighting approach. The non-diversified fund normally invested at least 80% of its net assets in index constituents or similar investments. The index composition was reviewed semi-annually, with quarterly weighting adjustments.

name: ProShares Online Retail ETF
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in component securities of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of publicly traded companies that principally sell online or through other non-store sales channels, such as through mobile or app purchases, rather than through "brick and mortar" store locations. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: ONLN is part of a suite of ProShares products that focus on retail disruption, alongside EMTY and CLIX. The fund tracks an index of global companies that mainly sell online or through other non-store sales channels, such as mobile or app purchase and excludes online travel companies. ONLN competes with Amplifys similar fund, IBUY. The biggest difference between the two is in the weighting of components unlike the equal-weighted IBUY, components of ONLN are held on a modified market-cap basis. That gives a big boost to the largest stocks in the segment, like Amazon and Alibaba. The modified market cap adjusts to the following: individual company weight may not exceed 24% of the index and the sum of all companies weighing more than 4.5% may not exceed 50% of the indexs value. A cap of 25% is placed on non-US holdings. The index is reconstituted annually in June and rebalanced monthly.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks investment results, before fees and expenses, that track the performance of the ProShares Online Retail Index (the index). The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of U.S.-listed companies deemed to be “Online Retailers.”Under normal circumstances, it will invest at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This ETF seeks investment results that track the performance of an index measuring companies primarily engaged in online or non-store retail sales, such as via mobile or app purchases, rather than traditional brick-and-mortar locations. The fund focuses on global companies within this segment, specifically excluding online travel, and has a cap on non-US holdings. It invests at least 80% of its assets under normal circumstances in securities that compose the index or have similar economic characteristics. The index uses a modified market-capitalization weighting approach, which results in a higher allocation to larger companies compared to equally weighted funds, with specific limits on individual and aggregated large component weights. The fund is non-diversified, and the underlying index is reconstituted annually and rebalanced monthly.

name: ProShares S&P 500 Dividend Aristocrats ETF
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in component securities of the index. The index contains a minimum of 40 stocks, which are equally weighted, and no single sector is allowed to comprise more than 30% of the index weight. It seeks to remain fully invested at all times in securities and/or financial instruments that, in combination, provide exposure to the returns of the index without regard to market conditions, trends or direction.
description_eftcom:
NOBL tracks an equal-weighted index of S&P 500 constituents that have increased dividend payments annually for at least 25 years.

NOBL only selects companies from the S&P 500 that have increased their dividends for at least 25 consecutive years. Holdings are equal-weighted, with sector weights capped at 30%. NOBLs methodology causes it to overweight traditional dividend-paying sectors. With a concentrated portfolio of at least 40 names, the fund might skew away from market-like exposure. Its methodology substantially limits NOBL's selection universe, and the fund has a pronounced midcap tilt. However, the fund may be less sensitive to market movements than other vanilla funds in the segment. The index is reconstituted annually and rebalanced quarterly.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks investment results, before fees and expenses, that track the performance of the S&P 500® Dividend Aristocrats® Index (the "index"). The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index.
