Securities considered to be an affiliated firm are capped at 22.5%, with the aggregate of those with a weight greater than 4.5% capped at 45% weight of the portfolio. The portfolio will hold stocks of all capitalizations. A representative sampling indexing strategy and derivatives are used to manage the fund. The index is rebalanced quarterly. Prior to April 10, 2023, the fund traded under the name iShares MSCI Peru ETF.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the MSCI All Peru Capped Index. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the index. A significant portion of the index is represented by securities of companies in the financials and materials industries or sectors. Companies with economic exposure to and/or carry out the majority of their operations in Peru may include companies organized, listed, or with significant operations in developed countries. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This passively managed fund seeks broad equity exposure to Peru by tracking a market cap-weighted MSCI index that includes securities of companies classified in, headquartered, listed, or with significant economic exposure to the country, potentially including those organized or listed in developed countries. It generally invests at least 80% of its assets in index components or equivalents and aims to hold a minimum number of Peruvian securities and issuers, offering exposure across all capitalizations. A significant portion of the portfolio is concentrated in the financials and materials sectors, and while applying capping methodologies like the MSCI 25/50 rule to manage concentration for tax purposes, the fund is considered non-diversified. The strategy employs representative sampling and derivatives, with the underlying index rebalanced quarterly.

name: Xtrackers High Beta High Yield Bond ETF
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets, (but typically far more) in component securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to track the performance of the segment of the U.S. dollar denominated high yield corporate bond market that exhibits higher overall beta to the broader high yield corporate fixed income market.
description_eftcom:
HYUP tracks an index of USD-denominated high yield bonds with a high yield to worst.

HYUP provides exposure to a portion of the USD high-yield bond space that exhibits higher beta, which may appeal to investors who want a risk-on approach. The index calculates the median yield to worst for each sector in the USD high-yield space, and then selects all eligible securities yielding higher than their sectors median yield. The result is a selection of bonds with higher volatility, lower credit quality, and higher yield than the broader high-yield market. Issues must have less than 15 years to maturity. The underlying index is market-value weighted, with monthly rebalancing and reconstitution.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance, before fees and expenses, of the Solactive USD High Yield Corporates Total Market High Beta Index (the "underlying index"). The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets, (but typically far more) in component securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to track the performance of the segment of the U.S. dollar denominated high yield corporate bond market that exhibits higher overall beta to the broader high yield corporate fixed income market.
merged_description: This ETF seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance of an underlying index focused on USD-denominated high yield corporate bonds. It targets a segment of the high yield market that exhibits higher overall beta to the broader high yield market, appealing to investors seeking a risk-on approach. The underlying index specifically selects eligible bonds with a high yield to worst, identifying those yielding higher than their sector's median yield to worst. This results in exposure to bonds with higher yield, increased volatility, and generally lower credit quality compared to the broader high-yield market. The index includes issues with less than 15 years to maturity, is market-value weighted, and undergoes monthly rebalancing and reconstitution. The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the component securities of this underlying index.

name: Goldman Sachs Ultra Short Bond ETF
description_original: The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets plus any borrowings for investment purposes (measured at the time of purchase) ("Net Assets") in a broad range of U.S. dollar denominated bonds. It will concentrate its investments in the financial services group of industries. Under normal circumstances, the fund's effective duration is expected to be one year or less.
description_eftcom:
GSST is an actively-managed ETF that seeks to provide current income with preservation of capital by investing in a broad range of USD-denominated ultra-short-term bonds.

GSST is an actively-managed bond fund with the main focus of holding investment-grade, ultra-short (less than one year) maturity fixed income instruments. The Fund primarily invests in US Government Securities, obligations of US banks, corporate notes, commercial paper, fixed and floating rate mortgage-backed securities, asset-backed securities, collateralized loan obligations and repurchase agreements. GSST may also invest in USD-denominated obligations issued or guaranteed by foreign banks, companies and governments. The Fund will concentrate its investments in the financial services group of industries.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to provide current income with preservation of capital. The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets plus any borrowings for investment purposes (measured at the time of purchase) ("Net Assets") in a broad range of U.S. dollar denominated bonds. It will concentrate its investments in the financial services group of industries. Under normal circumstances, the fund's effective duration is expected to be one year or less.
merged_description: This actively managed ETF seeks to provide current income with preservation of capital by investing in a broad range of U.S. dollar denominated bonds. Under normal circumstances, the fund aims to allocate at least 80% of its net assets to these instruments, which primarily consist of ultra-short-term fixed income with an effective duration expected to be one year or less. The portfolio may include government securities, corporate notes, commercial paper, structured credit, and other obligations, notably concentrating its investments within the financial services group of industries.

name: Pacer Trendpilot® US Bond ETF
description_original: A strategy driven fixed income exchange traded fund (ETF) that uses trend following to alternate exposure between high yield corporate bonds and U.S. Treasury Bonds.
description_eftcom:
PTBD tracks an index that uses a momentum-driven proprietary strategy that toggles between U.S. High Yield Corporate Bonds and 7-10 Year Treasury Bonds.

PTBDis the first in theTrendpilotseries to provide exposure to fixed income. The fundattempts to participate in an upward trending U.S.high yield corporate bond market and lessen exposure during downtrends. It accomplishes this via toggling feature that switches the weights between S&P US High Yield Corporate Bonds and S&P US Treasury 7-10 Yearbonds. The fund will toggle between allHigh Yield Corporate bonds,allTreasury bondsor a 50/50 mix by comparing the 100-moving average to the ratio of the Corporate Bond Index and Treasury Bond Index. The risk toggle providesselldiscipline butruns the risk of lagging the market on both sell and buy signals. Retail investors would be wise to check spreads before placing trades and use limit orders to control execution. Large institutional traders should use a liquidity provider before purchasing or selling this ETF. The strategy may also introduce increased capital gains risks.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the Pacer Trendpilot US Bond Index. The index uses an objective, rules-based methodology to implement a systematic trend-following strategy that directs exposure to one of the following positions: (i) 100% to the S&P U.S. High Yield Corporate Bond Index, (ii) 50% to the S&P U.S. High Yield Corporate Bond Index and 50% to the S&P U.S. Treasury Bond 7-10 Year Index or (iii) 100% to S&P U.S. Treasury Bond 7-10 Year Index, depending on the “Risk Ratio". Normally at least 80% of the fund's total assets will be invested in the component securities of the index.
merged_description: This strategy-driven fixed income exchange-traded fund tracks a rules-based index utilizing a systematic trend-following methodology. The strategy alternates exposure between U.S. High Yield Corporate Bonds and 7-10 Year U.S. Treasury Bonds. Based on specific trend signals, the index allocates assets to either 100% High Yield, 100% Treasuries, or a 50/50 mix, aiming to participate in upward trends in the high yield market while reducing exposure during downtrends. Normally, at least 80% of the fund's assets are invested in the component securities of the index.

name: Robo Global Artificial Intelligence ETF
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 80% of its total assets in securities of the index or in depositary receipts representing securities of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of publicly-traded companies that have a significant portion of their revenue derived from the field of artificial intelligence. It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
THNQ tracks a global index of companies involved in developing the technology and the infrastructure of enabling artificial intelligence.

THNQ tracks an index designed to measure the performance of publicly-traded companies that derive a significant portion of their revenue from the field of artificial intelligence. Stocks are selected from a proprietary database maintained by the index provider. Companies are classified as either Infrastructure or Applications and Services. Classifications are further defined by subsectors such as: big data/analytics, network and security, semiconductors, factory automation, eCommerce and business process. Each eligible company is individually scored based on AI revenue ranging from 1 to 100. Companies that score greater than 50 and meet market cap and liquidity requirements are eligible for inclusion. The index is comprised of a minimum of 50 and a maximum of 100 stocks. Stocks are weighted based on their score.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the price and yield performance of the ROBO Global® Artificial Intelligence Index. The fund will normally invest at least 80% of its total assets in securities of the index or in depositary receipts representing securities of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of publicly-traded companies that have a significant portion of their revenue derived from the field of artificial intelligence. It is non-diversified.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to track the performance of a global index focused on public companies deriving significant revenue from artificial intelligence (AI). The index identifies companies involved in developing AI technology and infrastructure through a proprietary selection process that classifies them into categories like Infrastructure and Applications/Services, scores them based on AI revenue, and selects eligible companies meeting certain criteria. The index typically holds between 50 and 100 stocks, weighted based on their AI revenue score. The fund normally invests at least 80% of its assets in securities of the index or related depositary receipts and is classified as non-diversified.

name: Invesco KBW Regional Banking ETF
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is a modified-market capitalization-weighted index comprised of companies primarily engaged in U.S. regional banking activities, as determined by the index provider. The underlying index is designed to track the performance of U.S. regional banking and thrift companies that are publicly-traded in the U.S.
description_eftcom:
KBWR tracks a modified market-cap-weighted index focused exclusively on regional banking firms in the US.

KBWR doesn't attempt to provide broad exposure to the US banking segment. Instead, the fund employs an index committee selection process, along with modified market-cap weighting to construct a portfolio of regional banking and thrift firms. This process makes an already small-cap oriented portfolio tilt even smaller. In fact, KBWR's portfolio has one of the smallest average market caps in the segment. The fund's scope does not stray from its narrow mandate: it provides the exact exposure it promises, with no industry tilts. The index is rebalanced and reconstituted on a quarterly basis.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the KBW Nasdaq Regional Banking IndexTM (the “underlying index”). The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is a modified-market capitalization-weighted index comprised of companies primarily engaged in U.S. regional banking activities, as determined by the index provider. The underlying index is designed to track the performance of U.S. regional banking and thrift companies that are publicly-traded in the U.S.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to track the performance, before fees and expenses, of a modified market-capitalization weighted index. It invests at least 90% of its total assets in the securities of this underlying index, which comprises U.S. regional banking and thrift companies publicly traded in the U.S. Unlike funds offering broad US banking exposure, this fund maintains a narrow mandate focused exclusively on regional banking firms. The portfolio, constructed through modified market-cap weighting and an index committee selection process, exhibits a tilt towards smaller average market capitalization, often resulting in one of the smallest average market caps in the segment. The index is rebalanced and reconstituted quarterly.

name: Direxion Daily Regional Banks Bull 3X Shares
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and ETFs that track the index and other financial instruments that provide daily leveraged exposure to the index or to ETFs that track the index. The index is a modified equal-weighted index that is designed to measure performance of the stocks comprising the S&P Total Market Index that are classified in the GICS regional banks sub-industry. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: DPST provides a way for investors to take a 3x leveraged bullish exposure to an equal-weighted index of US regional banks. The fund specifically holds securities from the S&P Total Market Index that are classified under the regional banks sub-industry according to GICS. Its equal-weighting scheme lowers concentration thus, reducing single-name risk. As a geared product with daily resets, DPST is designed as a short-term trading tool and not a long-term investment vehicle. As a result, long-term returns could materially differ from those of the underlying index due to daily compounding. Prior to December 1, 2016, DPST tracked the Solactive US Regional Banks Index.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks daily investment results, before fees and expenses, of 300% of the daily performance of the S&P Regional Banks Select Industry Index. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and ETFs that track the index, that, in combination, provide 3X daily leveraged exposure to the index, consistent with the fund's investment objective. The index is a modified equal-weighted index that is designed to measure performance of the stocks comprising the S&P Total Market Index that are classified in the GICS regional banks sub-industry. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This fund aims to provide 3x daily leveraged bullish exposure to the S&P Regional Banks Select Industry Index, a modified equal-weighted index tracking regional bank stocks within the S&P Total Market Index based on GICS classification. To achieve its objective of 300% of the index's daily performance, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in financial instruments like swaps and index-related securities. Designed as a short-term trading tool with daily resets, its returns over periods longer than a single day may significantly diverge from the index performance due to the effects of daily compounding. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Nuveen ESG Dividend ETF
description_original: The index is comprised of high dividend paying equity securities issued by companies listed on U.S. exchanges that meet certain environmental, social, and governance (“ESG”) criteria. Under normal market conditions, the fund invests at least 80% of the sum of its net assets and the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes in component securities of the index.
description_eftcom:
NUDV tracks an index of large- and mid-cap US-listed companies that exhibit high dividend yields and meet certain ESG criteria.

NUDV aims to invest in high dividend paying companies that meet certain ESG criteria, selected from its parent index, the MSCI USA Index. The funds underlying index screens for companies that have higher dividend yields than the parent index. After that, the index uses ESG criteria to exclude companies involved in controversial businesses, such as alcohol, weapons, nuclear power, and gambling. Companies that exceed carbon emissions thresholds are also excluded. The remaining firms are scored on ESG factors, and the highest scoring firms within each sector are selected for inclusion in the fund. The portfolio is weighted according to a multi-factor optimization algorithm that aims to keep holdings and performance similar to the parent index. The index is rebalanced and reconstituted quarterly starting each February.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results, before fees and expenses, of the TIAA ESG USA High Dividend Yield Index (the “index”). The index is comprised of high dividend paying equity securities issued by companies listed on U.S. exchanges that meet certain environmental, social, and governance (“ESG”) criteria. Under normal market conditions, the fund invests at least 80% of the sum of its net assets and the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes in component securities of the index.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to track an index composed of high dividend paying large- and mid-cap US equity securities that meet specific environmental, social, and governance (ESG) criteria. The index screens for companies with higher dividend yields than a broad market parent index and applies ESG exclusions, notably removing companies involved in controversial activities such as alcohol, weapons, nuclear power, and gambling, or those with high carbon emissions. Selection further prioritizes firms with the highest ESG scores within each sector. The resulting portfolio is weighted via a multi-factor optimization process designed to maintain similarity to the parent index and is rebalanced quarterly. Under normal market conditions, the fund normally invests at least 80% of its assets in the index's component securities.

name: iShares MSCI ACWI Low Carbon Target ETF
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to address two dimensions of carbon exposure - carbon emissions and potential carbon emissions from fossil fuel reserves.
description_eftcom:
CRBN tracks an index of stocks from global firms selected for a bias toward lower carbon emissions.

CRBN takes a green-hued position toward the wider market, seeking to track an index of large- and midcap stocks from both established and emerging markets. The fund selects stocks with a tilt toward a smaller carbon footprint, as measured by lower greenhouse gas and carbon emissions, relative to sales and market cap, respectively. The fund uses MSCI ESG CarbonMetrics data to determine these factors based on annual reports, corporate social responsibility reports, the Carbon Disclosure Project, oil and gas industry bodies, and relevant third-party sources. Absent these, data are estimated using a proprietary model. The index is reviewed semi-annually.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the MSCI ACWI Low Carbon Target Index. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to address two dimensions of carbon exposure - carbon emissions and potential carbon emissions from fossil fuel reserves.
merged_description: This fund generally invests at least 80% of its assets in securities designed to track an index focused on lower carbon emissions. Taking a position tilted towards a smaller carbon footprint, the underlying index includes large- and midcap stocks from established and emerging markets globally. It selects companies based on lower greenhouse gas and carbon emissions relative to sales and market cap, specifically addressing two dimensions of carbon exposure: actual carbon emissions and potential emissions from fossil fuel reserves. The index selection utilizes specific carbon metrics data and is reviewed semi-annually.

name: First Trust Rising Dividend Achievers ETF
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stock and depositary receipts that comprise the index. The index is designed to provide access to a diversified portfolio of small, mid and large capitalization companies with a history of raising their dividends while exhibiting the characteristics to continue to do so in the future by including companies with strong cash balances, low debt and increasing earnings.
description_eftcom:
RDVY tracks an index of 50 large-cap stocks with rising, high-quality dividends.

RDVY holds 50 US large-cap stocks screened for dividend growth and quality. The fund seeks stable dividend payers, but not necessarily high yields. RDVY selects its holdings from the 1000 largest US-listed companies, excluding REITs. Firms must meet cash-to-debt and payout ratio thresholds to be eligible, and must have increased both dividends and earnings over the past few years. Eligible companies are ranked by a combination of recent dividend increases, current yield, and payout ratio, and the best 50 stocks are selected. RDVY is reconstituted each March and rebalanced quarterly. The portfolio is equally weighted. Prior to December 14, 2016, the fund traded as the First Trust NASDAQ Rising Dividend Achievers ETF.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield (before fees and expenses) of the NASDAQ U.S. Rising Dividend Achievers TM Index. The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stock and depositary receipts that comprise the index. According to the index Provider, the index measures the performance of a selection of securities that have increased their dividend value over the previous three year and five-year annual periods. The index is comprised of four Sub-Portfolios.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to track the performance of an index that identifies U.S. companies from the 1000 largest U.S.-listed companies (excluding REITs) with a history of increasing dividends and the financial strength to potentially continue doing so. These companies are selected based on criteria including strong cash balances, low debt, increased earnings, cash-to-debt, and payout ratios. The index targets approximately 50 large-cap stocks that demonstrate quality and dividend growth, aiming for stable dividend payers rather than simply high yield. The resulting equally-weighted portfolio is reconstituted annually and rebalanced quarterly. The fund typically invests at least 90% of its assets in the common stock and depositary receipts that comprise the index.

name: ALPS/CoreCommodity Management CompleteCommodities Strategy Fund - Investor Class
description_original: The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, directly or indirectly in a combination of commodity-related equity securities ("Commodity Equity Investments") and commodity futures-linked derivative instruments ("Commodity Investments") and thereby obtaining exposure to the commodity markets.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to maximize real returns, consistent with prudent investment management. The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing,under normal circumstances,directly or indirectly in a combination of equity securities of natural resource companies, as commodity-related equity securities (“Commodity Equity Investments”) and commodity futures-linked derivative instruments thereby obtaining exposure to the commodity markets.
merged_description: This fund aims to maximize real returns, consistent with prudent investment management. It seeks to achieve this objective by investing, directly or indirectly, in a combination of equity securities of natural resource companies, which are considered commodity-related equities, and commodity futures-linked derivative instruments. This blended approach provides exposure to the commodity markets.

name: iShares U.S. Financials ETF
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of U.S. companies in the financial sector of the U.S. equity market.
description_eftcom:
IYF tracks a market-cap-weighted index of US financial companies, while utilizing a capping methodology to ensure diversification among its index constituents.

IYF offers a portfolio specific to the US financials segment, tracking a diversified, market-cap-weighted index for the financial space. The index pulls from a universe covering the top 95% of the market, thus offering broad US financials exposure. The capping methodology limits the sum of the weights of its securities, such that the aggregate weight of all issuers individually exceeding 4.5% are constrained to a maximum of 22.5%. Individual securities are also capped at 15%. The index is rebalanced on a quarterly basis. Prior to September 20, 2021, the fund tracked the Dow Jones U.S. Financials Capped Index.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the Russell 1000 Financials 40 Act 15/22.5 Daily Capped Index composed of U.S. equities in the financial sector. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of the financials sector of the U.S. equity market.
merged_description: This ETF aims to provide exposure to U.S. companies within the financial sector by tracking a market-capitalization-weighted index. The underlying index covers a broad universe of U.S. financials and incorporates a capping methodology to promote diversification. This capping limits the weight of individual securities, generally to 15%, and constrains the aggregate weight of larger constituents that exceed a certain threshold (such as 4.5% individually being limited to a combined 22.5%). The fund typically invests at least 80% of its assets in the securities of this index or instruments with similar economic characteristics, with the index itself undergoing quarterly rebalancing.

name: Janus Henderson U.S. Sustainable Equity ETF
description_original: The fund pursues its investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in equity securities that are economically tied to the U.S. The fund generally invests in a core group of 30-50 equity securities, which consist primarily of common stocks, but may also include other types of instruments, such as depository receipts and warrants. The fund will invest primarily in larger, well-established companies but may also invest in mid- and small-sized companies.
description_eftcom:
SSPX is an actively managed portfolio that seeks long-term capital growth by targeting US companies considered to be contributing positively to the environment and society.

SSPX actively selects US firms believed to have a positive impact on the environment and society as well as the development of the economy. The fund focuses on four environmental and social megatrends namely climate change, resource constraints, growing populations, and aging populations. It invests in companies of all sizes given that they fall under at least one of the 10 sustainability themes determined using a positive selection criterion including clean energy, efficiency, environmental services, water management, sustainable transport, sustainable property and finance, safety, quality of life, knowledge and technology, and health. Within this universe, the funds manager uses a bottom-up approach by reviewing individual securities based on fundamental research infused with ESG factors. Companies are also screened for their negative impacts on society or the environment. At least 30 to 50 equity securities will make up the portfolio. The fund seeks long-term capital growth.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks long-term growth of capital. The fund pursues its investment objective by investing, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in equity securities that are economically tied to the U.S. The fund generally invests in a core group of 30‑50 equity securities, which consist primarily of common stocks, but may also include other types of instruments, such as warrants. The fund will invest primarily in larger, well-established companies but may also invest in mid‑ and small‑sized companies.
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks long-term capital growth primarily by investing in US companies that are assessed as contributing positively to the environment and society. The investment strategy focuses on identifying opportunities within key sustainability trends, utilizing a selection process that combines fundamental research with environmental, social, and governance (ESG) factors, including screening for negative impacts. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its assets in US equity securities, typically holding a concentrated portfolio of 30 to 50 securities. While primarily investing in larger, well-established companies, it may also include mid- and small-sized firms, predominantly through common stocks, though other instruments like warrants and depository receipts may also be included.

name: iShares U.S. Regional Banks ETF
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The index measures the performance of the regional bank sector of the U.S. equity market. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: IAT specifically targets small- and mid-cap regional banks, creating a portfolio with a significant small-cap tilt compared to the broader banking market. Like the sector itself, this fund is extremely concentrated. IAT's underlying index selects from the small and midsize stocks of the Dow Jones U.S. Bank Index: It excludes mega-caps such as JP Morgan and Wells Fargo from the get-go. A company is also excluded if its three-year average total assets account for more than 5% of the three-year average total assets of the index selection universe. This size caveat aside, IAT offers market-like exposure as nearly all of its holdings overlap with our neutral benchmark. The index is market cap-weighted and is rebalanced quarterly.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the Dow Jones U.S. Select Regional Banks Index. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents, as well as in securities not included in the underlying index, but which BFA believes will help the fund track the underlying index. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to track the performance of an index representing the regional bank sector of the U.S. equity market, specifically targeting small and mid-cap regional banks. This focus leads to a portfolio with a significant small-cap tilt and a concentrated nature, deliberately excluding mega-cap institutions present in the broader banking landscape based on size and asset thresholds. The underlying index, the Dow Jones U.S. Select Regional Banks Index, selects components from eligible companies, is market cap-weighted, and rebalanced quarterly. The fund generally invests at least 80% of its assets in the securities of this index or those with substantially identical economic characteristics, though it may utilize other instruments for tracking purposes. Classified as non-diversified, its investment concept centers on capturing the specific performance characteristics of the smaller segment of the U.S. banking sector.

name: ETFMG Prime 2x Daily Junior Silver Miners ETF
description_original: The index tracks the performance of the equity securities of small-capitalization companies actively engaged in silver refining, mining, or exploration (“Junior Silver Companies”). The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and ETFs that track the index and other financial instruments that provide daily leveraged exposure to the index or to ETFs that track the index. It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
SILX tracks 2x the daily price movements of an index of small-cap silver mining and exploration companies.

This fund is delisting. The last day of trading is July 13, 2023. SILX provides daily 2x exposure to an index of global silver mining and exploration companies that include both pure-play and diversified silver firms. The fund determines and selects active junior silver miners'' which are small-cap companies that generate more or less 50% of their revenue from silver mining activities by utilizing available public disclosures. It employs a market-cap-based weighting scheme that starts with categorizing the components and adjusting the market cap for ranking in aim of overweighting pure-play silver miners/explorers and underweighting the non-pure-play companies. The Index is rebalanced and reconstituted quarterly. As a leveraged product with 2x factor that resets daily, SILX is not a buy-and-hold investment, and should not be expected to provide index leverage return greater than a one day period.
merged_description: This ETF provides 2x the daily leveraged exposure to an index focused on the equity securities of small-capitalization companies, often referred to as "junior" silver companies. These firms are primarily engaged in silver mining, exploration, and refining activities globally. The underlying index employs a market-cap based weighting scheme, adjusted to prioritize pure-play silver firms over diversified companies, and is rebalanced quarterly. The fund seeks to achieve its daily investment objective by investing at least 80% of its net assets in financial instruments like swap agreements that provide leveraged exposure to the index. As a daily leveraged product, it is not intended for long-term holding, and the fund is classified as non-diversified.

name: JPMorgan Climate Change Solutions ETF
description_original: The adviser identifies companies that, in the adviser’s opinion, are developing solutions to address climate change and are thus well positioned to benefit from growing demand for such solutions. The fund invests primarily in common stocks and depositary receipts. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
TEMP is actively managed and seeks to invest in companies from around the world that develop solutions to climate change and that are positioned to benefit from those changes.

TEMP actively invests in a portfolio of global companies that are in the process of creating solutions to address climate change, or are implementing business practices in response to climate change. The funds initial universe includes companies that relate to the climate change theme, which cover sustainability in transportation, construction, food and water, energy, and waste reduction. TEMP implements a three-step process to select securities: First, a framework is applied to exclude companies involved in certain business activities or industries, such as thermal coal. Then, a proprietary system, including the use of a ThemeBot, ranks stocks based on a thematic exposure score, which is calculated based on the business relevance and revenues attributed to the sub-themes. Lastly, the adviser combines fundamental research and constant engagement between the fund and the company to select the stocks it believes are best positioned to achieve the investment objective.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to achieve long-term capital appreciation by investing in companies that the adviser believes are developing solutions to address climate change. The adviser identifies companies that, in the adviser’s opinion, are developing solutions to address climate change and are thus well positioned to benefit from growing demand for such solutions. The fund invests primarily in common stocks and depositary receipts.
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks long-term capital appreciation by investing globally in companies involved in developing solutions to address climate change or implementing responsive business practices. Focused on identifying companies positioned to benefit from growing demand in areas like sustainable transportation, construction, food/water, energy, and waste reduction, the investment process employs exclusions, a proprietary system for assessing thematic exposure based on business relevance and revenue, and fundamental research combined with engagement. Primarily investing in common stocks and depositary receipts, the fund is structured as non-diversified.

name: Principal Healthcare Innovators ETF
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets, plus any borrowings for investment purposes, in equity securities of companies in the healthcare sector. It invests significantly in early-stage companies within the healthcare equipment and supplies, pharmaceuticals, biotechnology, and life sciences industries that are not yet consistently profitable.
description_eftcom:
BTEC is actively managed to hold equities of small- and mid-cap healthcare firms in the US. The fund uses a proprietary, quantitative model to construct the portfolio.

The security is being delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is July 31, 2024. BTEC seeks long-term capital growth by investing in small- and mid-cap companies in the Russell 3000 Healthcare Index. To build the portfolio, the fund utilizes a proprietary, quantitative model that emphasizes growth stocks and excludes the least liquid securities. The fund invests significantly in the healthcare equipment and supplies, pharmaceuticals, biotechnology, and life sciences industries, particularly in early-stage companies that are not yet consistently profitable. In constructing the model and managing the portfolio, the fund adviser uses insights from multiple sources, including internal research, industry reports, and third-party data. While the portfolio expects to rebalance at least annually, the fund adviser may make adjustments at its discretion. On July 15, 2022, the fund ceased tracking the NASDAQ U.S. Health Care Innovators Index and transitioned to an active management strategy.
merged_description: This actively managed ETF aims for long-term capital growth by investing in US small- and mid-cap equity securities, with a primary focus on the healthcare sector. It targets specific industries such as healthcare equipment and supplies, pharmaceuticals, biotechnology, and life sciences, significantly investing in early-stage companies within these fields that may not yet be consistently profitable. The fund utilizes a proprietary, quantitative model emphasizing growth stocks and avoiding illiquid securities, informed by various data sources for portfolio construction and management. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets, plus borrowings, in healthcare equity securities.

name: VanEck Egypt Index ETF
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 80% of its total assets in securities that comprise the fund's benchmark index. The index includes securities of Egyptian companies. A company is generally considered to be an Egyptian company if it is incorporated in Egypt or is incorporated outside Egypt but has at least 50% of its revenues/related assets in Egypt. Such companies may include small- and medium-capitalization companies. It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
EGPT tracks a market-cap-weighted index of companies that derive at least 50% of revenues from Egypt.

The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is March 21, 2024. EGPT offers reasonable exposure to this hard to reach space. It is a passively-managed fund that covers 90% of the investable universe consisting of the largest and most liquid companies that are incorporated in Egypt or have at least 50% of their revenues or related assets in Egypt. The index contains roughly 25 names, individually capped at 8% weighting in the index. Political turmoil shut down the Cairo exchange in spring of 2011, forcing VanEck to halt creations briefly. Investors should monitor the volatile condition in Egypt closely. Most of the distortions in exposure result from 1940 Act diversification requirements, which explain why the fund's sector breakdown differs materially from our unconstrained benchmark. The diversification rules also push the fund toward smaller firms relative to our benchmark. Apart from scheduled quarterly rebalances, the Index provider may carry out additional ad hoc rebalances to the Egypt Index.
merged_description: This passively-managed ETF, which has been delisted with its last trading day on March 21, 2024, was designed to provide exposure to the Egyptian equity market. It tracked a market-cap-weighted index composed of companies incorporated in Egypt or deriving at least 50% of their revenues or related assets from the country. The fund typically invested at least 80% of its assets in the securities of its benchmark index, covering approximately 90% of the eligible investment universe, including largest and most liquid names, usually numbering around 25 holdings with individual weights capped at 8%. Classified as non-diversified, its composition could differ from a comparative benchmark due to regulatory diversification rules, potentially leaning towards smaller companies relative to some benchmarks. Investors in this fund were exposed to the specific risks and volatility inherent in the Egyptian market.

name: Fidelity Covington Trust - Disruptive Automation ETF
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in securities of disruptive automation companies. Fidelity's disruptive strategies seek to identify innovative developments that could signal new directions for delivering products and services to customers. Generally, these companies have or are developing new or unconventional ways of doing business that could disrupt and displace incumbents over time. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: FBOT aims for long-term capital growth by utilizing Fidelitys disruptive strategies which identify global automation companies perceived to disrupt market conditions or displace incumbents over time. These companies are those that, in the adviser's opinion, are engaged in designing and manufacturing automation, enabling technology, tools, or processes including robotics, AI, machine vision, process sensors, pneumatic systems, autonomous driving & electric vehicles, and 3D printing. The portfolio is constructed using a fundamental analysis of factors like financial, market, and economic conditions, and industry positions. FBOT converted from a mutual fund called Fidelity Disruptive Automation Fund to an actively managed ETF structure starting with $112 million in net assets.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks long-term growth of capital. The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in securities of disruptive automation companies. Fidelity's disruptive strategies seek to identify innovative developments that could signal new directions for delivering products and services to customers. Generally, these companies have or are developing new or unconventional ways of doing business that could disrupt and displace incumbents over time. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: Seeking long-term capital growth, this actively managed ETF primarily invests in securities of disruptive automation companies, normally allocating at least 80% of assets to this theme. Utilizing disruptive strategies, the fund identifies global companies perceived to disrupt markets or displace incumbents over time through innovative methods and technologies like robotics, artificial intelligence, autonomous driving, and 3D printing. The non-diversified portfolio is constructed using fundamental analysis.

name: VanEck Gold Miners ETF
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in common stocks and depositary receipts of companies involved in the gold mining industry. The index is a modified market-capitalization weighted index primarily comprised of publicly traded companies involved in the mining for gold and silver. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
GDX tracks a market-cap-weighted index of global gold-mining firms.

GDX is one of the most popular funds in the global gold-mining segment, a trading powerhouse with deep primary, secondary and derivatives markets. Following a 2013 overhaul of the fund`s index, GDX is no longer limited to US-listed firms, nor does it filter out firms that have hedged their gold exposure with derivatives. In addition, it includes firms mining other precious metals in addition to gold, so it`s not entirely pure-play gold miners. GDX includes all the major names, but the fund`s broader take on the gold-mining space means that the big firms get less weight than in our neutral benchmark. As an industry benchmark, GDX falls a bit short, but it's still hugely popular.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to replicate as closely as possible, before fees and expenses, the price and yield performance of the NYSE® Arca Gold Miners Index®. The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in common stocks and depositary receipts of companies involved in the gold mining industry. The index is a modified market-capitalization weighted index primarily comprised of publicly traded companies involved in the mining for gold and silver. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to replicate the performance of a modified market-capitalization weighted index focused on companies in the precious metal mining industry. It normally invests at least 80% of its assets in common stocks and depositary receipts of these firms, primarily those involved in mining gold and silver, but also includes companies mining other precious metals and those with hedged exposure. The index is global and not limited to US-listed firms. This non-diversified fund is a popular choice for gaining exposure to the global gold mining segment, known for its significant trading activity, despite its broader scope potentially giving major companies less weight compared to some pure gold benchmarks.

name: First Trust Technology AlphaDEX Fund
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stocks that comprise the index. The index is a modified equal-dollar weighted index to objectively identify and select stocks from the Russell 1000® Index in the technology sector that may generate positive alpha relative to traditional passive-style indices through the use of the AlphaDEX® selection methodology.
description_eftcom:
FXL tracks a tiered, equal-weighted index of large- and mid-cap US technology firms. Holdings are selected and weighted based on growth and value metrics.

FXL attempts to outperform the broad US technology market by selecting securities based on growth and value factors, and skewing away from neutral coverage. The funds tiered equal-weighting scheme leads to a mid-cap bias and significant sector tilts. That is, FXL overweights semiconductor companies at the expense of larger software and IT services firms. Overall, the fund offers a smart beta approach to the US technology space, instead of giving market-like sector exposure. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield (before the fund's fees and expenses) of an equity index called the StrataQuant® Technology Index. The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the securities that comprise the index. The index is a modified equal-dollar weighted index to objectively identify and select stocks from the Russell 1000® Index in the technology sector that may generate positive alpha relative to traditional passive-style indices through the use of the AlphaDEX® selection methodology.
merged_description: This ETF seeks investment results corresponding generally to the price and yield of a specific equity index focused on the U.S. technology sector. Unlike traditional market-capitalization weighted strategies, this fund employs a smart beta approach using a quantitative methodology to select and weight stocks based on factors such as growth and value metrics. Drawing from large- and mid-cap U.S. technology firms within the Russell 1000® Index, the index utilizes a tiered, modified equal-weighting scheme designed to potentially generate positive returns relative to passive benchmarks. This distinctive strategy often results in a mid-cap bias and specific sector tilts, such as potentially overweighting semiconductor companies compared to larger software and IT services firms. The fund typically invests at least 90% of its net assets in the securities composing this index, which undergoes quarterly reconstitution and rebalancing.

name: iPath Series B S&P 500 VIX Mid-Term Futures ETN
description_original: The iPath Series B S&P 500 VIX Mid-Term FuturesTM ETNs (the "ETNs") are designed to provide exposure to the S&P 500 VIX Mid-Term FuturesTM Index Total Return (the “Index”).  The ETNs are riskier than ordinary unsecured debt securities and have no principal protection.  The ETNs are unsecured debt obligations of the issuer, Barclays Bank PLC, and are not, either directly or indirectly, an obligation of or guaranteed by any third party.  Any payment to be made on the ETNs, including any payment at maturity or upon redemption, depends on the ability of Barclays Bank PLC to satisfy its obligations as they come due.  An investment in the ETNs involves significant risks, including possible loss of principal and may not be suitable for all investors. The Index is designed to provide access to equity market volatility through CBOE Volatility Index (the "VIX Index") futures. The Index offers exposure to a daily rolling long position in the fourth, fifth, sixth and seventh month VIX futures contracts and reflects market participants’ views of the future direction of the VIX index at the time of expiration of the VIX futures contracts comprising the Index. Owning the ETNs is not the same as owning interests in the index components included in the Index or a security directly linked to the performance of the Index. For additional information regarding the risks associated with the ETNs, please see "Selected Risk Considerations" below.
description_eftcom:
VXZ tracks an index with exposure to futures contracts on the CBOE Volatility Index with average five-month maturity. Exposure resets daily.

VXZ offers generic midterm VIX futures exposure in an ETN wrapper. VIX futures allow investors to invest based on their view of the forward implied market volatility of the S&P 500. VXZ and other midterm ETPs provides exposure to VIX futures with average 5-month maturity. As a VIX ETP investor, it is important to note these two caveats: 1) Volatility ETPs deliver poor long-term exposure to the VIX index, and 2) Volatility ETPs have a history of erasing vast sums of investor capital over holdings periods. Investors should be aware of their expected position decay due to persistent contango in VIX futures, historically. Structured as an ETN, VXZ carries the counterparty risk of issuer Barclays. VXZ launched under the ticker VXZB as Series B replacement for the original VXZ. The old VXZ was delisted January 2019, and in May 2019, VXZB took over the VXZ ticker. The current VXZ provides identical exposure as the old one with some structural changes.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks return linked to the performance of the S&P 500® VIX Mid-Term Futures Index TR. The ETN offers exposure to futures contracts of specified maturities on the VIX index and not direct exposure to the VIX index or its spot level. The index is designed to provide investors with exposure to one or more maturities of futures contracts on the CBOE Volatility Index®.
merged_description: This investment seeks return linked to the performance of the S&P 500 VIX Mid-Term Futures Index Total Return. It provides exposure to futures contracts on the CBOE Volatility Index (VIX), specifically a daily rolling long position in the fourth, fifth, sixth, and seventh month VIX futures, resulting in exposure to contracts with an average five-month maturity rather than the spot VIX index. Structured as an unsecured debt obligation of Barclays, it carries counterparty risk and other significant risks, including possible loss of principal and potential performance decay over time due to factors like contango in VIX futures.

name: WisdomTree China ex-State-Owned Enterprises Fund
description_original: Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund's total assets (exclusive of collateral held from securities lending) will be invested in component securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such component securities. The index is a modified float-adjusted market cap weighted index that consists of common stocks in China, excluding common stocks of "state-owned enterprises." The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: CXSE aims to provide broad Chinese equity exposure while excluding state-owned enterprises (SOEs). The underlying investment thesis is that private corporations are run more efficiently and act in the best interests of shareholders rather than the state. CXSEs approach to the Chinese market effectively limits its exposure to large industrials, and focuses instead on technology and consumer firms. A-shares are included, but are capped at 5% of the portfolio. Most of the fund is invested in in H-shares, N-shares, and P-chips, as well as ADRs and direct US listings. Note: CXSE changed its index, ticker, and expense ratio in July 2015. Its old ticker, CHXF, tracked an index of Chinese ex-financial companies with a dividend focus. The fund added A-share exposure in August 2017.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the WisdomTree China ex-State-Owned Enterprises Index. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund's total assets (exclusive of collateral held from securities lending) will be invested in constituent securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such constituent securities. The index is a modified float-adjusted market cap weighted index that consists of common stocks in China, excluding common stocks of "state-owned enterprises." The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: Focused on capturing the performance of Chinese companies while excluding state-owned enterprises (SOEs), this ETF tracks a modified float-adjusted market cap weighted index of common stocks. The strategy is driven by the belief that private Chinese firms are more efficient and aligned with shareholder interests than state-controlled entities. This approach typically results in significant exposure to technology and consumer sectors, with less emphasis on large industrials. Investing at least 80% of its assets in the index constituents, the fund includes various share classes such as H-shares, N-shares, P-chips, ADRs, and direct US listings, with A-shares being a capped component. The fund is classified as non-diversified.

name: Avantis Responsible Emerging Markets Equity ETF
description_original: The fund invests primarily in a diverse group of companies related to emerging markets across market sectors, industry groups and countries. The fund may invest in companies of all market capitalizations. The portfolio management team limits its investable universe of companies by screening out those that raise concerns based on the team’s evaluation of multiple ESG metrics.
description_eftcom: AVSE limits its investable universe of stocks in emerging markets by initially screening out those that do not meet multiple ESG metrics. Portfolio managers utilize third party ESG data and scoring systems combined with a proprietary screening model to exclude stocks from investment consideration. The companies remaining are evaluated based on fundamental criteria, selecting stocks perceived to have higher profitability or lower valuations. As a result, the portfolio tends to overweight small-cap growth stocks. Holdings may include securities denominated in foreign currencies. Eligibility for inclusion is determined at the time of purchase. Should the ESG assessment of a portfolio holding change, the fund managers are not obligated to sell the security. The fund performance relies on efficient portfolio management and trading process to reduce unnecessary risks and transaction costs. The fund is able to engage in securities lending.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks long-term capital appreciation. The fund invests primarily in a diverse group of companies related to emerging markets across market sectors, industry groups and countries. The fund may invest in companies of all market capitalizations. The portfolio management team limits its investable universe of companies by screening out those that raise concerns based on the team’s evaluation of multiple ESG metrics.
merged_description: Seeking long-term capital appreciation, this fund primarily invests in a diverse universe of companies across emerging markets, spanning various sectors, industries, and countries, and may include companies of all market capitalizations. The portfolio management team limits this universe by initially screening out companies that do not meet their evaluation of multiple environmental, social, and governance (ESG) metrics, utilizing third-party data and a proprietary model. From the remaining eligible companies, the fund selects holdings based on fundamental criteria such as profitability and valuation, a process that tends to result in an overweighting of small-cap growth stocks. The fund has flexibility, such as holding securities denominated in foreign currencies and engaging in securities lending. ESG eligibility is determined at the time of purchase, with no obligation to sell if a holding's ESG assessment changes subsequently, and the management approach emphasizes efficient portfolio management and trading to mitigate risks and transaction costs.

name: First Trust South Korea AlphaDEX Fund
description_original: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield (before the fund's fees and expenses) of an equity index called the NASDAQ AlphaDEXÂ® South Korea Index. The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stocks, depositary receipts, real estate investment trusts ("REITs") and preferred shares that comprise the index. The index is designed to select stocks from the NASDAQ South Korea Index (the "base index") that may generate positive alpha, or risk-adjusted returns, relative to traditional indices through the use of the AlphaDEXÂ® selection methodology.
merged_description: This fund seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield, before fees and expenses, of an equity index focused on South Korean securities. The underlying index selects stocks from a base South Korea index using a proprietary AlphaDEX® methodology, which is designed to pick securities that may generate positive risk-adjusted returns, or alpha, compared to traditional indices. The fund typically invests at least 90% of its net assets, including investment borrowings, in the common stocks, depositary receipts, real estate investment trusts, and preferred shares that make up this index.

name: VanEck Oil Services ETF
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities that comprise the fund's benchmark index. The index includes common stocks and depositary receipts of U.S. exchange-listed companies in the oil services segment. Such companies may include small- and medium-capitalization companies and foreign companies that are listed on a U.S. exchange. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
OIH tracks a market-cap-weighted index of 25 of the largest US-listed, publicly traded oil services companies.

OIH had a makeover in late 2011 as the old 'Oil HOLDRS' was taken over by Van Eck and turned into a living, breathing ETF, with new management, and a simple strategy aimed at capturing the 25 largest and most liquid US-listed oil services companies. Although a fraction of its portfolio is focused overseas, OIH overweights the US and makes its own sector bets. Overall, the OIH offers extremely concentrated exposure with a strong bias to US-firms. The index is rebalanced semi-annually.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to replicate as closely as possible, before fees and expenses, the price and yield performance of the MVIS® US Listed Oil Services 25 Index. The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities that comprise the fund's benchmark index. The index includes common stocks and depositary receipts of U.S. exchange-listed companies in the oil services segment. Such companies may include small- and medium-capitalization companies and foreign companies that are listed on a U.S. exchange. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This fund is designed to track the performance of a market-cap-weighted index composed of 25 of the largest and most liquid US-listed companies in the oil services sector. It aims to replicate the price and yield performance of its benchmark index before fees and expenses, typically investing at least 80% of its assets in index securities. While focused on US-listed common stocks and depositary receipts, the index may include small- and medium-capitalization companies and foreign firms listed on a U.S. exchange, though the fund maintains a strong bias towards US companies. Reflecting its simple strategy of capturing these top companies, the fund offers extremely concentrated, non-diversified exposure to this industry segment, with the index undergoing semi-annual rebalancing.

name: Ishares ESG Aware MSCI USA Value ETF
description_original: The underlying index is an optimized equity index designed to reflect the equity performance of U.S. companies that exhibit value characteristics as well as positive ESG characteristics. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and may invest up to 10% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
EVUS is a passively managed fund that tracks an index of US value stocks with certain environmental, social, and governance criteria. The fund aims to maximize its ESG exposure.

EVUS tracks an index of large- and mid-cap US value stocks perceived to have positive ESG characteristics. The parent index, MSCI USA Value Index, identifies value stocks through book value-to-price ratio, 12-month forward earnings-to-price ratio, and dividend yield. Securities are then screened to exclude companies involved in controversial businesses and issues (e.g., weapons, tobacco, climate change issues). All selected securities are assigned an ESG score that evaluates a companys exposure to key ESG issues based on the companys business segment and geographic risk, as well as their strategies and programs to manage these risks and opportunities. Using a sector-specific weighting model, companies are rated and ranked against industry peers. The quantitative process leans toward higher-rated stocks while also considering market-cap and constraints based on the parent index. The fund may engage in securities lending. The index is reviewed and rebalanced quarterly.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the MSCI USA Value Extended ESG Focus Index. The underlying index is an optimized equity index designed to reflect the equity performance of U.S. companies that exhibit value characteristics as well as positive ESG characteristics. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and may invest up to 10% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This passively managed fund seeks to track an index focused on U.S. large- and mid-capitalization companies that demonstrate both value characteristics and positive environmental, social, and governance (ESG) profiles. The underlying index employs a quantitative process to identify value stocks using metrics like book value-to-price and earnings-to-price, while aiming to maximize overall ESG exposure by screening out controversial businesses and favoring companies with higher ESG scores based on their risk management strategies. The fund typically invests at least 90% of its assets in the securities of this index, with the remainder potentially allocated to cash or derivatives, and is considered non-diversified.

name: WisdomTree U.S. Growth & Momentum Fund
description_original: The fund employs a “passive management” – or indexing – investment approach designed to track the performance of the index. The index is provided by O’Neil Global Advisors, Inc. and is comprised of mid- and large-capitalization companies that provide exposure to a portfolio of high growth and momentum U.S. exchange-listed companies. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is October 20,2023. The fund is closing. The last day of trading on an exchange is October 20, 2023. WGRO provides exposure to high growth and momentum stocks in the US, selecting securities in a way that aims to capture positive performance while trying to avoid drawdowns. The fund scores and selects stocks based on fundamental strengths and technical factors, including long-term momentum compared to short-term mean reversion, standard deviation of returns over a one-year period, change in volume compared to historical average, and other growth characteristics. The top 50-100 stocks are then chosen based on each companys scores. Holdings are approximately equally weighted based on their ranks. The ratio of the companies with the maximum weight to the ones with the lowest weight is 2:1. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced on a monthly basis.
merged_description: This fund aimed to provide exposure to high growth and momentum US stocks, focusing on mid- and large-capitalization companies. It tracked a specific index provided by O’Neil Global Advisors, which employed a rules-based methodology to score and select 50-100 companies based on fundamental and technical factors like long-term momentum, volatility, volume changes, and other growth characteristics, with the goal of capturing positive performance while attempting to avoid drawdowns. Holdings were approximately equally weighted based on their rank, with a maximum-to-minimum weight ratio of 2:1. The portfolio was classified as non-diversified. However, the fund is now closing and was delisted from exchanges on October 20, 2023.

name: Invesco High Yield Equity Dividend Achievers ETF
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. Strictly in accordance with its guidelines and mandated procedures, Nasdaq, Inc. includes common stocks in the underlying index that have a consistent record of dividend increases, principally on the basis of dividend yield and consistent growth in dividends.
description_eftcom:
PEY tracks a yield-weighted index of US companies that have increased their annual dividends for at least 10 consecutive years.

PEY's commitment to dividend stability makes it an attractive option in the dividend-seeking space. The fund employs one of the segment's most robust dividend viability screens, only including firms with 10 straight years of dividend increases and growth. The 50 highest-yielding firms above $1 billion in market cap that fit this bill are then weighted by dividend yield. Its basket of US large- and midcaps also makes for easy creation/redemption. The index is reconstituted annually and rebalanced quarterly.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the NASDAQ U.S. Dividend AchieversTM 50 Index (the "underlying index"). The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. Strictly in accordance with its guidelines and mandated procedures, Nasdaq, Inc. includes common stocks in the underlying index that have a consistent record of dividend increases, principally on the basis of dividend yield and consistent growth in dividends. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This fund seeks to track a yield-weighted index comprising 50 US companies that have demonstrated a consistent record of increasing annual dividends for at least 10 consecutive years. Utilizing a robust dividend viability screen, the index selects the 50 highest-yielding firms above $1 billion in market capitalization from this universe, resulting in a basket of US large- and midcaps. These constituents are then weighted by their dividend yield. The fund generally invests at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise this index. This strategy is designed to offer exposure to stable, dividend-paying companies, making it an attractive option for income-seeking investors. The fund is non-diversified, and the underlying index is reconstituted annually and rebalanced quarterly.

name: iBET Sports Betting & Gaming ETF
description_original: The fund invests in equities of companies that are heavily engaged in sports betting or gaming activities and which the fund’s investment adviser believes may benefit from the development of existing and/or new products, services and/or technological improvements and innovation in sports betting and gaming. The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in securities of companies in the Casinos & Gaming sub-industry or companies whose primary business consists of owning, developing, or operating sports betting or gaming venues, software, media content, or electronic platforms. It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
IBET is an actively managed fund that invests in global companies engaged in sports betting and gaming activities, including esports and iGaming.

This fund closed. The last day of trading is September 7, 2023. IBET is one of the few ETFs that offer global exposure to the sports betting and gaming industry. The fund consists of large-, mid, small-cap companies classified under the Casinos & Gaming sub-industry, including iGaming and esports firms. Eligible companies must generate majority of their revenue from the sports betting and gaming industry or have primary business activities related to: i) operating casinos or racetracks, multiplayer video game competition platform, mobile sports betting platform, and online gaming communities, ii) owning real estate primarily used for gaming activities, and iii) developing educational tools for online gaming. Unlike BETZa passively managed fund with similar exposure, IBET actively selects its holdings based on the fund advisers internal research and proprietary fundamental analysis.
merged_description: This actively managed fund provided global exposure to companies deeply involved in the sports betting and gaming industries, encompassing esports and iGaming. It targeted large, mid, and small-capitalization firms primarily engaged in operating venues, platforms, owning related real estate, or developing educational tools within the sector, committing at least 80% of its assets to such securities. Positioned as non-diversified and notable for its global reach and active selection approach, this fund has since closed, with its final day of trading being September 7, 2023.

name: Teucrium Agricultural Fund
description_original: The fund seeks to provide daily investment results that reflect the combined daily performance of the underlying funds. Under normal market conditions, the fund seeks to achieve its investment objective generally by investing equally in shares of each underlying fund and, to a lesser extent, cash equivalents.
description_eftcom:
TAGS is a fund-of-funds that invests directly in the four Teucrium commodity funds. The fund rebalances daily to provide equal exposure to corn, wheat, sugar and soybeans.

TAGS is a fund-of funds that holds four single-commodity Teucrium ETFs (CANE, SOYB, WEAT, and CORN) with exposure to corn, soybeans, wheat and sugar. It rebalances its equally weighted holdings, daily. TAGS' equal weighting can vary greatly from a production-weighted benchmark. The four underlying funds depart from the market in their design, eschewing front-month contracts for contango-mitigation strategies.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to have the daily changes in the NAV of the fund’s Shares reflect the daily changes in a weighted average of the closing settlement prices for certain futures contracts for the commodity specified in the Teucrium Agricultural Fund Index. The fund seeks to provide daily investment results that reflect the combined daily performance of the underlying funds. Under normal market conditions, each underlying fund expects that 100% of its assets will be invested in Benchmark Component Futures Contracts and in cash and cash equivalents.
merged_description: This fund-of-funds provides exposure to agricultural commodities by investing equally in underlying funds focused on corn, wheat, sugar, and soybeans. It rebalances its holdings daily to maintain this equal weighting, a strategy that differs from production-weighted benchmarks. The fund seeks to reflect the combined daily performance of these underlying investments, which primarily consist of commodity futures contracts and cash equivalents. Notably, the underlying funds utilize specific strategies, such as avoiding front-month contracts, to potentially mitigate contango.

name: Janus Henderson Sustainable Corporate Bond ETF
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in U.S. dollar denominated corporate bonds and commercial paper of various maturities. The fund will invest principally in investment grade bonds. The fund will generally sell or dispose of portfolio investments when, in the opinion of the adviser, they no longer present attractive investment opportunity and/or no longer meet the fund’s ESG and/or sustainable criteria.
description_eftcom:
JLQD actively invests in USD-denominated corporate bonds and commercial paper across various credit qualities and maturities. The fund selects investments through a combination of bottom-up fundamental analysis and top-down macroeconomic evaluation.

JLQD seeks total returns primarily through USD-denominated corporate bonds and commercial paper, with a focus on investment-grade securities. It limits exposure to junk bonds to 15%. While industry concentration is typically capped at 25% of total assets, exceptions allow for a 35% allocation when an industry significantly influences the fund's benchmark. The adviser employs a blend of bottom-up fundamental analysis and top-down macroeconomic evaluation, selecting positions to capitalize on market shifts. Derivatives may also be utilized to manage risk, duration, yield curves, or enhance returns. Additionally, up to 20% of investments may include other domestic or foreign debts, such as US treasuries and bank loans. Lending activities may constitute up to one-third of the funds asset value. Prior to May 13, 2024, the fund was known as the Janus Henderson Sustainable Corporate Bond ETF, trading under the ticker SCRD.
