merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks total returns primarily through investments in USD-denominated corporate bonds and commercial paper. It concentrates at least 80% of assets in these securities, focusing principally on investment grade bonds while limiting exposure to lower-rated issues. The investment strategy employs a combination of bottom-up fundamental analysis and top-down macroeconomic evaluation to select holdings across various maturities. The fund may also invest in other domestic or foreign debts and utilize derivatives to manage risk or enhance returns, and can engage in lending activities. Investments are generally sold when they no longer meet investment criteria, present attractive opportunities, or align with potential sustainable considerations.

name: Amplify International Enhanced Dividend Income ETF
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in dividend-paying U.S. exchange-traded American depositary receipt (“ADR”) securities (“Equity Securities”) that are organized or located outside of the U.S. and will opportunistically utilize an “option strategy” consisting of writing (selling) U.S. exchange-traded covered call option contracts on such Equity Securities. It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
IDVO is an actively managed ETF that provides current income and capital appreciation by selecting dividend-paying ADRs of stocks from the MSCI ACWI ex USA Index, overlaid with a tactical call writing strategy.

IDVO aims to provide international equity exposure in a domestic wrapper through active management. It targets high-quality, dividend-paying American depositary receipts of global companies while strategically writing covered calls on those stocks. This ensures income and cash flows from both dividend payments and option premiums in line with the funds primary objective. While IDVO strives for a country- and sector-diversified portfolio, it focuses on large-cap constituents of the MSCI ACWI ex USA Index. Approximately 30-50 potential outperforming dividend-paying stocks are selected and given weights of no more than 8%. IDVOs option strategy involves writing short-term US exchange-traded covered call option contracts on some or all of its individual securities. Additionally, the fund aims to generate 3-4% of gross income from dividends alone and 2-4% from call option contract premiums. On May 14, 2024, the fund incorporated CWP to its name following the addition of a subadviser.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to provide current income as its primary investment objective and to provide capital appreciation as its secondary investment objective. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowings for investment purposes) in dividend-paying U.S. exchange-traded American depositary receipt (“ADR”) securities (“Equity Securities”) that are organized or located outside of the U.S. and will opportunistically utilize an “option strategy” consisting of writing (selling) U.S. exchange-traded covered call option contracts on such Equity Securities. It is non-diversified.
merged_description: Seeking primarily current income alongside capital appreciation, this actively managed ETF invests at least 80% of its assets in dividend-paying U.S. exchange-traded American depositary receipts (ADRs) of companies located outside the U.S. It strategically supplements this income and aims for cash flow by selling U.S. exchange-traded covered call options on its ADR holdings. The fund provides international equity exposure through its focus on dividend-paying large-cap constituents of the MSCI ACWI ex USA Index, though it is classified as non-diversified.

name: First Trust Indxx Innovative Transaction & Process UCITS ETF
description_original: The fund is an actively managed ETF that seeks to provide total return by investing at least 80% of its net assets in the equity securities of companies actively involved in the development and utilization of "transformational data sharing technologies". It may invest in non-U.S. equity securities, including depositary receipts.
description_eftcom: BLOK seeks total return by investing in companies developing or using what it calls transformational data sharing technologies, mostly focusing on blockchain technology. Blockchain, which is the technology that drives Bitcoin, is a distributed, peer-to-peer ledger that facilitates recording transactions and tracking assets in a business environment. The fund further classifies eligible companies into two groups: core, with 70% weight, are firms that derive direct revenue from developing or profitably deploying data sharing technologies, and secondary, having the remaining 30% of the portfolio, are those that have partnered with or invested in such firms. The funds active manager may select companies from any country or industry.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to provide investors with total return. The fund is an actively managed ETF that seeks to provide total return by investing at least 80% of its net assets in the equity securities of companies actively involved in the development and utilization of "transformational data sharing technologies". It may invest in non-U.S. equity securities, including depositary receipts.
merged_description: This actively managed ETF seeks total return by investing primarily in equity securities of companies involved in transformational data sharing technologies, with a significant focus on blockchain technology. The fund classifies eligible companies into core firms (70% weight) that derive direct revenue from developing or deploying these technologies, and secondary firms (30% weight) that have partnered with or invested in them. Its active manager has the flexibility to select companies from any country or industry.

name: First Trust Emerging Markets Human Flourishing ETF
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in the securities that comprise the index. According to the index provider, the index is constructed to track the performance of companies within emerging market countries that sufficiently promote human flourishing. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: FTHF invests in human rights and dignity by offering exposure to companies in the emerging market equity space that promotes human flourishing. Eligible securities are screened and derived from the Bloomberg Emerging Markets Large & Mid Cap universe to have sufficient Human Dignity Score based on freedom of expression and belief (80%) and freedom from religious persecution (20%). Companies that are in the top 50th percentile are further analyzed and screened with those associated with seven enumerated controversial practices removed. The remaining securities are then market cap-weighted with the largest 150 stocks further excluded. Among the outstandings, the 100 securities with the highest quality scores based on variability, profitability and leverage are then selected for inclusion in the index. The final constituents are free-float market cap-weighted, while subject to a country, sector, and issuer exposure cap. The index reconstitutes annually and rebalances semiannually.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield, before fees and expenses, of an equity index called the Emerging Markets Human Flourishing Index. The fund will normally invest at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in the securities that comprise the index. According to the index provider, the index is constructed to track the performance of companies within emerging market countries that sufficiently promote human flourishing. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This fund seeks to track an equity index focused on emerging market companies that promote human flourishing, typically investing at least 80% of its assets in the index's securities. The index identifies eligible companies from a broad emerging market universe, first screening them based on a Human Dignity Score incorporating freedom of expression, belief, and freedom from religious persecution. Companies involved in specific controversial practices are excluded, as are the 150 largest stocks by market cap. From the remainder, the 100 companies with the highest quality scores (based on variability, profitability, and leverage) are selected. These are then free-float market cap-weighted, subject to country, sector, and issuer caps. The index is reconstituted annually and rebalanced semiannually. This fund is non-diversified.

name: VanEck Rare Earth/Strategic Metals ETF
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities that comprise the fund's benchmark index. The index includes companies primarily engaged in a variety of activities that are related to the producing, refining and recycling of rare earth and strategic metals and minerals. It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
REMX tracks an index of global companies that mine, refine, or recycle rare earth and strategic metals.

REMX targets an obscure part of the mining marketrare earths metalswhich means it only covers a very thin slice of our global mining benchmark. The fund invests in the largest and most liquid companies that generate at least 50% of their revenues from the global rare earth and strategic metals segment, and has significant exposure to small- and micro-caps and emerging-market issuersthe firms you typically find producing cerium, manganese, titanium, and tungsten. REMX's narrow portfolio holds just a handful of names, selected and weighted by market cap, with a cap of 8% per issuer to ensure diversification. The index is rebalanced quarterly. Prior to May 6, 2024, the '/' in the fund name has been replaced with 'and'.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to replicate as closely as possible, before fees and expenses, the price and yield performance of the MVIS® Global Rare Earth/Strategic Metals Index. The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities that comprise the fund's benchmark index. The index includes companies primarily engaged in a variety of activities that are related to the producing, refining and recycling of rare earth and strategic metals and minerals. It is non-diversified.
merged_description: A fund tracks an index of global companies involved in the rare earth and strategic metals and minerals sector, aiming to replicate its performance by typically investing at least 80% of its assets in index securities. It focuses on firms primarily engaged in producing, refining, and recycling these materials, targeting those that derive a majority of their revenue from this specific, niche segment of the global mining market. The fund holds a narrow portfolio of the largest and most liquid companies in this sector, including significant exposure to small- and micro-cap companies and emerging market issuers. Holdings are market-cap weighted with an 8% issuer cap, and the index is rebalanced quarterly. The fund is considered non-diversified.

name: ProShares Pet Care ETF
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in component securities of the index. The index consists of U.S. and non-U.S. companies that potentially stand to benefit from interest in, and resources spent on, pet ownership. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: PAWZ is the first fund centered on companies related to pet ownership. To be selected, a stock must fit one of eight RBICS sub-industries: pet food manufacturing, pet supplies manufacturing, pet and pet supply stores, veterinary pharmaceuticals, veterinary diagnostics, veterinary product distributors, veterinary services, and internet pet and supply retail. Constituents may be domiciled in any country. PAWZ is weighted in two tiers: a core tier of companies deriving more than 50% of their revenue from the listed sub-industries and a non-core tier of companies with over $1B in revenue, but less than 50% of those revenues from the above groups. The core tier gets 85% of fund assets and the non-core tier gets the remainder. Within each tier, individual weights are determined by market cap. The index has an annual reconstitution and a monthly rebalance.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks investment results, before fees and expenses, that track the performance of the FactSet Pet Care Index (the "index"). The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of companies that stand to benefit from interest in or resources spent on pet ownership. Under normal circumstances, it will invest at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This fund aims to track the performance of an index designed to measure companies that stand to benefit from interest in or resources spent on pet ownership. It typically invests at least 80% of its total assets in component securities of this index or instruments with similar economic characteristics. Focused on companies related to pet ownership, the fund includes both U.S. and non-U.S. companies operating in specific sub-industries such as pet food and supplies manufacturing and retail, veterinary pharmaceuticals, diagnostics, distributors, and services, and internet pet retail. The fund employs a two-tier weighting approach, allocating 85% of its assets to a core group of companies with over 50% revenue from these industries and the remaining 15% to a non-core group meeting revenue thresholds but with less than 50% from these industries, with market capitalization determining weights within each tier. It undergoes annual reconstitution and monthly rebalancing, and is classified as non-diversified.

name: Amplify BlackSwan Tech & Treasury ETF
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the index. The index is a rules-based, quantitative index designed to allow for some participation in the investment gains experienced by QQQ while providing the opportunity for a buffer against significant losses through the index’s target portfolio weighting of approximately 90% U.S. treasury securities. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
QSWN tracks an index of long-dated LEAP options on Invesco QQQ Trust (QQQ) and US Treasurys averaging 10-year maturity.

The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is March 05, 2025 .QSWN expands Amplifys suite of ETFs attempting to hedge against unpredictable market events referred to as Black Swans. To provide capital protection, the fund holds 90% of its exposure in laddered US Treasury securities targeting a duration within six months of the 10-Year Note. The remaining 10% of the portfolio is used to buy in-the-money, long-term call options on the Invesco QQQ Trust (ticker: QQQ). QQQ provides exposure to the top 100 NASDAQ-listed nonfinancial stocks, skewing towards technology. The call options provide equity exposure and will have expirations of either June or December. At their expiration, the options will be rolled to the following year. Therefore, the index will be reconstituted and rebalanced every June and December. The call options selected will generally have a delta of 70 at the time of purchase, meaning that for every $1.00 USD of movement in the QQQ share price, each option should have a corresponding $0.70 USD gain or loss.
merged_description: This ETF tracks a quantitative, rules-based index designed to offer participation in the potential gains of the Invesco QQQ Trust (QQQ) while seeking to buffer against significant losses. Its strategy involves allocating approximately 90% of its assets to U.S. Treasury securities, specifically laddered notes targeting a duration similar to the 10-Year Note. The remaining roughly 10% is invested in long-term, in-the-money call options on QQQ, which represents the top 100 nonfinancial stocks listed on NASDAQ, with a focus on technology companies. These call options, selected with a general target delta of 70 at purchase, have June or December expirations and are rolled annually, coinciding with the index's semi-annual rebalancing. The fund is classified as non-diversified.

name: Vanguard Utilities Index Fund
description_original: The fund employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the MSCI US Investable Market Index (IMI)/Utilities 25/50, an index made up of stocks of large, mid-size, and small U.S. companies within the utilities sector, as classified under the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS). The Advisor attempts to replicate the target index by seeking to invest all, or substantially all, of its assets in the stocks that make up the index, in order to hold each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
The fund is passively managed to invest in the US utilities sector.

VPU is designed to track an all-cap index of US electric, gas, and water utility companies. The index is market-cap weighted index and subject to capping limitations. The capping is designed to ensure diversity among its portfolio by limiting the weight of a single issuer to 25% of the funds assets. The fund may also hold independent power producers, energy traders and companies engaged in electricity using renewable sources. VPU attempts to replicate the target index by seeking to invest all, or substantially all, of its assets in the stocks that make up the Index, in order to hold each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the Index. The index is rebalanced quarterly.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the performance of the MSCI US Investable Market Index (IMI)/Utilities 25/50. The fund employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the index, an index made up of stocks of large, mid-size, and small U.S. companies within the utilities sector, as classified under the GICS. The Advisor attempts to replicate the target index by seeking to invest all, or substantially all, of its assets in the stocks that make up the index, in order to hold each stock in approximately the same proportion as its weighting in the index. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This ETF is passively managed using an indexing approach to track the performance of the MSCI US Investable Market Index (IMI)/Utilities 25/50. This index is composed of stocks of large, mid-size, and small U.S. companies primarily within the utilities sector, including electric, gas, and water utilities, and may also hold related companies like independent power producers or those involved in renewable energy. The fund seeks to replicate the target index by investing substantially all of its assets in the constituent stocks in approximately the same proportion as their weighting in the market-cap weighted index, which includes a 25/50 capping limitation for portfolio diversity and is rebalanced quarterly. The fund is classified as non-diversified.

name: AAM Transformers ETF
description_original: The fund uses a “passive management” (or indexing) approach to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the index. The index is a rules-based index that measures the performance of U.S.-listed common equity securities, including American Depositary Receipts (“ADRs”) for foreign securities, of companies poised to benefit from a significant disruption and/or transformation of consumer behavior and technological innovation.
description_eftcom:
TRFM tracks a modified equal-weighted index of US-listed companies that have the potential to transform consumer behavior and technological innovation. Companies are screened for their spending on research and development (R&D).

TRFM holds equities of US-listed companies, including ADRs, that are positioned to benefit from a significant disruption or transformation of consumer behavior and technological innovation. Exposure includes autonomous driving and electric vehicles, digital economy, 5G, low-carbon technologies, and renewable energy. Aside from meeting a minimum market capitalization of $2 billion, an eligible company must typically have at least five analyst recommendations and a consensus analyst rating above 3.0. The index selects securities based on quantitative factors that indicate thematic exposure through R&D spending. The resulting portfolio is weighted into five tiers, categorized by market capitalization and domicile, with securities weighted equally within each tier. About 20% of the portfolio is allocated to US-based companies with over $100 billion in market capitalization. In aggregate, US-based companies are assigned 75% portfolio weight. The index is reconstituted quarterly.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the Pence Transformers Index. The fund uses a “passive management” (or indexing) approach to track the total return performance, before fees and expenses, of the index. The index is a rules-based index that measures the performance of U.S.-listed common equity securities, including American Depositary Receipts (“ADRs”) for foreign securities, of companies poised to benefit from a significant disruption and/or transformation of consumer behavior and technological innovation.
merged_description: This ETF employs a passive management strategy to track a rules-based index designed to measure the performance of US-listed companies, including ADRs, that are positioned to benefit from significant disruption and transformation in consumer behavior and technological innovation. The index selects securities based on quantitative factors, screening companies for criteria such as research and development spending, minimum market capitalization, and analyst recommendations. The portfolio is constructed with a modified equal-weighting approach, where securities are weighted equally within five market capitalization and domicile tiers, resulting in approximately 75% exposure to US-based companies. The underlying holdings represent key themes such as autonomous driving, electric vehicles, the digital economy, 5G, low-carbon technologies, and renewable energy.

name: Schwab U.S. REIT ETF
description_original: The index excludes mortgage REITs, defined as REITs that lend money directly to real estate owners and/or operators or indirectly through the purchase of mortgages or mortgage-backed securities, and hybrid REITs, defined as REITs that participate both in equity and mortgage investing. It is the fund’s policy that under normal circumstances it will invest at least 90% of its net assets in securities included in the index.
description_eftcom:
SCHH tracks a market-cap-weighted index of US real estate investment trusts, excluding mortgage REITs and hybrid REITs.

SCHH is passively managed to invest in US equity REITS which primarily own and operate income-producing real estate. The fund excludes mortgage REITS or those involved in real estate finance, and hybrid REITs involved in both equity and mortgage. The index selects its constituents based on market cap and liquidity screens, subject to certain constraints. First, no single companys weight can exceed 10% and second, aggregate weight of all companies weighing above 4.5% cannot exceed 22.5%. The Index is market-cap weighted and undergoes a quarterly review. Prior to June 22, 2020, SCHH follows the Dow Jones U.S. Select REIT Index which has the same methodology but without the additional cap constraints.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track as closely as possible, before fees and expenses, the total return of the Dow Jones Equity All REIT Capped Index† composed of U.S. real estate investment trusts classified as equities. The index excludes mortgage REITs, defined as REITs that lend money directly to real estate owners and/or operators or indirectly through the purchase of mortgages or mortgage-backed securities, and hybrid REITs, defined as REITs that participate both in equity and mortgage investing. It is the fund’s policy that under normal circumstances it will invest at least 90% of its net assets in securities included in the index.
merged_description: This product is a passively managed fund designed to track the total return of the Dow Jones Equity All REIT Capped Index†, which focuses exclusively on U.S. real estate investment trusts (REITs) primarily engaged in owning and operating income-producing real estate. A key characteristic is its deliberate exclusion of mortgage REITs and hybrid REITs to maintain a pure equity exposure to the real estate market. The underlying index is market-cap weighted but incorporates capping constraints: no single constituent can exceed 10% weight, and the aggregate weight of holdings exceeding 4.5% is capped at 22.5%; the index is reviewed quarterly. Under normal circumstances, the fund maintains a policy of investing at least 90% of its net assets in securities included in this index.

name: Xtrackers J.P. Morgan ESG Emerging Markets Sovereign ETF
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets, but typically far more, in instruments that comprise the underlying index. The index generally aims to keep the broad characteristics of its parent index, the J.P. Morgan EMBI Global Diversified Sovereign Index, resulting in a broad emerging markets sovereign debt market exposure with ESG aspects. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: The security is being delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is March 13, 2024. ESEB is passively managed to invest in USD-denominated emerging markets sovereign bonds. Securities include both investment-grade and high-yield fixed, floating-rate, and capitalizing/amortizing bonds, while it excludes convertible and inflation-linked debts. ESEB includes bonds with broad maturities, with at least 1-2 years until maturity. The index considers the characteristics of its parent index, J.P. Morgan EMBI Global Diversified Sovereign Index, in selecting its constituents. Then, it applies an ESG score to each issuer and assigns them to a quintile based on that score. Issuers in the lowest quintile are removed, and the remainder are weighted based on which quintile they were scored. ESEB is rebalanced on a monthly basis. Prior to May 12, 2020, the fund is known as Xtrackers Emerging Markets Bond - Interest Rate Hedged ETF (EMIH) and followed the Solactive Emerging Markets Bond - Interest Rate Hedged Index.
merged_description: This passively managed fund invests in USD-denominated emerging markets sovereign bonds, seeking broad exposure to this market segment. It is based on the characteristics of the J.P. Morgan EMBI Global Diversified Sovereign Index and incorporates an ESG screen that scores issuers, removes the lowest quintile, and weights the remaining constituents by their ESG score. The portfolio primarily consists of investment-grade and high-yield, fixed and floating-rate bonds with broad maturities (at least 1-2 years), while excluding convertible and inflation-linked debts. The fund is considered non-diversified and typically invests at least 80% of its assets in underlying index constituents. It is rebalanced monthly. Please note, this security is being delisted, with March 13, 2024, designated as its final day of trading.

name: Columbia Sustainable International Equity Income ETF
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the index and depositary receipts representing such securities. The index, which typically holds common stocks and depositary receipts, was constructed to provide exposure to foreign large- and mid-cap companies that are believed to offer sustainable levels of income, as well as total return opportunity.
description_eftcom: INEQ seeks total return by holding an income-producing equity portfolio of primarily large- and mid-cap developed market ex-US companies. To be eligible for inclusion, each company must have a low ESG Materiality Rating and a forward annualized dividend yield of at least 1%. Eligible companies are scored on a sector-relative basis, focusing on forward dividend yield, dividend growth, and cash-based dividend coverage ratio factors. The fund selects the 100 highest-scoring securities and weights the resulting portfolio on a market cap basis. Although the fund is actively managed, it applies investing rules at least quarterly. Before Oct. 14, 2022, the fund traded as Columbia Sustainable International Equity Income ETF and tracked the Beta Advantage Sustainable International Equity Income 100 Index. Prior to June 3, 2024, the fund was named Columbia International ESG Equity Income ETF, traded under the ticker ESGN, and tracked the Beta Advantage International ESG Equity Income Index.
merged_description: This ETF seeks total return by investing in a portfolio of primarily large- and mid-capitalization developed market equities outside the United States. It focuses on identifying companies believed to offer sustainable levels of income, as well as total return opportunity. The fund applies specific rules for security selection: eligible companies must meet certain criteria, including a low ESG materiality rating and a minimum forward annualized dividend yield. Securities are then scored on a sector-relative basis focusing on factors like forward dividend yield, dividend growth, and cash-based dividend coverage ratio. The portfolio typically consists of the highest-scoring securities, weighted by market capitalization, and may include depositary receipts alongside common stocks.

name: iShares MSCI Intl Quality Factor ETF
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The index measures the performance of international developed large- and mid-capitalization stocks exhibiting relatively higher quality characteristics as identified through three fundamental variables: return on equity, earnings variability and debt-to-equity.
description_eftcom:
IQLT tracks an index of large- and mid-cap stocks in developed countries, outside of the US. The index is selected and weighted for exposure to fundamental quality metrics.

IQLT screens its international equity universe based on three measures of fundamental quality: return on equity, debt/equity ratio, and earnings variability. At each semi-annual rebalance, the fund selects securities with the highest combined quality score. Holdings are weighted such that each sector receives the same weight as in the market cap-weighted universe. Within each sector, holdings are weighted by their quality score, scaled by market-cap. A capping scheme of 5% for each individual security is also applied.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the MSCI World ex USA Sector Neutral Quality Index. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The index measures the performance of international developed large- and mid-capitalization stocks exhibiting relatively higher quality characteristics as identified through three fundamental variables: return on equity, earnings variability and debt-to-equity.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to track the performance of an index focusing on large- and mid-capitalization stocks in developed countries outside the United States. It generally invests at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index or investments with substantially identical economic characteristics. The index measures the performance of international developed large- and mid-cap stocks exhibiting relatively higher quality characteristics, which are identified through fundamental variables including return on equity, earnings variability, and debt-to-equity. Securities are selected and weighted based on these quality metrics, structured to maintain sector neutrality relative to the broader market while emphasizing quality within sectors, subject to a per-security capping scheme.

name: Invesco S&P 500 Equal Weight Health Care ETF
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of all of the components of the S&P 500® Health Care Index, an index that contains the common stocks of all companies included in the S&P 500® Index that are classified as members of the health care sector, as defined according to the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS).
description_eftcom: RSPH holds a portfolio of health care companies from the S&P 500. Instead of weighting its holdings by market cap, RSPH uses an equal-weighting scheme. The result is a portfolio that does not deviate much from the broad US health care market but is still far less concentrated than the industry with a skew toward midcaps. This causes profound industry tilts, though it doesn't necessarily add more risk. With less concentration in pharma, RSPH provides more balanced exposure to other industries within the health care sector such as equipment & supplies, healthcare providers, and drug retailers. The index is rebalanced on a quarterly basis. Prior to June 07, 2023, the fund traded under the ticker, RYH.
merged_description: This fund focuses on the health care sector within the S&P 500 Index, typically investing at least 90% of its assets in the securities of its underlying index composed of common stocks from S&P 500 companies classified within this sector. A defining feature is its use of an equal-weighting scheme rather than traditional market capitalization weighting, which results in a portfolio significantly less concentrated than market-cap-weighted sector indices. This methodology leads to a skew towards midcap companies and provides more balanced exposure across various health care sub-industries, including equipment & supplies, healthcare providers, and drug retailers, mitigating heavy concentration in pharmaceuticals. The underlying index is rebalanced on a quarterly basis.

name: ProShares Ultra Semiconductors
description_original: The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should produce daily returns consistent with the fund's investment objective. The index is designed to measure the stock performance of U.S. companies in the semiconductors sub-sector. Component companies are engaged in the production and distribution of semiconductors and other integrated chips, as well as other related products such as semiconductor capital equipment and mother-boards. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
USD provides 2x exposure to a market-cap-weighted index that tracks the performance of large US semiconductor companies.

USD, as a levered product, is not a buy-and-hold ETF, it's a short-term tactical instrument. Investors get concentrated exposure to the biggest companies that engage in the production and distribution of semiconductors and other integrated chips, as well as other related products such as semiconductor capital equipment and motherboards. Like many levered funds, USD promises 2x exposure only for one day. Over longer periods, returns can vary significantly from 2x exposure to its underlying index.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks daily investment results that correspond to two times (2x) the daily performance of the Dow Jones U.S. SemiconductorsSM Index. The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should produce daily returns consistent with the Daily Target. The index is designed to measure the stock performance of U.S. companies in the semiconductors sub-sector. Under normal circumstances, the fund will obtain leveraged exposure to at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This leveraged fund seeks daily investment results that correspond to two times (2x) the daily performance of an index tracking U.S. companies in the semiconductors sub-sector. The index measures the stock performance of companies primarily engaged in the production and distribution of semiconductors, integrated chips, and related products such as semiconductor capital equipment and motherboards, providing concentrated exposure to the biggest firms in this sector. It invests in financial instruments designed to produce daily returns consistent with its 2x daily objective. As a leveraged product, it is designed for short-term, tactical use and is not suitable for long-term buy-and-hold strategies because its 2x exposure target is reset daily, meaning returns over longer periods may significantly differ from two times the index's performance. The fund is also non-diversified.

name: VanEck Biotech ETF
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities that comprise the fund's benchmark index. The Biotech Index includes common stocks and depositary receipts of U.S. exchange-listed companies in the biotechnology industry. Such companies may include medium-capitalization companies and foreign companies that are listed on a U.S. exchange. It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
BBH tracks a market-cap-weighted index of the 25 largest biotech firms globally.

BBH offers a more concentrated take on the global biotech industry. Although the space is already dominated by US firms, the fund aims to select just 25 US listed companies by market cap, also weighing each constituent by market cap. The underlying index has a flexible definition of biotech, encompassing companies engaged primarily in research (including research contractors) and development as well as production, marketing and sales of drugs based on genetic analysis and diagnostic equipment, excluding pharmacies. Also, despite capping its issuers to a maximum of 20%, the fund may still be top heavy due to the indexs concentrated nature. Overall, BBH is a viable take on this market. The index is reviewed semi-annually.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to replicate as closely as possible, before fees and expenses, the price and yield performance of the MVIS® US Listed Biotech 25 Index. The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities that comprise the fund's benchmark index. The Biotech Index includes common stocks and depositary receipts of U.S. exchange-listed companies in the biotechnology industry. Such companies may include medium-capitalization companies and foreign companies that are listed on a U.S. exchange. It is non-diversified.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to replicate the performance of a market-cap-weighted index focused on the biotechnology industry, normally investing at least 80% of its assets in the index's securities. The underlying index is composed of 25 US exchange-listed companies, primarily selected by market capitalization, and includes firms involved in the research, development, production, marketing, and sales of drugs based on genetic analysis and diagnostic equipment, excluding pharmacies. The index, which can include medium-capitalization and foreign companies listed on a US exchange, weights constituents by market cap and is reviewed semi-annually. Due to its limited number of holdings, the fund is considered concentrated and non-diversified, potentially resulting in a top-heavy structure despite an issuer cap.

name: Vanguard Total Corporate Bond ETF
description_original: The fund is a fund of funds and employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the Bloomberg U.S. Corporate Bond Index, which measures the investment-grade, fixed-rate, taxable corporate bond market. The index includes U.S. dollar-denominated securities that are publicly issued by industrial, utility, and financial issuers.
description_eftcom:
VTC tracks an index designed to provide exposure to investment-grade US corporate bonds with broad maturities.

VTC provides diversified exposure to the US investment-grade corporate bond market within one ticker. The fund uses a sampling method in tracking its index, which means it will invest in a sample of securities that collectively have an investment profile similar to that of the underlying index. The index is rebalanced monthly. Prior to March 4, 2025, the fund held three underlying ETFs that provided exposure across the duration spectrum, in attempt to track the same index.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the performance of the Bloomberg U.S. Corporate Bond Index. The fund is a fund of funds and employs an indexing investment approach designed to track the performance of the Bloomberg U.S. Corporate Bond Index, which measures the investment-grade, fixed-rate, taxable corporate bond market. The index includes U.S. dollar-denominated securities that are publicly issued by industrial, utility, and financial issuers.
merged_description: The ETF aims to track the performance of the Bloomberg U.S. Corporate Bond Index, which measures the investment-grade, fixed-rate, taxable U.S. corporate bond market. This index includes publicly issued, U.S. dollar-denominated securities from industrial, utility, and financial sectors, providing broad exposure across maturities. Designed to offer diversified access to the U.S. investment-grade corporate bond market, the fund currently uses a sampling method to invest in a selection of securities representative of the index, which undergoes monthly rebalancing. Previously, prior to March 4, 2025, the fund employed a fund-of-funds structure holding underlying ETFs to achieve its investment objective.

name: Vanguard U.S. Momentum Factor ETF
description_original: The fund invests primarily in U.S. common stocks with the potential to generate higher returns relative to the broad U.S. equity market by investing in stocks with strong recent performance as determined by the advisor. The portfolio will include a diverse mix of companies representing many different market sectors and industry groups. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund's assets will be invested in securities issued by U.S. companies.
description_eftcom:
VFMO is an actively managed fund that invests in large-, mid-, and small-cap US stocks with high momentum.

While VFMO is an actively managed fund, the portfolio manager follows a rules-based, quantitative approach to offer high momentum exposure to US equities of all sizes. Stocks are evaluated on their momentum for the past year, then selected and weighted using a proprietary model. The fund seeks diverse holdings, incorporating stocks of different market-caps and sectors.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to provide long-term capital appreciation by investing in stocks with strong recent performance as determined by the advisor. The fund invests primarily in U.S. common stocks with the potential to generate higher returns relative to the broad U.S. equity market by investing in stocks with strong recent performance as determined by the advisor. The portfolio will include a diverse mix of companies representing many different market sectors and industry groups. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund's assets will be invested in securities issued by U.S. companies.
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks long-term capital appreciation by investing primarily in U.S. common stocks selected for their strong recent performance or momentum. Following a rules-based, quantitative approach, the fund evaluates stocks based on their performance over the past year, using a proprietary model for selection and weighting. The portfolio aims for diverse holdings, including large, mid, and small-cap companies across various market sectors and industries, with at least 80% of assets typically invested in U.S. companies.

name: VanEck Pharmaceutical ETF
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities that comprise the fund's benchmark index. The index includes common stocks and depositary receipts of U.S. exchange-listed companies in the pharmaceutical industry. Such companies may include medium-capitalization companies and foreign companies that are listed on a U.S. exchange. It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
PPH tracks a market-cap-weighted index of 25 of the largest global pharmaceutical firms.

PPH provides exposure to the largest, US-listed multinational pharmaceutical giants in the world. The fund holds just 25 securities, including big weights in household names. Like the underlying pharmaceutical market, PPH is top heavy and has to reweight its big holdings to accommodate RIC diversification requirements, capping a single issuer to 20%. Still, it captures the space well, even after excluding Asia entirely. Overall, PPH is a great option for investors seeking exposure to big, multinational pharma companies. The index is reviewed on a semi-annual basis.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to replicate as closely as possible, before fees and expenses, the price and yield performance of the MVIS® US Listed Pharmaceutical 25 Index. The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities that comprise the fund's benchmark index. The index includes common stocks and depositary receipts of U.S. exchange-listed companies in the pharmaceutical industry. Such companies may include medium-capitalization companies and foreign companies that are listed on a U.S. exchange. It is non-diversified.
merged_description: This fund seeks to replicate the price and yield performance of a market-cap-weighted index focused on the pharmaceutical industry. The index provides exposure to approximately 25 global pharmaceutical companies, primarily large multinational firms, listed on US exchanges; it may also include medium-capitalization companies and foreign companies with US listings. The fund is non-diversified and tends to be top-heavy, although holdings are capped to meet regulatory requirements, such as a 20% maximum per issuer. It holds about 25 securities and notably excludes companies from Asia. The underlying index is reviewed semi-annually.

name: Invesco S&P MidCap 400 Pure Growth ETF
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of a subset of securities from the S&P MidCap 400® Index that exhibit strong growth characteristics.
description_eftcom:
RFG tracks a factor-weighted index of the S&P 400 companies exhibiting the strongest growth factors.

RFG is a growth-oriented mid-cap ETF picking companies in the S&P 400 based on sales growth, price-to-earnings growth, and momentum. It then weights them according to these growth characteristics. The Pure name claim comes from the fact that it excludes securities showing value characteristics and those in the middle of the growth-value spectrum, it chooses strictly growth stocks. Ultimately, RFG aims to provide a pure-style take on mid-cap growth companies. The Fund and the Index are rebalanced annually.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the S&P MidCap 400® Pure Growth Index (the "underlying index"). The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of a subset of securities from the S&P MidCap 400® Index that exhibit strong growth characteristics.
merged_description: This fund seeks to track an index focused on mid-cap companies selected from the S&P MidCap 400 Index. It aims to provide exposure to a "pure growth" style by strictly including companies exhibiting strong growth characteristics, specifically based on factors such as sales growth, price-to-earnings growth, and momentum, while excluding those with value or blend attributes. The selected companies are weighted according to these growth characteristics. The fund typically invests at least 90% of its assets in the underlying index securities, which are rebalanced annually.

name: iShares Global Clean Energy ETF
description_original: The index is designed to track the performance of approximately 100 clean energy-related companies. The fund generally invests at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents, as well as in securities not included in the index. It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
ICLN tracks a tiered index of global companies involved in clean energy businesses.

ICLN invests in global clean energy companies, which is defined as those involved in the biofuels, ethanol, geothermal, hydroelectric, solar, and wind industries. Aside from holding companies that produce energy through these means, ICLN also includes companies that develop technology and equipment used in the process. Selected by the index committee, the fund is weighted by market-cap and exposure score subject to several constraints and reconstituted semi-annually. Prior to April 19, 2021, the index followed a more narrow methodology.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the S&P Global Clean Energy Transition Index composed of global equities in the clean energy sector. The index is designed to track the performance of approximately 100 clean energy-related companies. The fund generally invests at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents, as well as in securities not included in the index. It is non-diversified.
merged_description: This ETF aims to capture the global clean energy transition by tracking the S&P Global Clean Energy Transition Index. This index comprises approximately 100 global equities representing companies primarily engaged in clean energy businesses, including generation from biofuels, ethanol, geothermal, hydroelectric, solar, and wind sources, as well as those developing related technology and equipment. The fund typically invests at least 80% of its assets in the index's components or equivalent investments, with flexibility to allocate up to 20% to derivatives, cash, and other securities. Index constituents are weighted based on market capitalization and exposure score with constraints, and the index undergoes semi-annual reconstitution. Due to its targeted focus on this sector, the fund is classified as non-diversified.

name: First Trust Health Care AlphaDEX Fund
description_original: The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the common stocks that comprise the index. The index is a modified equal-dollar weighted index to objectively identify and select stocks from the Russell 1000® Index in the health care sector that may generate positive alpha relative to traditional passive-style indices through the use of the AlphaDEX® selection methodology.
description_eftcom:
FXH tracks a tiered, equal-weighted index of large- and mid-cap US health care companies. Holdings are selected and weighted based on various growth and value criteria.

FXH tracks a quant-driven index that attempts to achieve excess returns by selecting health care stocks based on growth and value factors, and equal-weighting them in tiers. The portfolio offers noteworthy mid-cap exposure, downplaying familiar large-cap names relative to cap-weighted peer funds. Additionally, FXH underweights pharmaceuticals relative to the market, but allows a significant exposure to biotechnology and healthcare providers. Overall, this fund offers a smart beta approach to the US health care space, tilting away from big pharma and towards other facets of health care. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced on a quarterly basis.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield (before the fund's fees and expenses) of an equity index called the StrataQuant® Health Care Index. The fund will normally invest at least 90% of its net assets (including investment borrowings) in the securities that comprise the index. The index is a modified equal-dollar weighted index to objectively identify and select stocks from the Russell 1000® Index in the health care sector that may generate positive alpha relative to traditional passive-style indices through the use of the AlphaDEX® selection methodology.
merged_description: This ETF seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield of a quantitative index focused on the US health care sector. The index utilizes a modified equal-dollar weighting and employs an AlphaDEX® selection methodology to objectively identify and select stocks from the Russell 1000® Index based on various growth and value criteria. This approach aims to generate positive alpha relative to traditional passive indices and results in a portfolio with noteworthy mid-cap exposure, downplaying familiar large-cap names. It also underweights pharmaceuticals compared to the market while allowing significant exposure to biotechnology and healthcare providers, offering a smart beta tilt within the health care space. The fund normally invests at least 90% of its net assets in the securities comprising this index, which is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly.

name: Proshares S&P Global Core Battery Metals ETF
description_original: The index consists of companies that had (i) positive total revenue and (ii) positive production value from, in aggregate, the mining of lithium, nickel and cobalt during the previous year. Production value is the dollar market value of the lithium, nickel or cobalt produced. Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets, plus any borrowings for investment purposes, in the securities that comprise the index. It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: ION is a passively managed ETF that provides exposure to companies engaged in the mining of metals used in battery production. The portfolio is comprised of stocks and depositary receipts that had positive total revenue and production value (dollar market value) from the mining of lithium, nickel, and cobalt during the prior year. Companies could be of any market capitalization from both developed and emerging countries. Using a mathematical approach, the fund determines the type, quantity, and mix of investment positions that are expected to produce returns. Weighting is set to each securitys ranking based on production-value-to-revenue ratio divided by the sum of all ranks. A basket liquidity maximum weight is calculated to determine security capping, with excess amounts redistributed across the portfolio. The index is reweighted quarterly in January, April, July, and October, with annual reconstitution every July.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks investment results, before fees and expenses, that track the performance of the S&P Global Core Battery Metals Index. The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of companies in the S&P Global Broad Market Index engaged in the mining of cobalt, lithium, and nickel—base metals used to produce batteries. Under normal circumstances, it will invest at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. It is non-diversified.
merged_description: This passively managed ETF aims to provide exposure to companies primarily engaged in mining metals essential for battery production, specifically lithium, nickel, and cobalt. It invests in stocks and depositary receipts of companies from developed and emerging markets of any size, selected based on having positive total revenue and positive production value from these metals in the preceding year. Under normal circumstances, the fund typically invests at least 80% of its assets in securities that comprise the underlying index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. A mathematical approach is used for portfolio construction and weighting, involving a production-value-to-revenue ratio rank, security capping, and redistribution. The index is reweighted quarterly and undergoes annual reconstitution. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Fidelity Real Estate Investment ETF
description_original: The fund is an actively managed ETF that operates pursuant to an exemptive order from the Securities and Exchange Commission (Order) and is not required to publicly disclose its complete portfolio holdings each business day. The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in securities of companies principally engaged in the real estate industry and other real estate related investments. It invests in domestic and foreign issuers. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: FPRO provides exposure to companies that engage in the real estate industry and other related investments. The fund selects securities perceived to have above-average income and long-term capital growth, using fundamental analyses of factors such as each companys financial condition and industry position, as well as market and economic conditions. As an actively managed fund, FPRO is not required to publicly disclose its complete portfolio holdings each business day, but instead publishes its Tracking Basket and Tracking Basket Weight Overlap daily, which are designed to closely track the daily performance of the fund without disclosing the actual portfolio and how similar they are in percentage terms. The fund only discloses its complete holdings monthly with a 30-day lag.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks above-average income and long-term capital growth, consistent with reasonable investment risk. The fund is an actively managed ETF that operates pursuant to an exemptive order from the Securities and Exchange Commission (Order) and is not required to publicly disclose its complete portfolio holdings each business day. The fund normally invests at least 80% of assets in securities of companies principally engaged in the real estate industry and other real estate related investments. It invests in domestic and foreign issuers. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This actively managed ETF seeks above-average income and long-term capital growth by investing at least 80% of its assets in companies and investments related to the real estate industry, including both domestic and foreign issuers. It is non-diversified and selects securities using fundamental analysis of factors like financial condition, industry position, and market conditions. Operating under an SEC exemptive order, the fund is not required to publicly disclose its complete portfolio holdings daily; instead, it publishes a daily Tracking Basket and Weight Overlap, disclosing complete holdings monthly with a 30-day lag.

name: Global X Funds - Global X PropTech ETF
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets, plus borrowings for investments purposes (if any), in the securities of the Global X PropTech Index, which may include common stocks, American Depositary Receipts ("ADRs") and Global Depositary Receipts ("GDRs") based on the securities in the underlying index. The underlying index is owned and was developed by Global X Management Company LLC, an affiliate of the fund and the fund's investment adviser. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
PTEC tracks an index comprised of 50 global property technology companies, PropTechs, benefiting from innovations relating to residential and commercial real estate efficiency. Selection and weighting are based on market capitalization.

PTEC tracks a narrow portfolio of global PropTechs or real estate-based companies. PropTech firms make at least 50% of their revenue (pure-play) from technological optimization toward real estate operation, management, and development. These include research and analytics, online marketplace and platforms, and property management. The selection process begins with FactSet, which identifies PropTech companies. After which, securities are filtered with typical screens such as daily turnover, minimum market capitalization, available public shares, and country listing. To build the portfolio, the top 50 pure-play stocks are selected and weighted based on their market capitalization. The fund may lend a third of its assets. The index rebalances and reconstitutes semi-annually, made on the last day of February and August.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the Global X PropTech Index. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets, plus borrowings for investments purposes (if any), in the securities of the Global X PropTech Index, which may include common stocks, American Depositary Receipts ("ADRs") and Global Depositary Receipts ("GDRs") based on the securities in the underlying index. The underlying index is owned and was developed by Global X Management Company LLC, an affiliate of the fund and the fund's investment adviser. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This ETF tracks an index designed to provide investment results that correspond generally to the performance of global property technology (PropTech) companies. It focuses on firms benefiting from technological innovations relating to residential and commercial real estate efficiency, specifically those deriving at least 50% of their revenue from technological optimization in real estate operation, management, or development. The underlying index is comprised of 50 such global companies, selected based on criteria including revenue source and size, and weighted by market capitalization. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets, plus borrowings, in the securities of this underlying index, which may include common stocks, ADRs, and GDRs. The index is rebalanced and reconstituted semi-annually. The fund is non-diversified.

name: Virtus LifeSci Biotech Clinical Trials ETF
description_original: Under normal market conditions, the fund will invest not less than 80% of its assets in component securities of the index. The index seeks to track the performance of the common stock of U.S. exchange-listed biotechnology companies with a primary product offering ("lead drug") that is typically in a Phase 1, Phase 2 or Phase 3 clinical trial stage of development, but prior to receiving marketing approval.
description_eftcom: BBC focuses on biotech companies with lead drugs that are still in various phases of clinical trials and not yet approved marketing. Given the low historical success rates in clinical trials, the fund is a high-risk and high-reward bet on a small subset of biotech companies. It excludes companies with a lead drug candidate thats still in preclinical testing or research stage, prior to entering into human clinical trials. Also excluded are the following 12 distinct sub-industries: Animal Health, Diversified Healthcare, Investment Management, Healthcare Services, Non-Healthcare, Large Pharmaceuticals, Specialty Pharmaceuticals, Medical Devices, Vaccines, Nutraceuticals, OTC Healthcare, or Tools. As such, investors looking for broad biotech exposure, won't find it in BBC. The Index Committee utilizes various public data sources to select portfolio holdings, including, SEC filings, public documents from the U.S. FDA, company press releases and official corporate websites.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond, before fees and expenses, to the price and yield performance of the LifeSci Biotechnology Clinical Trials Index. Under normal market conditions, the fund will invest not less than 80% of its assets in component securities of the index. The index seeks to track the performance of the common stock of U.S. exchange-listed biotechnology companies with a primary product offering ("lead drug") that is typically in a Phase 1, Phase 2 or Phase 3 clinical trial stage of development, but prior to receiving marketing approval.
merged_description: This fund aims to mirror the performance of an index comprising US exchange-listed biotechnology companies. Its core focus is on firms whose primary product, or "lead drug," is actively progressing through Phase 1, Phase 2, or Phase 3 clinical trials but has not yet received marketing approval. The fund typically allocates at least 80% of its assets to these securities. Companies in preclinical or research stages, as well as those in twelve specific related sub-industries like large pharmaceuticals or medical devices, are specifically excluded, narrowing the scope significantly. Consequently, the fund offers a high-risk, high-reward opportunity targeting a specific, unapproved clinical stage of biotech development, rather than providing broad sector exposure.

name: SPDR NYSE Technology ETF
description_original: The SPDR NYSE Technology ETF seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the NYSE Technology Index (the “Index”).The NYSE Technology Index is composed of 35 leading US-listed technology-related companies. The Index is equal-weighted at its annual rebalance. The index comprises stocks in the Information Technology sector and technology-related stocks in the Consumer Discretionary sector.
description_eftcom:
XNTK tracks an equal-weighted index of 35 US-listed technology-related stocks.

XNTK has a broader take on the technology space by extending its exposure to tech-related firms in the consumer discretionary sector. The fund follows a proprietary selection schemewhich comes with market-cap, liquidity, revenue- and sales-based screenersand then equal-weights its holdings. The result is a concentrated portfolio of 35 large- and midcap tech and tech-related firms. XNTK tilts smaller, since its equal-weighting scheme reduces the influence of industry giants. The fund is not the right ETF for frequent traders but may suffice for longer-term investors. The index is reviewed and rebalanced annually. Note: Prior to Sept. 11, 2017, the fund was known as the SPDR Morgan Stanley Technology ETF, traded under the ticker MTK and tracked the Morgan Stanley Technology Index. The change in index provide no material change to exposure.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the NYSE Technology Index that tracks the performance of publicly traded technology companies. The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index. It may invest in equity securities that are not included in the index, cash and cash equivalents or money market instruments, such as repurchase agreements and money market funds. The index is composed of 35 leading U.S.-listed technology-related companies.
merged_description: The ETF seeks to provide investment results that correspond generally to the total return performance of the NYSE Technology Index before fees. This index tracks publicly traded technology companies and is composed of 35 leading US-listed technology-related firms. The ETF's concept offers a broader view of the technology sector by including companies from the Information Technology sector alongside tech-related firms within the Consumer Discretionary sector. The index components are selected via a proprietary scheme using various screeners, and the portfolio holdings are equal-weighted and rebalanced annually. This equal-weighting strategy results in a concentrated portfolio of large- and mid-cap technology and tech-related companies, intentionally tilting the exposure smaller by mitigating the impact of industry giants. The fund generally invests substantially all, at least 80%, of its assets in the index securities, while also retaining flexibility to hold non-index equity or cash equivalents.

name: QRAFT AI-Enhanced U.S. Large Cap Momentum ETF
description_original: The fund is an actively-managed ETF that seeks to achieve its investment objective by utilizing an investment strategy enhanced by the use of artificial intelligence. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amounts of any borrowings for investment purposes, in securities of U.S.-listed large capitalization companies. The Adviser consults a database generated by Qraft's AI Quantitative Investment System, which automatically evaluates and filters data according to parameters supporting a particular investment thesis. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
AMOM is an actively-managed portfolio of U.S. Large Cap equities chosen with the aid of artificial intelligence.

Actively-managed AMOM uses a proprietary artificial intelligence (AI) security selection process that extracts patterns from analyzing data. The AI system finds a period within those 3 to 36 months that resulted in the best performance of stocks in the past and ranks those stocks by their residual returns, which are defined as its total return after removal of market, size and value risks factored into portfolio construction under conventional portfolio management. AMOM uses this metric on the stock management theory which states that stocks with higher residual returns have the potential to perform better and more consistently over time than conventional momentum stocks. The fund limits the weighting of a single security to 10% and no more than 40% of the funds assets may be invested in securities with more than 5% weighting in the portfolio.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks capital appreciation. The fund is an actively-managed ETF that seeks to achieve its investment objective by utilizing an investment strategy enhanced by the use of artificial intelligence. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amounts of any borrowings for investment purposes, in securities of U.S.-listed large capitalization companies. The Adviser consults a database generated by Qraft's AI Quantitative Investment System, which automatically evaluates and filters data according to parameters supporting a particular investment thesis. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This actively-managed ETF aims for capital appreciation by utilizing an investment strategy significantly enhanced by artificial intelligence. It primarily focuses on U.S.-listed large capitalization companies, investing at least 80% of its assets in such securities. The AI system analyzes data to select holdings, identifying potential outperformers based on metrics like residual returns, which differ from conventional momentum approaches by accounting for market, size, and value factors. The fund is non-diversified.

name: iShares Emerging Markets Dividend ETF
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the index. The index measures the performance of 100 leading dividend-paying emerging-market companies, selected by dividend yield subject to screening and buffering criteria.
description_eftcom:
DVYE tracks a dividend-weighted index of high-dividend-paying emerging markets companies.

DVYE has a somewhat narrow focus, holding 100 of the highest-yielding stocks from emerging markets. Selecting and weighting constituents are primarily based on dividend yield, subject to screening and buffering criteria. It delivers some extra yield, but in terms of total return, the case for DVYE is somewhat less clear. The universe begins with the S&P Emerging BMI, excluding real estate investment trusts. Stocks are then screened largely for dividend yield along with other fundamental factors. Stocks are weighted based on indicated annual dividend, with no single country going above 25%. The index is reconstituted annually, subject to quarterly reviews.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the Dow Jones Emerging Markets Select Dividend Index composed of relatively high dividend paying equities in emerging markets. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the index. The index measures the performance of 100 leading dividend-paying emerging market companies, selected according to indicated annual dividend yield, subject to screening and buffering criteria and weighting constraints.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to track the performance of an index focused on high-dividend-paying companies in emerging markets. The index is composed of 100 leading stocks, selected primarily based on their indicated annual dividend yield from a broad emerging markets universe, excluding REITs, and subject to screening and buffering criteria and other fundamental factors. These constituents are weighted according to their indicated annual dividend, incorporating constraints such as a country cap. The fund typically invests at least 80% of its assets in the index's components or investments with substantially identical economic characteristics. With its index reviewed regularly, the strategy is designed to emphasize generating yield from dividend-focused equities within emerging markets.

name: LifeGoal Home Down Payment Investment ETF
description_original: The fund is designed to assist investors in saving for a home down payment. Under normal market conditions, the fund will invest its assets within the following ranges: 60-95% of its assets in fixed income and cash and cash equivalents, 5-35% of its assets in equities, and 0-35% of its assets in a combination of underlying funds providing exposure to commodities, REITs and high yield debt securities. The adviser seeks to emphasize exposure to fixed income, in order to avoid excessive volatility of returns.
description_eftcom: The fund is being delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is June 12, 2023. HOM aims to attract investors interested in housing. Note the fund does not target a specific investment time horizon, which is important when considering investing in a home, obtaining a mortgage or renting. The fund seeks to generate current income and capital appreciation by allocating 60-95% of its assets to fixed income, 5-35% to equities, and 0-20% to commodities, REITs and high yield bonds. The fund may tilt 5-15% of the portfolio to housing related industries such as home furnishings, home builders, lumber and precious metals. The funds advisor uses their own proprietary research to select and allocate, with very few limitations, to mutual funds and ETFs to provide such exposure. Fixed income securities may be from issuers both domestic and international, public and private, including convertibles and inflation-linked, and of any maturity. Equity exposure as well may be US or international including developed and emerging markets, and of any market capitalization.
merged_description: This fund is designed to assist investors interested in saving for a home down payment or those with a general interest in housing. Its strategy primarily focuses on fixed income and cash, allocating 60-95% of assets to manage volatility and generate income. The portfolio also includes exposure to equities (5-35%) and alternatives (0-20%), such as commodities, REITs, and high yield bonds, with potential tilts towards housing-related industries like home builders and furnishings. The fund may invest in various domestic and international securities, including underlying funds selected via proprietary research, and does not target a specific investment time horizon. Please be aware that this fund is being delisted, with its last day of trading scheduled for June 12, 2023.

name: Invesco DWA Consumer Staples Momentum ETF
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of at least 30 securities of companies in the consumer staples sector that have powerful relative strength or "momentum" characteristics.
description_eftcom: PSL provides an alternate take on US consumer staples firms. It starts its selection universe covering about 2,000 of the largest companies by market cap within the NASDAQ US Benchmark Index. The fund then follows the Dorsey-Wright Technical Leaders Indexs momentum-focused scoring scheme to narrow down its constituents to a minimum of 30. At the same time, this momentum score will also be the basis of their respective weightings. Meaning, securities that scored the highest receives greater weight in the index. This relative strength strategy aims to focus on securities performance when it comes to intermediate and long-term upward price movements as compared to a market benchmark. Index rebalancing and reconstitution occurs quarterly. Prior to August 28, 2023, the ETF's name was Invesco DWA Consumer Staples Momentum ETF.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the Dorsey Wright® Consumer Staples Technical Leaders Index (the "underlying index"). The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of at least 30 securities of companies in the consumer staples sector that have powerful relative strength or "momentum" characteristics.
merged_description: This fund offers exposure to US consumer staples companies selected based on their relative strength or "momentum" characteristics. It seeks to track an index that identifies a minimum of 30 securities exhibiting powerful upward price movements compared to a market benchmark. The index draws from a universe of large US companies, using a momentum-focused scoring scheme to select and weight constituents, with securities showing stronger momentum receiving higher allocations. The fund generally invests at least 90% of its assets in the securities of this underlying index, which undergoes quarterly rebalancing and reconstitution.
