This security is scheduled for delisting, with its last day of trading on an exchange being April 28, 2025.

name: FlexShares Real Assets Allocation Index Fund
description_original: Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets (exclusive of collateral held from securities lending) in the securities of the underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of an optimized allocation to the underlying funds that is intended to provide exposures to certain real assets and minimize overall volatility of investment in the underlying funds.
description_eftcom:
ASET is a fund-of-funds that gives investors diversified global exposure to real assets.

ASET is designed to serve as a core real asset allocation by investing in three of FlexShares ETFs: FlexShares Morningstar Global Upstream Natural Resources Index Fund (GUNR), FlexShares STOXX Global Broad Infrastructure Index Fund (NFRA) and FlexShares Global Quality Real Estate Index Fund (GQRE). The portfolio managers use a proprietary optimization methodology to allocate between these three funds with the goal of minimizing overall return volatility. This fund is meant as an all-in-one product addressing investors need for both inflation-hedging and income. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced at least annually.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield performance, before fees and expenses, of the Northern Trust Real Assets Allocation IndexSM. Under normal circumstances, the fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets (exclusive of collateral held from securities lending) in the securities of the underlying index. The underlying index measures the performance of an optimized allocation to the underlying funds that is intended to provide exposures to certain real assets and minimize overall volatility of investment in the underlying funds.
merged_description: This investment product functions as a fund-of-funds, offering diversified global exposure to real assets. It is designed as a core real asset allocation strategy, primarily investing (at least 80% of assets under normal circumstances) in underlying funds that focus on sectors such as natural resources, infrastructure, and real estate. The allocation among these underlying investments is optimized, often guided by a proprietary methodology or an underlying index, with the specific goal of minimizing overall portfolio volatility. This structure aims to provide investors with a single, comprehensive solution for accessing real assets, potentially serving objectives like inflation hedging and income generation.

name: iShares Factors US Growth Style ETF
description_original: The underlying index is designed to select equity securities from the Russell 1000® Growth Index, which in turn is a subset of the Russell 1000® Index. It generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its underlying index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: GARP focuses on large- and mid-cap US growth stocks that exhibit value and quality traits, or growth at a reasonable price. The selection process begins with the MSCI USA Index, where each stock is assigned a growth score based on five criteria: long-term and short-term forward EPS growth rates, historical EPS and sales per share growth trends, and current internal growth rate. Stocks with higher growth scores are selected until they represent approximately 50% of the parent index. Each stock receives a tilt score, which considers value (P/B, forward P/E, and EV/CFO) and quality (ROE, D/E, and earnings variability) metrics relative to its sector. The portfolio is then tilted toward securities that score favorably on both metrics, with weights adjusted for portfolio diversification. Index rebalancing is done quarterly. Before June 3, 2024, the fund was named iShares Factors US Growth Style ETF under the ticker STLG and tracked the Russell US Large Cap Factors Growth Style Index.
merged_description: This ETF applies a Growth at a Reasonable Price (GARP) strategy to US large- and mid-cap equities, drawing its selection universe from the Russell 1000 Growth Index. The approach involves scoring stocks based on various growth metrics, then tilting the portfolio towards securities that also demonstrate favorable characteristics in value (using metrics such as price-to-book and forward price-to-earnings) and quality (like return on equity and debt-to-equity), assessed relative to their sectors. The portfolio is weighted towards stocks scoring well across these growth, value, and quality factors, and the underlying index is rebalanced quarterly. The fund is non-diversified and generally invests at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index or investments with substantially identical economic characteristics.

name: Cabana Target Leading Sector Conservative ETF
description_original: The manager seeks to achieve the fund's investment objective primarily by allocating its assets among ETFs that invest in securities of companies in the various sectors of the U.S. market. It operates in a manner that is commonly referred to as a "fund of funds," meaning that it primarily invests in other ETFs. The ETFs may invest in any of the five major asset classes - equities, fixed income, real estate, currencies, and commodities. It may invest directly in securities and other instruments to obtain the desired exposure to a specific sector. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
CLSC is an actively managed fund-of-funds which aims to provide long-term growth. The fund uses a proprietary algo to identify attractive sectors at any given time in the business cycle.

The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is January 05, 2024.CLSC is an actively-managed fund-of-funds that shifts its allocation based on the economic conditions and market outlook for variety of asset classes: equities, fixed income, real estate, currencies and commodities. Equities will include both domestic and foreign companies, including emerging markets. Fixed Income securities have no restrictions in terms of maturity, quality or duration. The Sub-Adviser utilizes a proprietary algorithm that combines fundamental economic and technical price data to identify assets that appear to be attractive based on the current business cycle. The fund claims a conservative investment style, it optimizes the portfolio to target minimum volatility in bearish markets and allocates to leading sectors that are believed to outperform during bullish markets. The Sub-Advisor has full discretion to override the algo if a perceived breakdown or systemic change has occurred.
merged_description: This actively managed fund-of-funds, which has been delisted with its final trading day on January 5, 2024, aimed for long-term growth by primarily allocating assets among other ETFs. Its strategy dynamically adjusted exposure across a range of asset classes including equities (both domestic and foreign, including emerging markets), fixed income (without restrictions on maturity, quality, or duration), real estate, currencies, and commodities. This dynamic strategy was informed by a proprietary algorithm analyzing fundamental economic and technical price data to identify attractive sectors based on the business cycle, with discretion for the sub-adviser to override. The fund sought a conservative approach, targeting minimum volatility in bearish markets while allocating to leading sectors in bullish markets. It was non-diversified and could also invest directly in securities or instruments for specific sector exposure.

name: Direxion Daily Aerospace & Defense Bull 3X Shares
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowing for investment purposes) in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, and securities of the index, ETFs that track the index and other financial instruments that provide daily leveraged exposure to the index or ETFs that track the index. The index attempts to measure the performance of the aerospace and defense industry of the U.S. equity market. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: DFEN is a daily 3x leveraged bet on the Dow Jones U.S. Select Aerospace and Defense Index, a market-cap-weighted index of US-listed aerospace and defense stocks. Unleveraged exposure to the same index can be found in ITA a fund from BlackRock. The geared 3x nature of DFEN is designed to magnify the daily performance of the index, not to return 300% of the index performance over extended periods of time. Due to compounding and the daily reset function, the fund is meant to be a trading vehicle for investors to make short-term bets on the direction of the aerospace and defense industry and not a long-term investment strategy. Compounding becomes more pronounced and more of a concern as holding periods increase, and the fund is likely to stray from the returns of the underlying index in such cases. Due to the fund`s day trading personality, trading volume and bid/ask spread are more important cost considerations than expense ratio.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks daily investment results, before fees and expenses, of 300% of the daily performance of the Dow Jones U.S. Select Aerospace & Defense Index. The fund invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus borrowing for investment purposes) in financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and exchange-traded funds ("ETFs") that track the index, that, in combination, provide 3X daily leveraged exposure to the index, consistent with the fund's investment objective. The index attempts to measure the performance of the aerospace and defense industry of the U.S. equity market. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: Seeking to provide daily investment results that are 300% of the daily performance of the Dow Jones U.S. Select Aerospace & Defense Index, which measures the U.S. aerospace and defense industry, this ETF is designed as a daily leveraged trading vehicle. It achieves its 3X daily exposure by investing at least 80% of its assets (plus borrowing) in a combination of financial instruments, such as swap agreements, securities of the index, and ETFs that track the index. Due to the effects of compounding and the daily reset feature, the fund is not intended for long-term investors, as its performance over periods longer than one day is unlikely to be three times that of the index and can significantly deviate. The fund is non-diversified.

name: ProShares Supply Chain Logistics ETF
description_original: The fund invests in securities that ProShare Advisors believes should track the performance of the index. The index provider then selects into the index the 40 largest companies, by market capitalization, that generate 75% or more of their revenue from products or services produced or provided by one or more of the applicable RBICS Sub-Industries. The fund will invest at least 80% of its net assets in the securities that comprise the index. It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: SUPL tracks an index of companies primarily involved in the logistics of moving raw materials, intermediate goods, and finished products around the globe. Eligible companies must be included in at least one of 17 RBICS Sub-Industries related to the supply chain logistics industry, which encompasses logistics support and software, rail and air freight, trucking, and sea shipping. The index selects the 40 largest companies that generate at least 75% of their revenue from the related industry. If less than 25 companies are selected, the revenue threshold is decreased to 50% and companies with the highest percentage revenue related to the industry are added until the portfolio reaches 25 constituents. Weightings are based on market-cap, with a limit of 4.5% per issuer. The index will principally invest in common shares, ADRs and GDRs listed for trading on a stock exchange globally. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced semi-annually in June and December.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks results, before fees and expenses, that track the performance of the FactSet Supply Chain Logistics Index (the “Index”). The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should track the performance of the index. The index is designed to measure the performance of companies focused on raw materials and merchandise shipping and delivery. Under normal circumstances, it will invest at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. It is non-diversified.
merged_description: This ETF aims to track the performance of an index focused on companies involved in the global logistics of moving raw materials, intermediate goods, and finished products. The index identifies companies generating a significant portion of their revenue from specific supply chain logistics activities, including shipping, delivery, logistics support, software, rail/air freight, and trucking. It selects the 40 largest companies by market capitalization that meet a primary revenue threshold, potentially lowering the threshold if necessary to ensure at least 25 constituents. The portfolio is market-cap weighted with a per-issuer limit. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its assets in securities that comprise the index or have similar economic characteristics, primarily holding common shares, ADRs, and GDRs listed globally. The fund is non-diversified, and its underlying index is reconstituted and rebalanced semi-annually.

name: iShares S&P 500 Growth ETF
description_original: The index measures the performance of the large-capitalization growth sector of the U.S. equity market. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents.
description_eftcom:
IVW tracks an index of large-cap US stocks. The index selects stocks with growth characteristics from the S&P 500 Index, based on three growth factors.

IVW is one of the most established and popular growth-focused ETFs, holding firms with growth characteristics from the S&P 500 Index. S&P's style methodology selects companies based on three growth factors: sales growth, earnings growth, and momentum. IVW was one of the first growth-focused ETFs to launch. The portfolio shows only modest sector tilts compared to our large-cap-growth benchmark, with a small but persistent bias toward midcaps. VOOG and SPYG track the same index with similarly low holdings cost. Overall, the fund is inexpensive and provides balanced exposure to large-cap-growth firms.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the S&P 500 Growth IndexTM composed of large-capitalization U.S. equities that exhibit growth characteristics. The index measures the performance of the large-capitalization growth sector of the U.S. equity market. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. It is non-diversified.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to track the performance of a large-capitalization U.S. equity index focused on the growth sector of the market. Composed of stocks selected from the S&P 500 Index, the underlying index identifies companies with growth characteristics using specific factors such as sales growth, earnings growth, and momentum. The fund typically invests at least 80% of its assets in securities that make up this index or in investments with substantially identical economic characteristics, reserving up to 20% for certain futures, options, swap contracts, cash, and cash equivalents. Classified as non-diversified, this established and popular growth-focused ETF, one of the earliest launched, offers generally inexpensive and balanced exposure to large-cap growth firms, although it may exhibit modest sector tilts and a slight bias toward mid-cap stocks relative to a strict large-cap growth benchmark.

name: IQ Clean Oceans ETF
description_original: The manager employs a “passive management” — or indexing — investment approach designed to track the performance of the underlying index. The underlying index incorporates thematic selection criteria designed to provide exposure to equity securities of companies that help to protect and/or achieve a cleaner ocean through reduced pollution and increased resource efficiency. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
OCEN tracks a market-cap-weighted index of globally-listed companies that are believed to contribute in achieving a cleaner ocean through reduced pollution and increased resource efficiency.

The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is April 9, 2025. OCEN is passively managed, holding a portfolio of companies engaged in ocean-related sustainability. The portfolio aims to cast a wide net, selecting from a universe of companies involved in a circular economy, clean energy, water and waste treatment, electronic components, energy-efficient economy, seafood and alternatives, shipping and ports, and sustainable packaging. Companies not meeting globally sustainability trends, non-compliant with the UN Global Compact, or engaged in controversial activities are excluded. Eligible companies are given a score based on revenue generated from thematic exposure and impact on the environment. The top 50 to 80 companies are selected and the resulting portfolio is market-cap-weighted, with single security weights capped at 3%. The index is rebalanced quarterly. Prior to Aug. 28, 2024, the fund name was branded under IndexIQ.
merged_description: This passively managed fund tracks a market-cap-weighted index designed to provide exposure to globally-listed companies contributing to a cleaner ocean through reduced pollution and increased resource efficiency. Targeting 50 to 80 holdings, the index selects companies from sectors such as circular economy, clean energy, and water treatment based on their thematic revenue and environmental impact, while excluding those engaged in controversial activities or violating sustainability principles. Individual security weights are capped at 3%, and the index is rebalanced quarterly. Potential investors should be aware this is a non-diversified fund that is scheduled for delisting, with its last day of trading on April 9, 2025.

name: John Hancock Multifactor Consumer Staples ETF
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of its net assets (plus any borrowings for investment purposes) in securities that compose the fund's index. The index is designed to comprise securities in the consumer staples sector within the U.S. Universe whose market capitalizations are larger than that of the 1001st largest U.S. company at the time of reconstitution. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This fund is designed to track an index focusing on the U.S. consumer staples sector, specifically targeting companies with market capitalizations larger than the 1001st largest U.S. company at index reconstitution. It normally invests at least 80% of its assets in these index securities. The fund is considered non-diversified, indicating a concentrated portfolio approach.

name: Vanguard U.S. Liquidity Factor ETF
description_original: The fund invests primarily in U.S. common stocks with the potential to generate higher returns relative to the broad U.S. equity market by investing in stocks with lower measures of trading liquidity as determined by the advisor. The portfolio will include a diverse mix of companies representing many different market sectors and industry groups. Under normal circumstances, at least 80% of the fund's assets will be invested in securities issued by U.S. companies.
merged_description: This fund aims for potentially higher returns relative to the broad U.S. equity market by primarily investing in U.S. common stocks that the advisor determines have lower measures of trading liquidity. The portfolio is built with a diverse mix of companies across various market sectors and industry groups. Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its assets in securities issued by U.S. companies.

name: VanEck Digital Transformation ETF
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities of Digital Transformation Companies. The index is a global index that tracks the performance of Digital Transformation Companies. The fund will not invest in digital assets (including cryptocurrencies) (i) directly or (ii) indirectly through the use of digital asset derivatives. It also will not invest in initial coin offerings. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
DAPP tracks a market-cap-weighted index of global innovative companies that are involved in the digitalization of the worlds economy through a diverse range of digital assets.

DAPP offers pure-play exposure to companies leading the digital transformation of the economy through digital assets without geo constraints. The funds underlying index is composed of diversified companies of all capitalization defined as Digital Assets Stocks which derive at least 50% of their revenue from digital assets projects. These companies include digital asset exchanges, payment gateways, miners, equipment, technology, and service providers, digital asset infrastructure businesses, and e-commerce. Eligible securities are ranked in terms of market-cap with the top 85% qualified for inclusion. The largest 25 ranking companies are chosen as index constituents and are then weighted by market-cap with single security capping at 8%. The index is reconstituted and rebalanced quarterly
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track as closely as possible, before fees and expenses, the price and yield performance of the MVIS® Global Digital Assets Equity Index. The fund normally invests at least 80% of its total assets in securities of Digital Transformation Companies. The index is a global index that tracks the performance of Digital Transformation Companies. The fund will not invest in digital assets (including cryptocurrencies) (i) directly or (ii) indirectly through the use of digital asset derivatives. It also will not invest in initial coin offerings. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This fund seeks to track a global, market-cap-weighted index focused on companies driving the digital transformation of the economy through involvement in digital assets. It aims to provide pure-play exposure to these "Digital Transformation Companies," specifically targeting those that derive significant revenue (typically at least 50%) from digital asset projects such as exchanges, mining, infrastructure, and technology providers. The fund normally invests at least 80% of its assets in the securities of these companies, which are selected globally based on market capitalization (often focusing on top-ranking firms within the eligible universe) and weighted with an 8% cap per security, with quarterly rebalancing. Notably, the fund explicitly avoids direct or indirect investment in digital assets like cryptocurrencies or initial coin offerings (ICOs). It is considered a non-diversified fund.

name: iShares MSCI KLD 400 Social ETF
description_original: The fund generally invests at least 90% of its assets in securities of the underlying index and in depositary receipts representing securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is a free float-adjusted market capitalization index designed to provide exposure to U.S. companies that have positive environmental, social and governance ("ESG") characteristics.
description_eftcom:
DSI tracks a market cap-weighted index of 400 US companies deemed to have positive environmental, social, and governance characteristics, as determined by MSCI.

DSI is a viable choice for those wanting a socially conscious ETF while maintaining reasonably market-like exposure. The fund limits its holdings to firms deemed to be socially responsible, from an environmental, social, and governance (ESG) standpoint. In practice, this means explicitly excluding firms that are significantly involved with weapons manufacturing, vice products, nuclear energy, and genetic modification. Those firms that make the cut are then ranked by their performance according to those ESG criteria. While the fund excludes many familiar names, it avoids making huge sector bets. It overweights technology and underweights financials and industrials, but this doesn't substantially change the funds risk profile. The index is rebalanced during regular semi-annual and quarterly reviews. Prior to February 19, 2025, the fund name was iShares MSCI KLD 400 Social ETF.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the MSCI KLD 400 Social Index composed of U.S. companies that have positive environmental, social and governance characteristics. The fund generally invests at least 90% of its assets in securities of the underlying index and in depositary receipts representing securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is a free float-adjusted market capitalization index designed to provide exposure to U.S. companies that have positive environmental, social and governance ("ESG") characteristics.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to track a market cap-weighted index of approximately 400 U.S. companies identified as having positive environmental, social, and governance (ESG) characteristics. It generally invests at least 90% of its assets in the securities or depositary receipts of this underlying index. The fund targets companies based on ESG performance, notably excluding those significantly involved in weapons manufacturing, vice products, nuclear energy, or genetic modification. While it provides reasonably market-like exposure, suitable for socially conscious investors, it achieves this by selecting and ranking firms based on their ESG profile, resulting in minor sector variations without substantial risk changes.

name: ProShares Ultra Oil & Gas
description_original: The fund invests in financial instruments that ProShare Advisors believes, in combination, should produce daily returns consistent with the fund's investment objective. The index measures the performance of certain companies in the oil and gas sector of the U.S. equity market. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: DIG provides 2x leveraged exposure to the S&P Energy Select Sector Index, a market-cap-weighted index of US oil and gas companies. This is a concentrated market that especially captures industry giants. Specifically, the fund typically includes firms involved in oil and gas exploration and production, integrated oil and gas, equipment for oil as well as renewable energy, pipelines, and alternative fuel producers. As a geared product with daily resets, DIG is designed as a short-term trading tool and not a long-term investment vehicle. Long-term returns could materially differ from those of the underlying index due to daily compounding. Prior to Mar. 20, 2023, the fund was called ProShares Ultra Energy that tracked the Dow Jones U.S. Oil & Gas Index.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks daily investment results that correspond to two times (2x) the daily performance of the S&P Energy Select Sector Index. The index is designed to measure the performance of energy companies included in the S&P 500 Index. Under normal circumstances, the fund will obtain leveraged exposure to at least 80% of its total assets in components of the index or in instruments with similar economic characteristics. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This fund provides daily investment results seeking to correspond to two times (2x) the daily performance of the S&P Energy Select Sector Index. This market-cap-weighted index tracks U.S. energy companies from the S&P 500, including firms involved in oil and gas exploration and production, integrated operations, equipment, pipelines, and alternative fuels. The fund is non-diversified and captures a concentrated market of industry giants. As a geared product utilizing daily resets, it is intended strictly as a short-term trading tool, as returns over periods longer than a day can differ significantly from the index due to compounding.

name: Global X U.S. Infrastructure Development ETF
description_original: The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to measure the performance of U.S. listed companies that provide exposure to domestic infrastructure development, including companies involved in construction and engineering; production of infrastructure raw materials, composites and products; industrial transportation; and producers/distributors of heavy construction equipment.
description_eftcom:
PAVE tracks a market-cap-weighted index of US-listed companies that derive the majority of their revenue from or have a stated business purpose related to infrastructure development.

PAVE`s definition of infrastructure includes many players in the construction supply chain, such as producers of raw materials, construction equipment producers, industrial transportation, and engineering services. Unlike most other infrastructure-themed funds, PAVE focuses on domestic infrastructure, as companies must be listed in and derive more than 50% of their revenue from the US. The Index may include large-, mid-, and small-cap companies weighted by market capitalization. MLPs, REITs and BDCs are excluded. For diversification purposes, PAVE undergoes annual reconstitution and rebalance with a single security cap of 3% and a single security floor of 0.3%.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to provide investment results that correspond generally to the price and yield performance, of the Indxx U.S. Infrastructure Development Index. The fund invests at least 80% of its total assets in the securities of the underlying index. The underlying index is designed to measure the performance of U.S. listed companies that provide exposure to domestic infrastructure development, including companies involved in construction and engineering; production of infrastructure raw materials, composites and products; industrial transportation; and producers/distributors of heavy construction equipment.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to track a market-cap-weighted index focused on U.S. domestic infrastructure development, typically investing at least 80% of its assets in the securities of its underlying index. The fund targets US-listed companies that derive significant revenue from or have a stated business purpose related to infrastructure projects within the United States, encompassing sectors such as construction, engineering, production of raw materials and heavy equipment, and industrial transportation. The index structure includes large-, mid-, and small-cap companies while excluding MLPs, REITs, and BDCs, with annual rebalancing and security-level constraints applied for diversification and structure.

name: Pacer American Energy Independence ETF
description_original: A strategy-driven exchange traded fund (ETF) that aims to offer investors exposure to U.S. and Canadian companies that generate the majority of their cash flow from midstream energy infrastructure activities.
description_eftcom: USAI focuses on US and Canadian midstream energy infrastructure companies that derive the majority of their revenue from the processing, transportation and storage of oil, natural gas and refined products. Holdings are selected by market cap and separated into two fixed-weight categories based upon legal structure: US & Canadian midstream companies (80%) and US midstream MLPs (20%). Holdings within each category are weighted by market cap. Because less than 25% of USAIs holdings are taxed as partnerships, it avoids the tax issues faced by many competitors in the MLP space. The index is rebalanced on a quarterly basis.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the performance, before fees and expenses, of the American Energy Independence Index. The Advisor attempts to invest all, or substantially all, of its assets in the component securities that make up the index. The index uses a proprietary, rules-based methodology to measure the performance of a portfolio of U.S. and Canadian exchange-listed equity securities of companies that generate a majority of their cash flow from certain qualifying "midstream" energy infrastructure activities. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This exchange traded fund offers exposure to US and Canadian midstream energy infrastructure companies, focusing on firms that derive a majority of their cash flow from activities like processing, transportation, and storage of oil, natural gas, and refined products. It tracks a proprietary, rules-based index that selects holdings by market cap and structures the portfolio into two fixed-weight categories: 80% US and Canadian midstream companies and 20% US midstream MLPs, with market cap weighting applied within each. A key advantage is its structure avoids certain tax issues common to MLP investments by limiting partnership holdings to less than 25%. The fund is non-diversified and its tracking index is rebalanced quarterly.

name: Xtrackers Net Zero Pathway Paris Aligned US Equity ETF
description_original: The index is comprised of large and mid-capitalization companies in the United States that meet certain ESG criteria. The fund will normally invest at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in equity securities of issuers incorporated in the United States and as considered by the Advisor to be aligned with the Paris Agreement and consistent with the Net Zero Investment Framework. It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: USNZ offers an enhanced climate approach to the US large- and mid-cap space by tracking an index geared toward a low-carbon economy transition. The index initially screens out stocks from the Solactive GBS United States Large & Mid Cap Index (parent index), that are involved in controversial business activities. In addition, firms that fail to observe established norms with respect to environment, human rights, corruption, and labor rights, as well as companies with an ISS ESG Corporate Rating of D- and a negative impact on UN Sustainable Development Goals are also removed. Holdings are initially weighted by market-cap. Weights are then tilted based on: a) greenhouse gas emissions reduction targets, b) climate disclosure standards, and c) green revenue. Lastly, the portfolio is optimized to reduce carbon intensity by 50% with a target reduction of 7% year-over-year, and increased exposure to high climate impact sectors relative to its parent index. The index rebalances semi-annually.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance, before fees and expenses, of the Solactive ISS ESG United States Net Zero Pathway Enhanced Index. The index is comprised of large and mid-capitalization companies in the United States that meet certain ESG criteria. The fund will normally invest at least 80% of its net assets, plus the amount of any borrowings for investment purposes, in equity securities of issuers incorporated in the United States and as considered by the Advisor to be aligned with the Paris Agreement and consistent with the Net Zero Investment Framework. It is non-diversified.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to track the performance of an index designed to provide exposure to US large and mid-capitalization companies aligned with the Net Zero Investment Framework and the Paris Agreement, emphasizing a transition to a low-carbon economy. The underlying index screens companies for involvement in controversial activities, adherence to established environmental, social, and governance norms (including human rights, corruption, and labor), low ESG ratings, and negative UN Sustainable Development Goal impact. After initial market-cap weighting, constituents' weights are tilted based on climate criteria including greenhouse gas emission targets, climate disclosure standards, and green revenue. The index is optimized to significantly reduce carbon intensity compared to a broad market benchmark, targeting substantial initial and ongoing annual reductions, while potentially increasing exposure to high climate impact sectors. Typically investing at least 80% of its assets in US equity securities meeting these requirements, the fund follows an index that rebalances semi-annually. It is considered non-diversified.

name: WisdomTree U.S. Dividend ex-Financials Fund
description_original: The fund normally invests at least 95% of its total assets will be invested in component securities of the index and investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the economic characteristics of such component securities. The index is comprised of the 10 highest dividend-yielding companies in each sector, selected from the 300 largest companies by market value in the WisdomTree U.S. Dividend Index outside the financials sector. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
AIVL is an actively managed fund that provides exposure to US value stocks from developed markets.

AIVL invests in US value stocks by employing a proprietary, quantitative AI model that analyzes various inputs, including company fundamentals and market sentiment, to select 60-190 stocks that exhibit value characteristics. The AI model weights stocks based on their overall model scores, capped at 6% per individual security. The sub-adviser generally buys and sells stocks monthly based on the AI models updated recommendations. As an actively managed fund, the portfolio managers can analyze market and financial data to make buy, sell, and hold decisions at their discretion. Prior to Jan. 18, 2022, the fund was called WisdomTree U.S. Dividend ex-Financials Fund, which traded under the ticker DTN, and tracked the WisdomTree U.S. Dividend ex-Financials Index.
merged_description: This actively managed fund seeks exposure to US value stocks. It employs a proprietary quantitative AI model to analyze company fundamentals and market sentiment, selecting 60 to 190 holdings that demonstrate value characteristics. These stocks are weighted based on their AI model scores, with individual positions capped at 6%. The portfolio is generally rebalanced monthly according to updated AI recommendations, though portfolio managers also have discretionary authority.

name: LeaderShares Activist Leaders ETF
description_original: The fund will be invested in equity securities of companies listed on a U.S. exchange with market capitalizations of at least $1 billion at the time of initial purchase. It may focus its investments in a particular sector, industry or group of industries. The fund may utilize derivatives, such as equity options and total return swap agreements, to seek to achieve its objective and for hedging purposes.
description_eftcom:
ACTV actively selects US equity securities that are the target of shareholder activism.

ACTV aims to generate long-term capital growth by focusing on all-cap equity securities of companies whose shares have been acquired by individuals identified as Activist Leaders. The SEC requires anyone acquiring more than 5% of a companys shares, with activist intent, to file a Schedule 13D. The funds adviser applies a quantitative methodology to the 13D filings to identify and rate Activist Leaders based upon their effectiveness of achieving the stated objective and creation of positive returns in such positions. Once the Activist Leaders are selected, the funds adviser adds and removes constituents to the portfolio by following these investors activities through the 13D filings. The list of Activist Leaders will change over time. With this, ACTVs investors should anticipate frequent trading resulting in high portfolio turnover. In addition, the fund can become concentrated in a particular sector, industry or group.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to generate long-term capital growth. The fund will be invested in equity securities of companies listed on a U.S. exchange with market capitalizations of at least $1 billion at the time of initial purchase. It may focus its investments in a particular sector, industry or group of industries.
merged_description: This fund aims to generate long-term capital growth by actively investing in US-listed equity securities of companies with a market capitalization of at least $1 billion at the time of purchase. Its core strategy focuses on companies targeted by shareholder activism, specifically those whose shares have been acquired by identified "Activist Leaders." The fund employs a quantitative methodology to analyze SEC Schedule 13D filings (used by investors with >5% ownership with activist intent) to identify and rate these leaders based on their track record of achieving stated objectives and creating positive returns. The portfolio is constructed and adjusted by following the activities of these chosen Activist Leaders through subsequent filings, which is anticipated to result in frequent trading and high portfolio turnover. The fund may become concentrated in particular sectors, industries, or groups, and may utilize derivatives, such as equity options and total return swaps, to pursue its investment objective and for hedging.

name: Merk Stagflation ETF
description_original: The index is a rules-based index that allocates its exposure to the four funds, each of which represents a stagflation-sensitive asset class. The fund will generally use a “replication” strategy to achieve its investment objective, meaning it generally will invest in all of the components of the index in approximately the same proportions as in the index. It also may invest in securities or other investments not included in the index, but which the Adviser believes will help the fund track the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is December 26, 2023. STGF introduces stagflation-sensitive investing, which aims to protect against persistent inflation during a period of weak economic growth. This multi-asset fund allocates among four ETFs: 1) Schwab US TIPS ETF (SCHP), 2) Vanguard Real Estate ETF (VNQ), 3) VanEck Merk Gold Trust (OUNZ), and 4) Invesco DB Oil Fund (DBO). Constituent weights are adjusted based on a trend-following methodology. Positive or negative price trends in gold, oil, and real estate will either increase or decrease respective index weights, resulting in 5% to 15% of the total asset allocation. The remaining 55% to 85% of the portfolio will be allocated to US TIPS. The fund expects to gain exposure to commodities by investing up to 25% of its net assets, in a wholly-owned subsidiary organized under the laws of the Cayman Islands. The index is rebalanced whenever a change in price trend in gold, oil or real estate is detected or any of these asset classes has exceeded its minimum or maximum allocations.
merged_description: Designed for stagflation-sensitive investing to mitigate the impact of persistent inflation during periods of weak economic growth, this multi-asset strategy tracked a rules-based index. It achieved its objective by replicating exposure to four key asset classes: US TIPS, Real Estate, Gold, and Oil. The fund employed a trend-following methodology to dynamically allocate between 5% and 15% to Real Estate, Gold, and Oil individually, based on their price trends. The dominant portion of the portfolio, ranging from 55% to 85%, was consistently allocated to US TIPS. Exposure to commodities like Gold and Oil was facilitated through a wholly-owned subsidiary organized under the laws of the Cayman Islands, potentially representing up to 25% of net assets. The index, which the fund generally replicated, was rebalanced when price trend changes were detected in gold, oil, or real estate, or when any asset class breached its minimum or maximum allocation limits. Classified as non-diversified, the fund's allocation strategy was driven entirely by the rules of its underlying index.

name: SPDR S&P Global Natural Resources ETF
description_original: The SPDR S&P Global Natural Resources ETF seeks to provide investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the S&P Global Natural Resources Index (the “Index”)Seeks to provide exposure to a number of the largest market cap securities in three natural resources sectors - agriculture, energy, and metals and miningMaximum weight of each sub-index is capped at one-third of the total weight of the Index
description_eftcom:
GNR tracks an index of global companies in natural resources and/or commodity businesses.

GNR offers exposure to global natural resources companies including those engaged in commodities businesses. The fund equally-weights S&P's three natural resources subindexes to evenly split weight between the metals & mining, agriculture, and energy sectors. Eligible securities will be ranked according to market cap and the top 30 companies from each subindex will be included for a total of 90 index constituents. These stocks must be listed on a developed market exchange. Selected securities will then be weighted by market-cap within each buckets, subject to constraints such that US stocks are capped at 40% and emerging market stocks are capped at 15%. In addition, no individual security must have a weight greater than 5%. The index rebalancing occurs annually.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks investment results that, before fees and expenses, correspond generally to the total return performance of the S&P Global Natural Resources Index. The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 80%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index and in depositary receipts based on securities comprising the index. The index is comprised of 90 of the largest U.S. and foreign publicly-traded companies, based on market capitalization, in natural resources and commodities businesses that meet certain investability requirements.
merged_description: This fund seeks to track the performance of an index representing global companies involved in the natural resources and commodities businesses. The index is composed of 90 of the largest publicly-traded companies, selected from the agriculture, energy, and metals and mining sectors based on market capitalization. The index structure gives equal weighting to each of these three main sectors, with each sector's total weight capped at one-third, while companies within each sector are weighted by market capitalization. The index includes both U.S. and foreign companies, subject to investability requirements and various constraints, such as a 40% cap on U.S. stocks, a 15% cap on emerging market stocks, and a 5% cap on any single security. The fund typically invests at least 80% of its assets in the securities that comprise the index or related depositary receipts.

name: Invesco KBW Property & Casualty Insurance ETF
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is a modified-market capitalization-weighted index designed to track the performance of companies primarily engaged in U.S. property and casualty insurance activities, as determined by the index provider. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
KBWP tracks a modified market-cap-weighted index focused exclusively on property & casualty insurance companies in the US.

KBWP doesn't attempt to provide broad-market exposure to the US Insurance sector. Instead, the fund focuses specifically on property & casualty insurance firms. Its holdings also have a significant position in reinsurance companies. To curate the portfolio, an index committee determines the fund constituents and a modified market-cap weighting is put into use. Notably, the portfolio underweights mega-cap insurance brokers, life & health insurance firms and other huge conglomerates, tilting the portfolio small. The index is rebalanced and reconstituted on a quarterly basis.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the KBW Nasdaq Property & Casualty IndexTM (the "underlying index"). The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is a modified-market capitalization-weighted index designed to track the performance of companies primarily engaged in U.S. property and casualty insurance activities, as determined by the index provider. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to track an index focusing exclusively on U.S. property and casualty insurance companies. The underlying index uses a modified market-capitalization weighting, specifically designed to exclude broad insurance sector exposure, underweight mega-cap brokers, and life/health insurers, resulting in a portfolio tilted towards smaller companies within the P&C sector. Holdings also feature a significant position in reinsurance companies. The fund generally invests at least 90% of its assets in the securities of this index, which is non-diversified. Index constituents are determined by a committee, and the index is rebalanced quarterly.

name: Hartford Sustainable Income ETF
description_original: The fund invests primarily in domestic and foreign debt securities that the sub-adviser, Wellington Management Company LLP (“Wellington Management”), considers to be attractive from a yield perspective while considering total return and also incorporating a sustainability framework. The fund normally invests in non-investment grade debt securities and highly rated securities. The fund will normally invest at least 80% of its assets in securities of issuers that Wellington Management determines meet its sustainable investing criteria.
description_eftcom:
HSUN is an actively managed ETF that provides broad exposure to debt securities from around the world, including emerging markets.

HSUN invests in debt securities deemed attractive from a yield perspective while considering total return. The fund invests in junk bonds and highly rated debt securities, stretching across multiple sectors from anywhere in the world, including emerging markets. The portfolio may include corporate and government bonds, bank loans, or loan participation interests in secured, second lien or unsecured variable, fixed or floating rate loans, and securitized debt (e.g., mortgage-related and asset-backed securities, including CLOs). The fund may use derivatives to manage portfolio risk. As an actively managed fund, HSUN can analyze market and financial data to make buy, sell, and hold decisions at their discretion. Prior to Sep. 30, 2024, the fund was called Hartford Sustainable Income ETF.
merged_description: This is an actively managed ETF that seeks broad exposure to debt securities from around the world, including emerging markets. Its investment strategy focuses on debt considered attractive from a yield perspective while also seeking total return. A core aspect is the integration of a sustainability framework, with the fund normally investing at least 80% of its assets in securities of issuers meeting the sub-adviser's sustainable investing criteria. The portfolio can include a wide range of debt types, spanning both highly rated and non-investment grade securities (such as junk bonds), including corporate and government bonds, bank loans, loan participation interests, and various forms of securitized debt. Derivatives may be used to manage portfolio risk.

name: Xtrackers MSCI USA Climate Action Equity ETF
description_original: The fund, using a “passive” or indexing investment approach, seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance, before fees and expenses, of the underlying index, which is comprised of large and mid-capitalization companies in the United States that the underlying index’s methodology assesses as leading their sector peers in taking action relating to a climate transition. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in component securities of the index. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: USCA provides a climate-friendly approach to investing in the US large- and mid-cap space. The fund tracks an index screened toward stocks considered leaders in taking actions relating to climate transition. The fund drafts its selection universe from the MSCI USA Index, removing those involved in controversial business activities. The fund also screens out firms that are non-compliant with norms on the environment, human rights, governance, and carbon reduction goals approved by the United Nations Global Compact, and other SBTi. A screen for companies with bleak climate risk management removes the bottom quarter from each sector. The remaining stocks undergo a security-level assessment based on: (i) science-based target initiative, (ii) greenhouse gas intensity, (iii) emission track record, and (iv) green business revenue. Based on the assessment, the top 50% within each sector are selected. The index is market cap-weighted and rebalances on a semi-annual basis.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance, before fees and expenses, of the MSCI USA Climate Action Index. The fund, using a “passive” or indexing investment approach, seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance, before fees and expenses, of the underlying index, which is comprised of large and mid-capitalization companies in the United States that the underlying index’s methodology assesses as leading their sector peers in taking action relating to a climate transition. The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in component securities of the index. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This passive ETF aims to track the performance of an index comprised of large and mid-capitalization US companies identified as leaders within their respective sectors in taking action relating to a climate transition. The index methodology involves initial screens to remove companies engaged in controversial business activities or non-compliant with key environmental and governance norms, followed by a security-level assessment based on criteria like science-based targets, greenhouse gas intensity, and green business revenue to select top performers from each sector. The fund will invest at least 80% of its assets in these index components, which are market cap-weighted and rebalanced semi-annually. The fund is considered non-diversified.

name: Invesco Global Water ETF
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index, as well as ADRs and GDRs that are based on the securities in the underlying index. The underlying index is comprised of securities of global exchange-listed companies located in the United States, as well as developed and emerging markets throughout the world, that create products designed to conserve and purify water for homes, businesses and industries. It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
PIO tracks a liquidity-weighted index of global companies that create products to conserve and purify water for homes, businesses, and industries.

PIO provides viable exposure to the broader global water market. The fund's (ironically appropriate) liquidity-weighting scheme produces a concentrated portfolio that only loosely resembles our market-cap-weighted benchmark. PIO is dominated by large- to midcap firms that create products that conserve and purify water for homes, businesses, and industries. Also, only companies participating in the Green Economy as determined by SustainableBusiness.com LLC are eligible for inclusion. The index currently limits weighting in both the country and issuer level, to ensure diversification between constituents. Lastly, it is important to note that the fund uses a full replication method to track the underlying index. Rebalancing is done quarterly while reconstitution is done annually.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results (before fees and expenses) of the NASDAQ OMX Global WaterTMIndex. The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index, as well as ADRs and GDRs that are based on the securities in the underlying index. The underlying index is comprised of securities of global exchange-listed companies located in the United States, as well as developed and emerging markets throughout the world, that create products designed to conserve and purify water for homes, businesses and industries. It is non-diversified.
merged_description: This ETF seeks to track a liquidity-weighted index by investing at least 90% of its total assets in the securities (including related ADRs and GDRs) of global exchange-listed companies. The index comprises firms, primarily large- to midcap, located in the United States, developed, and emerging markets, which are involved in creating products to conserve and purify water for homes, businesses, and industries. Utilizing a full replication strategy, the fund's portfolio is concentrated, reflecting the liquidity-weighting, and includes only companies participating in the Green Economy. It aims to provide viable exposure to the broader global water market, with the underlying index rebalanced quarterly and reconstituted annually.

name: iShares MSCI Global Gold Miners ETF
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the underlying index. The index has been developed by MSCI Inc. (the "index provider" or "MSCI") to target a minimum of 30 companies in developed and emerging markets that are involved in the business of gold mining. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
RING tracks a market-cap-weighted index of companies that generate revenue primarily from gold mining.

RING provides exposure to gold mining companies, as classified by GICS, from developed and emerging markets. A minimum of at least 30 securities that do not hedge to gold prices are selected from the MSCI ACWI Investable Market Index. If there are less than 30 securities, companies with hedging activities will be screened to meet criteria-based requirements. Only then can other precious metals companies outside the investable universe be considered. Weighting is based on the MSCI 25/50 methodology, such that the fund diversifies its holdings through capping limits. The index is reviewed quarterly starting every February.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the MSCI ACWI Select Gold Miners Investable Market Index. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of the underlying index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of the underlying index. The index has been developed by MSCI Inc. (the "index provider" or "MSCI") to target a minimum of 30 companies in developed and emerging markets that are involved in the business of gold mining. The fund is non-diversified.
merged_description: This ETF aims to provide exposure to global gold mining companies by tracking a market-cap-weighted index. The index targets a minimum of 30 companies primarily involved in gold mining across developed and emerging markets, with a preference for those that do not hedge gold prices. While contingency rules exist for selection if enough non-hedgers aren't available, the fund generally invests at least 80% of its assets in index components or similar investments. The underlying index utilizes the MSCI 25/50 capping methodology and is reviewed quarterly starting in February. The fund itself is classified as non-diversified.

name: The Consumer Discretionary Select Sector SPDR Fund
description_original: The Consumer Discretionary Select Sector SPDR Fund seeks to provide investment results that, before expenses, correspond generally to the price and yield performance of the Consumer Discretionary Select Sector Index (the “Index”)The Index seeks to provide an effective representation of the consumer discretionary sector of the S&P 500 IndexSeeks to provide precise exposure to companies in specialty retail; broadline retail; hotels, restaurants and leisure; textiles, apparel and luxury goods; household durables; automobiles; automobile components; distributors; leisure products; and diversified consumer services.Allows investors to take strategic or tactical positions at a more targeted level than traditional style based investing
description_eftcom: XLY is a portfolio of US large-cap consumer-discretionary stocks. XLY's basket of stocks represents the sector well, despite concentration in the largest names. As a part of the Select Sector SPDR suite, the fund pulls its holdings from the S&P 500, which differs from the broad-market universe used by competing funds in that it excludes small-caps and most midcaps. The resulting basket contains just a fraction of the names held by our more diverse benchmark, however, industry biases are small and XLY tends to provide market performance. The fund's average market cap is higher than our benchmarks, but overall XLY provides solid exposure.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks investment results that, before expenses, correspond to the price and yield performance of publicly traded equity securities of companies in the Consumer Discretionary Select Sector Index. The Advisor employs a replication strategy. The fund generally invests substantially all, but at least 95%, of its total assets in the securities comprising the index. The index includes companies that have been identified as Consumer Discretionary companies by the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS®). It is non-diversified.
merged_description: This fund aims to provide investment results corresponding to the price and yield performance of an index representing the Consumer Discretionary sector of the S&P 500 Index. Focused on US large-cap companies, it employs a replication strategy by investing substantially all assets in the index's securities, drawing its holdings exclusively from the S&P 500. The portfolio covers diverse industries within the sector, including retail, automotive, hotels, and leisure, allowing investors to take strategic or tactical positions for precise, targeted exposure to this specific market segment. While considered non-diversified and concentrated in the sector's largest names, it provides solid exposure to this key segment of the US equity market.

name: Nuveen ESG Emerging Markets Equity ETF
description_original: In seeking to track the investment results of the index, the advisor attempts to replicate the index by investing all, or substantially all, of its assets in the securities represented in the index in approximately the same proportions as the index. The index identifies equity securities from the base index that satisfy certain ESG criteria, based on ESG performance data collected by MSCI ESG Research, Inc.
description_eftcom:
NUEM tracks an index of large- and mid-cap emerging-market stocks that score highly on environmental, social, and governance (ESG) criteria. The index is optimized for market-like risk and return characteristics.

NUEM aims to invest in the most socially responsible companies while still providing reasonably market-like exposure to emerging-market stocks. The index selects large- and mid-cap stocks from its parent index, MSCI Emerging Markets Index. From there, NUEM screens out companies involved in controversial businesses, such as alcohol, weapons, nuclear power, and gambling. Companies that exceed carbon emissions thresholds are also excluded. The remaining firms are scored on ESG factors, and the highest scoring firms within each sector (the top 50% by market cap) are selected for inclusion in the fund. The portfolio is weighted according to an multi-factor optimization algorithm that tries to minimize any risk and return distortions created by the fund`s ESG screen. The index is rebalanced and reconstituted quarterly starting each February.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results, before fees and expenses, of the TIAA ESG Emerging Markets Equity Index (the "index"). In seeking to track the investment results of the index, the advisor attempts to replicate the index by investing all, or substantially all, of its assets in the securities represented in the index in approximately the same proportions as the index. The index identifies equity securities from the base index that satisfy certain ESG criteria, based on ESG performance data collected by MSCI ESG Research, Inc.
merged_description: This ETF aims to provide socially responsible exposure to large and mid-cap emerging market stocks by tracking an index that applies environmental, social, and governance (ESG) criteria. Drawing from a broad emerging markets parent index, it first screens out companies involved in controversial businesses or with high carbon emissions. From the remaining universe, it selects companies scoring highest on ESG factors, seeking representation across sectors. The underlying index is specifically optimized to maintain market-like risk and return characteristics despite these screens. The fund seeks to replicate the performance of this index by investing substantially all assets in its securities, with the portfolio rebalanced quarterly.

name: Goldman Sachs ActiveBeta Paris-Aligned U.S. Large Cap Equity ETF
description_original: The fund seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing at least 80% of its assets in securities included in its underlying index, in depositary receipts representing securities included in its underlying index and in underlying stocks in respect of depositary receipts included in its underlying index. The index is designed to deliver exposure to equity securities of large capitalization U.S. issuers.
description_eftcom:
GPAL tracks an index of tier-weighted US large-cap stocks comprising four factor sub-indices: value, momentum, quality, and low volatility. Holdings are screened and reweighted based on ESG criteria in line with the Paris Climate Agreements carbon reduction goals.

The security was delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is January 12, 2024. GPAL is a passively managed fund that combines Goldman Sachs ActiveBeta strategy with ESG screens that are aligned with the goals of the Paris Climate Agreement, that is to combat climate change and its long-term effects. To construct the portfolio, the fund initially narrows down its reference index (Solactive US Large Cap Index) by removing companies involved in controversial industries such as weapons, tobacco, and fossil fuels. In addition, firms that are deemed non-compliant with the UN Global Compact principles are also excluded. Remaining securities are assigned with a factor score in order to create four sub-indices focusing on: value, momentum, quality, and low volatility. These four sub-indices are then combined in equal weights to form the Factor Diversity Portfolio. Final security weights are adjusted in accordance with the funds target greenhouse gas emission intensity, low carbon impact, and overall factor exposures. The index rebalances quarterly.
merged_description: This fund seeks exposure to large capitalization U.S. equity securities by investing at least 80% of its assets in its underlying index or related instruments. The index employs a multi-factor strategy based on value, momentum, quality, and low volatility. A key feature is the integration of ESG criteria, including the exclusion of companies involved in controversial industries or non-compliant with UN Global Compact principles. Additionally, final portfolio weights are adjusted to align with Paris Climate Agreement carbon reduction goals and other ESG targets. The index rebalances quarterly.

name: Invesco S&P 500 Equal Weight Materials ETF
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities that comprise the underlying index. The underlying index is composed of all of the components of the S&P 500® Materials Index, an index that contains the common stocks of all companies included in the S&P 500® Index that are classified as members of the materials sector, as defined according to the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS).
description_eftcom:
RSPM tracks an equal-weighted index of US materials companies in the S&P 500.

RSPM differentiates itself by using an equal-weighting strategy, which only includes basic materials companies in the S&P 500. Smaller companies have the same weighting as giants, tilting the whole fund to midcaps. Perhaps surprisingly, this does not increase RSPM's portfolio volatility. In short, investors who want to make a less-concentrated bet on the most liquid basic materials firms can do so with confidence in RSPM. The index is rebalanced on a quarterly basis. Prior to June 7, 2023, the fund traded under the ticker RTM.
merged_description: This ETF tracks an equal-weighted index composed of U.S. materials companies found within the S&P 500. The index includes all companies classified in the materials sector according to the Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS) and is rebalanced quarterly. By weighting each company equally regardless of market capitalization, the strategy provides a less-concentrated exposure compared to market-cap weighting and tends to tilt the portfolio towards mid-capitalization stocks. This approach is noted to not increase portfolio volatility. The fund aims to invest at least 90% of its total assets in the securities of this underlying index.

name: The Cannabis ETF
description_original: The fund will invest at least 80% of its total assets in the component securities of the index. It will also invest, under normal circumstances, at least 80% of its net assets, plus borrowings for investment purposes, in exchange listed common stock (or corresponding American Depositary Receipts ("ADRs") of Cannabis Companies. The index is a proprietary, rules-based index designed to track the performance of a portfolio of Cannabis Companies. The fund is non-diversified.
description_eftcom: The security is being delisted. The last day of trading on an exchange is February 21, 2024. THCX seeks to provide exposure to cannabis companies primarily located in the US and Canada. The fund targets pure-play firms that derive at least 50% of their revenue from production and distribution of cannabis, hemp, and pharmaceutical or consumer wellness applications. The initial universe consists of publicly-listed companies involved in the legal cannabis industry. This may include securities in countries outside of North America but they must be listed on exchanges that require compliance with all laws and regulations applicable to their business. Cannabis is defined as (i) marijuana (or products derived from marijuana) and (ii) hemp (or products derived from hemp, which includes CBD-based products (i.e., products that contain cannabidiol). The index is reconstituted and rebalanced on a monthly basis. On January 20, 2023, the fund and index names changed due to reorganization. The fund previously traded as The Cannabis ETF and tracked the Innovation Labs Cannabis Index.
merged_description: This ETF aims to provide exposure to the legal cannabis industry by tracking a proprietary, rules-based index. It primarily targets publicly-listed "pure-play" companies that derive at least 50% of their revenue from the production and distribution of cannabis, hemp (including CBD products), or related pharmaceutical and consumer wellness applications. While primarily focused on firms in the US and Canada, it may include securities from other compliant markets. The fund invests at least 80% of its total and net assets in the index components, typically exchange-listed common stock or corresponding ADRs, and is considered non-diversified. The index undergoes monthly reconstitution and rebalancing. Please note that this security is being delisted, with the final day of trading scheduled for February 21, 2024.

name: iShares Biotechnology ETF
description_original: The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. It is non-diversified.
description_eftcom:
IBB tracks the performance of a modified market-cap-weighted index of US biotechnology companies listed on US exchanges.

IBB tracks an index of US biotechnology companies listed on the major US exchanges. This includes companies engaged in the research and development of therapeutic treatments but are not focused on the commercialization and mass production of pharmaceutical drugs. This also includes companies that are engaged in the production of tools or systems that enable biotechnology processes. IBB includes companies of all capitalizations, and weights using a modified market-cap methodology. Individual holdings are subject to capping requirements, 8% on the five largest constituents and 4% for the remaining. The index is rebalanced quarterly and fully reconstituted annually in December. Prior to June 21, 2021, the fund was named iShares Nasdaq Biotechnology ETF and tracked the NASDAQ Biotechnology Index.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the NYSE Biotechnology Index composed of U.S.-listed equities in the biotechnology sector. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents. It is non-diversified.
merged_description: The fund seeks to track the investment results of the NYSE Biotechnology Index, composed of U.S.-listed biotechnology sector equities of all capitalizations. This index utilizes a modified market-cap weighting methodology with individual holding capping and focuses on companies involved in R&D, therapeutic treatments, and enabling technologies. The fund generally invests at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its underlying index or economically equivalent investments, with flexibility to invest up to 20% in certain futures, options, swap contracts, cash, and cash equivalents. The index is rebalanced quarterly and reconstituted annually. The fund is non-diversified.

name: iShares ESG Aware Aggressive Allocation ETF
description_original: The fund is a fund of funds and seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing primarily in underlying funds that themselves seek investment results corresponding to their own respective underlying indexes each of which takes into account ESG characteristics. The underlying index is composed of a portfolio of underlying equity and fixed income funds with positive environmental, social, and governance characteristics intended to represent an aggressive risk profile.
description_eftcom: EAOA is part of iShares suite of target-risk strategies that screens for positive ESG traits. The fund invests exclusively in iShares ETFs aiming for exposure that is consistent with aggressive risk tolerance. The index allocates its assets to four equity ETFs (ESGU, ESML, ESGD, ESGE) and one fixed income ETF (EAGG). The equity basket has a fixed 80% allocation and provides an all-cap exposure to developed and emerging markets securities, while the fixed income basket has a fixed 20% allocation to broad USD-denominated investment grade bonds. The index rebalances semi-annually to realign the allocations. Prior to February 19, 2025, the fund name was iShares ESG Aware Aggressive Allocation ETF.
description_moringstar: The investment seeks to track the investment results of the BlackRock ESG Aware Aggressive Allocation Index (the “underlying index”). The fund is a fund of funds and seeks to achieve its investment objective by investing primarily in underlying funds that themselves seek investment results corresponding to their own respective underlying indexes each of which takes into account ESG characteristics. The underlying index is composed of a portfolio of underlying equity and fixed income funds with positive environmental, social, and governance characteristics intended to represent an aggressive risk profile.
merged_description: This fund is designed to track an index representing an aggressive allocation strategy focused on environmental, social, and governance (ESG) characteristics. Operating as a fund of funds, it seeks to achieve its objective by investing exclusively in underlying ETFs that themselves incorporate ESG considerations. The portfolio is composed of underlying equity and fixed income funds, targeting an aggressive risk profile typically with an allocation of approximately 80% to global equity providing all-cap exposure to developed and emerging markets, and 20% to broad USD-denominated investment grade bonds. The underlying index undergoes semi-annual rebalancing to maintain its target allocation.

name: MicroSectors U.S. Big Oil Index 3X Leveraged ETNs
description_original: The notes are senior unsecured medium-term notes issued by Bank of Montreal with a return linked to a three times leveraged participation in the performance of the index, compounded daily, less a Daily Investor Fee, the Daily Financing Charge and, if applicable, the Redemption Fee Amount. The index is an equal-dollar weighted index designed to represent the 10 U.S. listed stocks with the largest market capitalization in the energy/oil sector.
description_eftcom:
NRGU tracks three times the performance of an equal-weighted index of US Oil & Gas companies.

NRGU is a leveraged take on the US Oil and Gas industry and tracks three times its underlying index. The index selects the 10 most liquid stocks from the Solactive GBS United States Large & Mid Cap Index, screened for market cap and liquidity. Specifically, those with above USD 1 billion free-float market cap and those with minimum of 1-month and 6-month ADTV above USD 25 million are included. The index is weighted equally and TRBC Oil & Gas Industry classification is used. Its worth noting that the product isnt designed for long-term investors. The fund rebalances daily.
